{"id": "38592", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38592", "title": "Fael", "text": "Fael, also known as \"Darcin Cole\", is ostensibly a merchant operating a stall outside the &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale%20Inn\"&gt;Imnesvale Inn&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; area map during the campaign.\nIdentity.\nIn reality, he is an agent of the &lt;a href=\"Twisted%20Rune\"&gt;Twisted Rune&lt;/a&gt;, and a contact for &lt;a href=\"Rejiek%20Hidesman\"&gt;Rejiek Hidesman&lt;/a&gt; as part of a scheme to create a suit of enchanted &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Armor\"&gt;Leather Armor&lt;/a&gt; made from &lt;a href=\"Human%20Flesh\"&gt;Human Flesh&lt;/a&gt;. This is part of a quest.\nDestroying the Twisted Rune.\nIf instead of completing the armor you wish to destroy the Twisted Rune, talk to Fael, buy the \"History of the Zhentarim\" book from him. When he asks you about your choice of reading material, confront him about his connection to &lt;a href=\"Rejiek%20Hidesman\"&gt;Rejiek Hidesman&lt;/a&gt; (\"Your business is over! I know of your relationship with the tanner in Athkatla\"). This will cause him to leave and go to &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale%20Inn\"&gt;Imnesvale Inn&lt;/a&gt;. Enter the inn and attack him WITHOUT killing him immediately. Some of his allies will appear and the fight will commence. Kill Fael and his allies but be careful not to kill any innocents in the inn (massive reputation loss).\nFael's Potions.\nPrior to revealing his identity as Darcin Cole, Fael operates as a merchant, who can Identify items, but from which you cannot steal. He has a limited stock of potions and books.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Adalon%27s%20Blood\"&gt;Adalon's Blood&lt;/a&gt; mod adds content regarding Fael and his role in the &lt;a href=\"Finish%20the%20leather%20armor%20begun%20by%20Rejiek%20Hidesman\"&gt;Finish the leather armor begun by Rejiek Hidesman&lt;/a&gt; questline."}
{"id": "2606", "revid": "3482277", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2606", "title": "Faerun", "text": ""}
{"id": "2561", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2561", "title": "Faer\u00fbn", "text": "Faer\u00fbn is a continent on the world of &lt;a href=\"Toril\"&gt;Toril&lt;/a&gt; in which the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Tethyr\"&gt;Tethyr&lt;/a&gt; are located, home to the settings of the \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" series.\nIt is where the majority of the &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Aforgottenrealms%3AForgotten%20Realms\"&gt;Forgotten Realms&lt;/a&gt; games and novels are set."}
