{"id": "50224", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50224", "title": "Faheed", "text": "Faheed is encountered by the player during the expansion in &lt;a href=\"Faheed%27s%20Home\"&gt;Faheed's Home&lt;/a&gt; within the village of &lt;a href=\"Amkethran\"&gt;Amkethran&lt;/a&gt;. He is with his wife &lt;a href=\"Majira\"&gt;Majira&lt;/a&gt;. They are both experienced former adventurers. Later in the quest, he will have a potential role to play for you so that you may continue your mission.\nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes a few alterations to Faheed. He is made a Fighter Mage 20/20, gets an SCS mage script, carries some random treasure, has his saving throws improved slightly, and his spell memorization is improved to be commensurate with a level 20 mage. If you have installed the \"Smarter Mages\" component, and if your difficulty level is high enough, he also has access to two mage HLA's and spell sequencers/triggers are ready to use. If you have the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod installed, then you he will have the SR arcane spells versions memorized."}
{"id": "50216", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50216", "title": "Faheed's Home", "text": "Within this home are a married couple, &lt;a href=\"Faheed\"&gt;Faheed&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Majira\"&gt;Majira&lt;/a&gt;, who are former Adventurers. If you speak with Faheed he says \"\"Greetings, my name is Faheed. I wish we had the room to offer you a place to rest... Perhaps you should best try the inn\".\" \nIf you address Majira she replies \"Be on your way, whoever you are\".\nThere are two containers in the home with unknown contents. Beware trying to take anything from these, they are watching you.\nMuch later in the game, these two will have a potential role in your adventure, so killing them would be a poor choice for your ability to fulfill your mission."}
{"id": "7726", "revid": "234572", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7726", "title": "Fahrington", "text": "Fahrington is an elf in the north-western part of the &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Wood\"&gt;Spider Wood&lt;/a&gt; area. He is not easily seen, dressed in clothing the same color as the rocky ground on which he stands. He has had his \"scroll of wisdom\" (&lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Scroll%20of%20Foolishness\"&gt;Cursed Scroll of Foolishness&lt;/a&gt;) stolen by a &lt;a href=\"Tasloi\"&gt;Tasloi&lt;/a&gt;. If you have a &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt; of at least 7, he asks you to recover it for him, which begins the quest &lt;a href=\"Fahrington%27s%20Scroll\"&gt;Fahrington's Scroll&lt;/a&gt; (see below).\nDialogue.\nWhen you first speak to Fahrington he will give you the quest Fahrington's Scroll in one of two ways (based on your &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt;):\n\"A tasloi has stolen my scroll of wisdom, wanderer, and fled to the east. If you could retrieve it for me, your karma shall exceed your wildest expectations.\"\n-or-\n\"A tasloi has stolen my scroll of wisdom, wanderer, and fled eastward towards the ettercap's lair. The poor tasloi is probably quite dead by now but the ettercaps, of course, will not recognize the scroll's value. If you could retrieve it for me, I promise to brighten your karma.\"\nOther things he may say:"}
{"id": "9084", "revid": "39375451", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9084", "title": "Fahrington's Scroll", "text": "Fahrington's Scroll is the side quest to find &lt;a href=\"Fahrington\"&gt;Fahrington&lt;/a&gt;'s \"scroll of wisdom\" and return it to him. You will find it in the possession of an &lt;a href=\"ettercap\"&gt;ettercap&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"coordinates\"&gt;coordinates&lt;/a&gt; x3525, y605 in &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Wood\"&gt;Spider Wood&lt;/a&gt;. In appearance it is a Protection From Cold scroll, but if you cast &lt;a href=\"Identify%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Identify&lt;/a&gt; on it, it will be revealed as a &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Scroll%20of%20Foolishness\"&gt;Cursed Scroll of Foolishness&lt;/a&gt;. It is Fahrington's gift to you for retrieving it, although it is unclear how this will aid your karma, or his."}
{"id": "39380", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39380", "title": "Failed Phylactery", "text": "The Failed Phylactery is an attempt by the &lt;a href=\"Lich\"&gt;Lich&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Coldhearth%20Lich\"&gt;Coldhearth&lt;/a&gt; to create the &lt;a href=\"Coldhearth%20Phylactery\"&gt;Coldhearth Phylactery&lt;/a&gt;. The Failed Phylactery can be found with the &lt;a href=\"Notes%20on%20a%20Failed%20Experiment\"&gt;Notes on a Failed Experiment&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Lich%20Outpost\"&gt;Lich Outpost&lt;/a&gt; atop the Laboratory desk."}
