{"id": "13955", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13955", "title": "Fanegonorom", "text": "Fanegonorom is a &lt;a href=\"revenant\"&gt;revenant&lt;/a&gt; ancestor of &lt;a href=\"Korlasz\"&gt;Korlasz&lt;/a&gt; that the party can awaken from his slumber in the &lt;a href=\"Korlasz%20Family%20Tomb\"&gt;Korlasz Family Tomb&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nHe is not initially hostile to the party if they open his sarcophagus but do not loot its contents (one &lt;a href=\"emerald\"&gt;emerald&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Pearl%20Necklace\"&gt;Pearl Necklace&lt;/a&gt;, and ). As it is often natural to loot such containers, it can be easy to miss his dialogue and resulting &lt;a href=\"The%20Mummy%27s%20Orders\"&gt;The Mummy's Orders&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nIf the party is respectful toward him, they can promise to rid his tomb of intruders and learn a little about the Korlasz family. If they complete his quest successfully, he will reward them with the &lt;a href=\"Shield%20of%20Egons\"&gt;Shield of Egons +2&lt;/a&gt;. \nIf the party elects to fight him (whether through dialogue or by angering him by looting his tomb) he will cast &lt;a href=\"Aura%20of%20Fear\"&gt;Aura of Fear&lt;/a&gt; at the start of battle, and his attack inflicts a disease which causes continuous 1 &lt;a href=\"poison%20damage\"&gt;poison damage&lt;/a&gt; and -2 &lt;a href=\"charisma\"&gt;charisma&lt;/a&gt;. The disease will wear off on its own and does not require &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Disease\"&gt;Cure Disease&lt;/a&gt;. \nHe will also summon other undead to aid his battle with the party, with a varying type of undead allies based on the game difficulty selection."}
