{"id": "40029", "revid": "269383", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40029", "title": "Farmer Brun's Missing Son", "text": "Farmer &lt;a href=\"Brun\"&gt;Brun&lt;/a&gt; can be found in the farm area of the fishing village north of the &lt;a href=\"Friendly%20Arm%20Inn\"&gt;Friendly Arm Inn&lt;/a&gt;.\nTalk to him and he'll tell you his son is missing and suspects bandits have taken him.\nHis son is located in the &lt;a href=\"Ankheg%20Pit\"&gt;Ankheg Pit&lt;/a&gt; just west of Farmer Brun's house . If you're comfortable with &lt;a href=\"Ankheg\"&gt;Ankheg&lt;/a&gt;s, feel free to climb down:\nJournal.\nUpon finishing:\nDialog.\nUpon returning with his dead son's body: \nFarmer Brun: \"Have you found my son? Is he well?\"&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; : \"I am afraid Nathan is dead, sir. He died defending your farm from a nest of strange beasts.\"&lt;br&gt;\nFarmer Brun: \"No, my only son... It is a black day. He died for his farm, but I am too old to work for it, and too poor to hire someone else. I've lost him AND the land. At least now I know. Thank you for your help but... I wish to be alone now.\"&lt;br&gt;"}
