{"id": "8155", "revid": "4868365", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8155", "title": "Farmlands", "text": "The\u00a0Farmlands, also known as Upper Chionthar, lie to the east of the city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and to the north of &lt;a href=\"Wyrm%27s%20Crossing\"&gt;Wyrm's Crossing&lt;/a&gt;. The eastern side of the river is inaccessible.\nCharacters.\n&lt;a href=\"Wenric\"&gt;Wenric&lt;/a&gt;\nEnemies.\n&lt;a href=\"Zombie\"&gt;Zombie&lt;/a&gt;s from the quest mentioned below.\nNotable Loot.\nInside &lt;a href=\"Wenric%27s%20House\"&gt;Wenric's House&lt;/a&gt;, there is a &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Protection%20%2B1\"&gt;Cloak of Protection +1&lt;/a&gt; in a locked chest of drawers.\nPlot.\nThis is an optional area.\nSide quests.\n&lt;a href=\"Zombie%20Infestation\"&gt;Zombie Infestation&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "35541", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35541", "title": "Magical Rope", "text": "Magical rope is a &lt;a href=\"miscellaneous%20item\"&gt;miscellaneous item&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". As its name suggests, it is a length of enchanted rope that is required to descend from the &lt;a href=\"Underwater%20City\"&gt;Underwater City&lt;/a&gt; down the great hole into the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt; below.\nAcquisition.\nThe magical rope is obtained in the &lt;a href=\"Underwater%20City\"&gt;Underwater City&lt;/a&gt;, after the party has been brought here by the &lt;a href=\"sahuagin\"&gt;sahuagin&lt;/a&gt;. There are multiple ways to obtain the rope, and the party is not required to take sides in any conflict:"}
{"id": "5056", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5056", "title": "Magical Stone", "text": "Magical Stone is a 1st level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; only usable by &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt;s. It deals 1d4 direct magic damage.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this divine spell, revising its effects, class availability, casting time, duration and description. See below:\nMagical Stone\nLevel: 1\nSchool: Enchantment\nSphere: Combat\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 2 turns\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nUsing this spell, the priest can temporarily enchant ten small stones, no larger than sling bullets. The character using them can then hurl up to three stones per round at an opponent, with a +1 bonus to attack rolls. Each stone that hits inflict 1d4+2 points of crushing damage (1d4+5 against undead) and is considered to be of +1 enchantment to determine what it can hit. The magic in each stone expires after 2 turns or when used."}
