{"id": "32661", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32661", "title": "Magical damage", "text": "&lt;onlyinclude&gt;Magical damage is one of the 10 main damage types of the game, typically inflicted by spells like &lt;a href=\"Skull%20Trap\"&gt;Skull Trap&lt;/a&gt; or items like &lt;a href=\"The%20Victor\"&gt;The Victor&lt;/a&gt;. The term Magical Damage can also be referred to as Magic Energy Damage, such as seen in the 6th Level arcane spell &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magic%20Energy\"&gt;Protection From Magic Energy&lt;/a&gt;. \nNote: \"Resistance to Magical damage has nothing to do with &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and must not be confused with it. The former allows to alter the amount of damage received from one of the damage types \u2013 Magical damage \u2013 the latter is a percentage chance for a spell to have no effects whatsoever, damage or otherwise. They are both stats that belong to the creature on the receiving end, like resistance to &lt;a href=\"Physical%20damage\"&gt;Physical damage&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt;. In-game, the term \"Magic\" actually refers to *Magic resistance* in the character sheet, as can be seen in the screenshot.\"&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;"}
