{"id": "32744", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32744", "title": "Magical item", "text": "Magical is an item property in the . It is not to be confused with the enchantment of an &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt;, and in this context, the terminology not always follows the one used in the \"&lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Aforgottenrealms%3ADungeons%20%26amp%3B%20Dragons\"&gt;Advanced Dungeons &amp; Dragons&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Aforgottenrealms%3A2nd%20edition%20sourcebooks\"&gt;2nd edition sourcebook&lt;/a&gt; publications.\nBackground.\nMagical &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt;s are not necessarily also enchanted, while on the other hand not every &lt;a href=\"enchanted%20item\"&gt;enchanted item&lt;/a&gt; has to be magical. While the enchantment mostly determines if a &lt;a href=\"weapon\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; will hit opponents with immunities up to certain , the property \"magical\" is referred to, among other things, by protection spells: &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Normal Weapons&lt;/a&gt;. Though &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt; works differently, in case of the former two &lt;a href=\"spells\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"ammunition\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt;, \"not\" the \"weapon\" it's fired with, is taken into account.\nSee the following for an \u2013 as of May 09, 2019, completely incomplete \u2013 overview of all magical items and especially weapons:\nImmunities.\n&lt;a href=\"Creatures\"&gt;Creatures&lt;/a&gt; can be immune to or &lt;a href=\"normal%20weapons\"&gt;normal weapons&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 in some cases both \u2013 without necessarily resorting to the above mentioned &lt;a href=\"spells\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt;. Such immunities can include an additional enchantment threshold: theoretically it's possible for a creature to be protected from magical weapons with an enchantment level of up to four and simultaneously from normal weapons with no enchantment.\nSee the following for an \u2013 as of May 17, 2019, completely incomplete \u2013 overview of creatures with immunities to:\nProtection From Normal Missiles.\nBeing magical, does not automatically mean, this type of &lt;a href=\"ammunition\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; will hit a &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;protected from normal missiles&lt;/a&gt;; see the list of &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles%23Affected%20items\"&gt;affected items&lt;/a&gt; on that &lt;a href=\"spell\"&gt;spell&lt;/a&gt;'s article for an overview.\nEditor's note.\nThe will place &lt;a href=\"items\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt; automatically in the related categories if the according parameter, codice_1, is set."}
