{"id": "51293", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51293", "title": "Magma Ball", "text": "Magma Ball is an innate ability effect available to most &lt;a href=\"Magma%20Mephit\"&gt;Magma Mephit&lt;/a&gt; creatures in the game saga. \nEffects.\nThe spell effect is uninterruptable and takes almost no time to deploy. A lava projectile is launched at a single target in range. It will strike the target and inflict 1d6 &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe innate ability has no saving throw, ignores magic resistance and has level 2 spell power, and thus could be blocked by spell protections like &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;."}
