{"id": "47336", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47336", "title": "Magma Mephit", "text": "A Magma Mephit is an extra-planar \"outsider\" (i.e., linked to various Elemental, Quasi-Elemental and Outer planes of existence). These creatures are similar to &lt;a href=\"Imp\"&gt;Imps&lt;/a&gt;. The are found in a number of areas during the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;\"Baldur's Gate II\"&lt;/a&gt; games.\nGameplay.\nThe Magma Mephit is one of the more dangerous varieties in the game. It needs to get fairly close in order to attack in melee with its Firey claws, or near enough to get within range of its innate ability attack, the &lt;a href=\"Magma%20Ball\"&gt;Magma Ball&lt;/a&gt;. The creature is scripted to use its &lt;a href=\"Blur\"&gt;Blur&lt;/a&gt; spell once an enemy is spotted, which will improve the creatures armor class and saving throws. A few seconds later it will launch a Magma Ball at the nearest detected target. It can fire another on a eight second interval. The creature has an unlimited use of the magma attack. \nA Magma Mephit has elemental fire resistance and will be healed by fire damage. See the InfoBox for a list of status effect immunities."}
{"id": "29819", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29819", "title": "Magreb", "text": "Magreb is an elven &lt;a href=\"ranger\"&gt;ranger&lt;/a&gt; who lives in a house to the north of the entrance to the goblin encampment in &lt;a href=\"Adoy%27s%20Enclave\"&gt;Adoy's Enclave&lt;/a&gt;. He's unstable because the goblins killed his close friend &lt;a href=\"Rilsa\"&gt;Rilsa&lt;/a&gt;. He asks the party to give her a proper burial and get &lt;a href=\"Rilsa%27s%20Ring\"&gt;her ring&lt;/a&gt;. He has some information about &lt;a href=\"Adoy\"&gt;Adoy&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"wild%20mage\"&gt;wild mage&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Neera\"&gt;Neera&lt;/a&gt; is seeking, and the goblins."}
{"id": "9989", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9989", "title": "Magreb and Rilsa", "text": "This quest can be obtained in &lt;a href=\"Adoy%27s%20Enclave\"&gt;Adoy's Enclave&lt;/a&gt;, an area located to south of &lt;a href=\"Firewine%20Bridge\"&gt;Firewine Bridge&lt;/a&gt; and unlocked by &lt;a href=\"Neera\"&gt;Neera&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Neera%20%28quest%29\"&gt;companion quest.&lt;/a&gt;\nTalk to &lt;a href=\"Magreb\"&gt;Magreb&lt;/a&gt; (x = 1215, y = 1090) just outside of an old run-down house with a hole in the roof and what looks like the front door on the ground. (Like many ruined houses, it cannot be entered.) The ranger will ask you to find the remembrance of his close friend whose life has been taken by the goblins.\nFind &lt;a href=\"Rilsa\"&gt;Rilsa&lt;/a&gt;'s remains at southeastern part of the goblin cave. Next to the treasure pile, there is a corpse on the ground with a leather armor and two swords and other trash loot on top of it, take it all and click on the corpse to notice it is Rilsa's (the cursor turns to a small circle showing you can interact with it). Give her a proper burial and take &lt;a href=\"Rilsa%27s%20Ring\"&gt;the ring&lt;/a&gt;. Return to Magreb, he'll take the ring and reward you with 250 XP for granting her a final rest. Margreb will also give you 250 XP for slaying the hobgoblin inside the cave and another 250 XP for finding the ring."}
{"id": "48768", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48768", "title": "Mahar", "text": "Mahar is a &lt;a href=\"monk\"&gt;monk&lt;/a&gt; assassin hired by an anti-magic faction in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign. He only appears in the &lt;a href=\"The%20Planar%20Sphere\"&gt;Planar Sphere&lt;/a&gt; during the final phase of the &lt;a href=\"Mage%20Stronghold\"&gt;Mage Stronghold&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nAs a monk, Mahar fights entirely unarmed, having no weapons or armor. He is accompanied by six others, including four fighter-assassins named &lt;a href=\"Sergeant%20Natula\"&gt;Sergeant Natula&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Tyrian\"&gt;Tyrian&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Vilhelm\"&gt;Vilhelm&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Jalin%20Tix\"&gt;Jalin Tix&lt;/a&gt;, along with &lt;a href=\"Alnarow\"&gt;Alnarow&lt;/a&gt; (a &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;Thief&lt;/a&gt;), and &lt;a href=\"Sorsha\"&gt;Sorsha&lt;/a&gt; (a &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt;)."}
{"id": "55039", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55039", "title": "Maharajah", "text": "Maharaja the &lt;a href=\"Rakshasa\"&gt;Rakshasa&lt;/a&gt; can be encountered during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe raksasha will attempt to pollute the battlefield with a &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Lightning\"&gt;Chain Lightning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cloudkill\"&gt;Cloudkill&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Storm\"&gt;Ice Storm&lt;/a&gt;. If able, he'll fire off various offensive damage spells as shown in the InfoBox. Remember, the raksasha are immune to spells with a &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; between 1 through 7, and thus he won't be touched by any of the AoE spells he will try.\nThe unmodified creature's game script will fire off offensive spells at any nearest target, but the script has no idea if the target is protected, or if the spell will bounce back. it also can't remove spell protections or dispel an opponent. It can only attack and has no defensive buffs. \nIn close quarters combat the creature will conduct melee attacks with his rapid APR longsword ability. \nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises this raksasha. A new \"Smarter Mage\" AI script is assigned. The maharajah's experience level is raised to 17. \nA new battery of memorized arcane spells are scripted for use. The creature will be able to launch a chain of protective buffs at the outset of hostilities, to include: &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Haste\"&gt;Improved Haste&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;.\nA set of prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trigger\"&gt;Spell Trigger&lt;/a&gt; are scripted for instant deployment.\nA scripted potion is assigned for healing purposes.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod the creature's spell versions will be the SR variety. Expect being unable to break the mage's invisibility and illusions due to SR's Non-Detection. Peel away the protective layers first."}
{"id": "12748", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12748", "title": "Maheer", "text": "Maheer is a merchant from &lt;a href=\"Rashemen\"&gt;Rashemen&lt;/a&gt; who now does business in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign.\nHours and Locations.\nDuring the day, he has an outdoor stall in Waukeen's Promenade . At night (21:30 to 6:30) he can be found west of &lt;a href=\"Enge%27s%20Shop\"&gt;Enge's Shop&lt;/a&gt;, inside the &lt;a href=\"Weaponsmith%20%28Waukeen%27s%20Promenade%29\"&gt;Weaponsmith shop&lt;/a&gt; which is empty during the day. Maheer is only labelled as \"Storekeep\" in dialog, and as \"Merchant\" in the Buy/Sell screen.\nDialog.\nOf the weapons he sells, \"Maheer has all kinds to offer... scimitars, swords\u00a0 even iron weapons from the Storm Horn Mountains!\" Regarding \"special weapons\" he replies again in the 3rd-person, \"\"Maheer does not possess the craft to create weapons, himself. There is a fine dwarven smith in this city who knows such skills. The stout one's name be &lt;a href=\"Cromwell\"&gt;Cromwell&lt;/a&gt;, my Lord... and his shop is within the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Docks District&lt;/a&gt; here in the city.\"\"\nMaheer and &lt;a href=\"Minsc\"&gt;Minsc&lt;/a&gt; might have a side-conversation if he is in the party.\nThe Horns of Vahalla.\nAfter mentioning Cromwell, he proudly switches to 1st-person to announce that he can upgrade the Horn of Vahalla.\"I will tell you one thing, my Lord... I can create the finest of musical horns -- the dwarf knows not of this art.\"Maheer is the only NPC in the game who can upgrade it, starting with the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Horn%20of%20Valhalla\"&gt;Silver Horn of Valhalla&lt;/a&gt;, then to &lt;a href=\"Bronze%20Horn%20of%20Valhalla\"&gt;Bronze&lt;/a&gt;, and finally to &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Horn%20of%20Valhalla\"&gt;Iron.&lt;/a&gt;\"Ah, yes... the old magic of my family shall turn your fine horn into the great Iron Horn. Rarely have a \"[sic]\" seen its like, casadhi... here you go. Use it well.\"\nBuy and Sell.\nBesides upgrading the horn, his notable items include &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20Throwing%20Dagger\"&gt;Poisoned Throwing Daggers&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Arrows of Fire&lt;/a&gt;, and a number of +1 weapons and +2 missiles."}
