{"id": "6696", "revid": "8506165", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6696", "title": "Mana Bow", "text": "The Mana Bow +4 is an enchanted longbow which offers the wielder 20% resistance to magical damage.\nGameplay.\nThis longbow can launch any arrow ammunition available in the game. \nThe bow provides a 5 point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus to hit and has a base rate of fire of 2 &lt;a href=\"Attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;Attacks per round&lt;/a&gt;. Weapon proficiency in Longbows can influence this bow's effectiveness.\nWhile the bow is equipped the wielder receives a 20% resistance to &lt;a href=\"Magical%20damage\"&gt;Magical energy damage&lt;/a&gt; - such as is produced from a &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Abi-Dalzim%27s%20Horrid%20Wilting\"&gt;Abi-Dalzim's Horrid Wilting&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Finger%20of%20Death\"&gt;Finger of Death&lt;/a&gt; spells.\nThe bow is a launcher of ammunition, and its +4 enchantment rating is not transferred to the missile aimed at a target for the purposes of what the ammunition can strike. For example, an ordinary &lt;a href=\"Arrow\"&gt;Arrow&lt;/a&gt; fired from this bow is still a non-magical and unenchanted missile when it attempts to strike a target creature.\nAcquisition.\nFound in a pool within the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Tethir%20Cave\"&gt;cave&lt;/a&gt; that's located in the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Tethir%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;Forest of Tethir&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; of the \"Shadows of Amn\" campaign."}
