{"id": "2650", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2650", "title": "Manor House", "text": "The Manor House is the large home located in the northeast area of the town of &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt;. The front door is locked. There is nothing to do here except loot the house of its belongings. Be aware that opening the locked container near the front door and the one in &lt;a href=\"Samantha\"&gt;Samantha&lt;/a&gt;'s room within eyesight of the residents will result in two &lt;a href=\"Amnian%20Soldier%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;Amnian Soldiers&lt;/a&gt; being summoned.\nGround Floor.\nThe ground floor is populated by the &lt;a href=\"Nobleman\"&gt;owner&lt;/a&gt; and his &lt;a href=\"Noblewoman\"&gt;wife&lt;/a&gt;. Neither carries any pickpocket items and &lt;a href=\"Charmed\"&gt;charming&lt;/a&gt; them reveals no useful information. \nThe console table in the foyer is locked and contains . The four bookcases against the wall contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Bell%20in%20the%20Depths\"&gt;History of the Bell in the Depths&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Chosen%20of%20Mystra\"&gt;History of the Chosen of Mystra&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Tethyr\"&gt;History of Tethyr&lt;/a&gt;. The three bookcases in the small office contain a scroll of &lt;a href=\"Chill%20Touch\"&gt;Chill Touch&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield&lt;/a&gt; along with copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20XII\"&gt;History of Shadowdale XII&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20XIII\"&gt;History of Shadowdale XIII&lt;/a&gt;.\nSecond Floor.\nOn the second floor you can speak to Samantha for information on the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;mines&lt;/a&gt; or if you want to meet her boyfriend &lt;a href=\"Jamie\"&gt;Jamie&lt;/a&gt;. The Noblewoman carries nothing.\nThe desk by the stairs is locked and contains and a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20IX\"&gt;History of Shadowdale IX&lt;/a&gt;. The chest of drawers near the doorway in Samantha's bedroom is unlocked and contains and a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invisibility\"&gt;Potion of Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;. The chest of drawers near the bed is locked and contains a &lt;a href=\"Murky%20Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Healing&lt;/a&gt; and .\nThe bookcases along the outer walls of the floor contains copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Last%20March%20of%20the%20Giants\"&gt;History of the Last March of the Giants&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Moonsea\"&gt;History of the Moonsea&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20I\"&gt;History of the North I&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20II\"&gt;History of the North II&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20III\"&gt;History of the North III&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20IV\"&gt;History of the North IV&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20V\"&gt;History of the North V&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20VI\"&gt;History of the North VI&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20North%20VII\"&gt;History of the North VII&lt;/a&gt;.\nNotes.\nThe Manor House and &lt;a href=\"Travenhurst%20Manor\"&gt;Travenhurst Manor&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt; use identical interior maps for both floors."}
{"id": "5865", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5865", "title": "Mantle", "text": "Mantle confers complete invulnerability to all weapons of +2 or lower enchantment.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this spell to self only.\nUpon completion of the spell a text is displayed reading \"Protected by Mantle\".\nThe caster has a brief 3D effect and color glow animation rendered over their sprite.\nA player character shows an icon (No. 104) titled \"Mantle\" on their portrait.\nAdditionally, a sound effect will audible when the spell expires.\nThe spell implements protection from all weapon attacks (melee or missile) including normal weapons/missiles, and magical/enchanted ones that are less than +3 enchantment value.\nThis spell can be removed by an appropriate &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect, or a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset has no Wizard spell, or equivalent spell to \"Mantle\". The game version of this spell is entirely a Bioware creation.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced the \"Mantle\" spell with the spell described below:\nPrismatic Mantle\nLevel: 7\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 6 rounds\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: Caster\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen this spell is cast, an opaque globe of shimmering, multicolored light temporarily surrounds the caster. Opponents that hit the caster with a weapon or spell from within this radius are subject to a random prismatic effect. Due to this spell\u2019s short casting time and duration, it is mainly used to buy the wizard a few rounds in the thick of combat."}
