{"id": "8654", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8654", "title": "Marek", "text": "Marek is an assassin hired by the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt; to kill &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party. Unlike the other assassins, he will try to achieve this through poison instead of open battle as the antagonist of the &lt;a href=\"Marek%20and%20Lothander\"&gt;Marek and Lothander&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nQuest.\nThe first time you'll encounter Marek and his partner &lt;a href=\"Lothander\"&gt;Lothander&lt;/a&gt; is when you travel to the eastern section of the district of &lt;a href=\"Northeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Northeast Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. Marek will immediately initiate dialogue and instruct you to cease interfering with their employer's business. Then they both head off and disappear.\nOnce you've completed all of the necessary actions to solve Lothander's dilemma, he'll provide you with the &lt;a href=\"Blushing%20Mermaid\"&gt;location&lt;/a&gt; of Marek so you can obtain his half of the &lt;a href=\"Marek%27s%20Potion%20of%20Antidote\"&gt;antidote&lt;/a&gt;.\nMarek is located on the second floor of the inn towards the rear of the gambling hall. This time you must initiate dialogue and then fighting commences.\nIf you do not want to do this quest but still want to go to the area of the city Marek is in, you can simply kill him on sight to avoid getting poisoned at all. You also get almost 5k XP and some good loot (but you miss out on more XP and loot from the quest)."}
{"id": "11074", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11074", "title": "Marek's Potion of Antidote", "text": "Marek's Potion of Antidote can be obtained only from &lt;a href=\"Marek\"&gt;Marek&lt;/a&gt; himself in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Five\"&gt;Chapter Five&lt;/a&gt;. It is the end goal of the quest &lt;a href=\"Marek%20and%20Lothander\"&gt;Marek and Lothander&lt;/a&gt; and is needed to cure the party of a deadly poison in . It can be used up to ten times but only the &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;protagonist&lt;/a&gt; needs to drink it, and only once.\nIn the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Original BG1&lt;/a&gt;, this item is not actually the cure to Marek's poison. To be healed, the player must talk to Marek towards the end of the quest, or talk with &lt;a href=\"Tethtoril\"&gt;Tethtoril&lt;/a&gt; in Candlekeep before the poison kills them. Only the Marek route will provide &lt;a href=\"Experience%20Tables\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt; and an acknowledgement that the party was healed."}
{"id": "20185", "revid": "978785", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20185", "title": "Marek's potion of antidote", "text": ""}
{"id": "10982", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10982", "title": "Marek and Lothander", "text": "The party is poisoned by an &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt; assassin named &lt;a href=\"Marek\"&gt;Marek&lt;/a&gt; and must find an antidote in ten days or die. His partner, &lt;a href=\"Lothander\"&gt;Lothander&lt;/a&gt;, offers to help if you find a way to free him of his &lt;a href=\"geas\"&gt;geas&lt;/a&gt;.\nAcquisition.\nThe \"pre-quest\" begins when the party is approached by Marek and Lothander in the eastern section of &lt;a href=\"Northeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Northeast Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; district. Marek tells them to leave or there will be dire consequences. What the protagonist replies to him has no effect on the outcome of the quest. However, if Marek is attacked and killed there, then he can never poison the party and the quest is avoided.\nThe actual quest begins when the protagonist meets Lothander in the &lt;a href=\"Marketplace%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;marketplace&lt;/a&gt; in the district of &lt;a href=\"Central%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Central Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. He will inform the party that they were poisoned while they slept and they will all die in ten days. At this point the ten day quest timer has just begun and the Marek and Lothander quest will be entered in the quest section of your Journal (see below).\nA slight hope.\nLothander tells the party he has the antidote but he will only give it to them if they will help to release him from a geas that binds him to the Iron Throne's service. If the party tells him \"No\" he leaves, and they will not be able to talk to him again, resulting in their death from poisoning later on, which cannot be cured and ends the game. Killing him or pick pocketing him will also result in death as the cure he has on him is fake. If the player agrees to help him he leads the player to the &lt;a href=\"Diviner%20%28NPC%29\"&gt;Diviner&lt;/a&gt; who he thinks can tell them how to break his geas. It costs 50 gold to get a reading for Lothander. The player can refuse but, again, it only results in the party's death.\nThe Diviner tells the party that only the high priestess of &lt;a href=\"Umberlee\"&gt;Umberlee&lt;/a&gt; can break the geas. When they inform Lothander of this, he tells them to meet him at the &lt;a href=\"Blade%20and%20Stars\"&gt;Blade and Stars Inn&lt;/a&gt; when they have found a way to break the geas. The &lt;a href=\"temple%20of%20Umberlee\"&gt;temple of Umberlee&lt;/a&gt; (Labeled 'Water Queen's House') is located near the waterfront docks in the district of &lt;a href=\"South%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;South Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce inside the temple, speak to one of the priestesses and ask to see the high priestess, &lt;a href=\"Jalantha%20Mistmyr\"&gt;Jalantha Mistmyr&lt;/a&gt;. The party will need to bribe the priestess with 50 &lt;a href=\"Gold%20Piece\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt; to see Jalantha. She will tell them to wait, and after a few seconds the high priestess comes to speak with the party. She promises to help them break the geas if they will acquire the &lt;a href=\"Tome%20of%20Understanding\"&gt;Tome of Understanding&lt;/a&gt; for her. It can be obtained from &lt;a href=\"Chanthalas%20Ulbright\"&gt;Chanthalas Ulbright&lt;/a&gt;, who is in the &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%27s%20Hall\"&gt;Temple of Tymora&lt;/a&gt; (otherwise known as 'The Lady's Hall'), located in the district of &lt;a href=\"West%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;West Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. Alternatively, Jalantha can be killed for the scroll, however this will interfere with other quests involving her (see &lt;a href=\"Tremain%27s%20Son\"&gt;Tremain's Son&lt;/a&gt;). Alternatively, you can pickpocket the Geas Removal Scroll and a Sphene Gem from Jalantha. You should still go and get the Tome of Understanding, but it will save you returning to Jalantha.\nRetrieving the Tome of Understanding.\nOnce inside the Lady's Hall, speak to Chanthalas Ulbright with your character who has the highest charisma. Tell him the party needs the Tome of Understanding. Ulbright will ask why he should give it up. If the party has at least 500 gold you will be able to offer it to him as payment, which he will say is desperation enough and will simply give you the book. Alternatively you can tell him it is a matter of life and death. If the party member speaking to him has a high enough reaction score he will give you the book, otherwise he may refuse. Failing all of these, he may be pickpocketed or killed for the book (with loss of reputation).\nRegardless of method, once the party has the book, return to the Water Queen's House and give the book to Jalantha. She will give the player a &lt;a href=\"Geas%20Removal%20Scroll\"&gt;scroll&lt;/a&gt; in return which will break Lothander's geas.\nReturning to Lothander and finding Marek.\nMeet Lothander at the Blade and Stars. The inn is located in the district of &lt;a href=\"Southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southeast Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; in the northwest corner of the local map. Lothander is on the second floor of the inn standing with a large group of &lt;a href=\"Commoner\"&gt;Commoner&lt;/a&gt;s. Once the player gives him the scroll, he gives the player a\nand tells them where they can find Marek who has the \u201cother half\u201d of the antidote. The potion he gave the player is useless as it is only a common potion of antidote. Marek is the only one with the real antidote, however you get for freeing Lothander of his geas.\nThe player can find Marek in the &lt;a href=\"Blushing%20Mermaid\"&gt;Blushing Mermaid&lt;/a&gt;. He will only appear there after Lothander tells the player he is there. It is impossible to find him without helping Lothander. The Blushing Mermaid is in the district of &lt;a href=\"Northeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Northeast Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; on the western side of the local map. It has a full color picture of a mermaid on the side with a blue background.\nMarek is on the second floor. When the player speaks to him he will attack the party. \nJournal.\nThe first encounter with Marek and Lothander is recorded as an untitled entry in the Journal section of the Journal.\nJournal entries appear in the Quest section under the heading Marek and Lothander beginning with Lothander's request\u2014and offer\u2014 when he approaches the party in the marketplace in Central Baldur's Gate.\nAgree to help Lothander with his geas:\nAfter talking to the seer:\nDiplomatic option #2:"}
{"id": "50531", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50531", "title": "Margie", "text": "Margie is a woman that you can speak with in &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale\"&gt;Imnesvale&lt;/a&gt; village, part of the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; area. She's married to &lt;a href=\"Dale%20the%20Herder\"&gt;Dale the Herder&lt;/a&gt;. If you speak with her, and find out what she has to say, she might interject \"My... my name is Margie. Short for Margaret. My husband is Dale... one of the herders. We fled from the outskirts of the village lands because of the wolves\"."}
{"id": "13615", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13615", "title": "Marilith", "text": "Mariliths are sixed-armed demons, with an upper body of a &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; female and a lower body of a snake. Mariliths carry a sword in each arm and are immune to normal weapons. They are usually capable of casting magic spells and use &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;. \nMariliths appear in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt; and are mentioned in . &lt;a href=\"Azothet\"&gt;Azothet&lt;/a&gt; is a marilith that appears in &lt;a href=\"Dorn%27s%20bloody%20path\"&gt;Dorn's Bloody Path&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod, and the \"Improved Fiends\" component will Improve the Marilith as follows:\nMariliths (cast at 20th level):&lt;br&gt;\nStoneskin, once per three rounds&lt;br&gt;\nProtection from Magic Weapons, once per five rounds&lt;br&gt;\nCloudkill, once per three rounds&lt;br&gt;\nAnimate Dead, once per three rounds&lt;br&gt;\nRemove Magic, Teleport without Error, and True Sight, at will&lt;br&gt;\nBlade Barrier and Telekinesis, at will&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "46600", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46600", "title": "Marketplace (Baldur's Gate)", "text": "The Marketplace is located in the center of &lt;a href=\"Central%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Central Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and serves as an area where citizens of the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;city&lt;/a&gt; can shop and experience various forms of entertainment. It is also an area of the city where &lt;a href=\"Commoner\"&gt;Commoner&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Nobleman\"&gt;Noblemen&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Noblewoman\"&gt;Noblewomen&lt;/a&gt; all mingle together.\nLayout.\nThe area is comprised of market stalls, a couple of rides, and 10 tents. Only the three biggest tents are accessible.\n\"Gambling Tent 1\".\n&lt;br&gt;\nThis is the first of the two biggest tents in the area. The entrance is hidden from view and faces the &lt;a href=\"Drakon%20Tavern\"&gt;Drakon Tavern&lt;/a&gt;. Inside there are multiple gaming tables, regular tables, and what appears to be a small bar. There are four &lt;a href=\"Gamesman\"&gt;gamesmen&lt;/a&gt; and ten male commoners. None of the gamesman or commoners carry any gold. The single lootable table is empty.\n\"Gambling Tent 2\".\n&lt;br&gt;\nThis is the second of the two biggest tents in the area. The entrance faces the center of the marketplace. Inside there are multiple gaming tables, regular tables, and what appears to be a small bar. There are four gamesmen and six commoners. None of the gamesman or commoners carry any gold. The single lootable table is empty.\n\"Diviner's Tent\".\n&lt;br&gt;\nThis is the blue and white striped tent in the top corner of the area. The entrance faces the center of the marketplace. \nInside is the &lt;a href=\"Diviner%20%28NPC%29\"&gt;Diviner&lt;/a&gt; who will answer only one question per day for 50 .\nQuests.\n&lt;a href=\"Marek%20and%20Lothander\"&gt;Marek and Lothander&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nOnce you have come across &lt;a href=\"Marek\"&gt;Marek&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lothander\"&gt;Lothander&lt;/a&gt; in the eastern side of &lt;a href=\"Northeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Northeast Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, the next time you enter the marketplace area, Lothander can be found standing between the smaller tent located above the first gambling tent and the Diviner's tent. He will immediately approach upon sight and explain his dilemma to you. Helping him will truly save your life as this quest has a ten day limit for its completion once Lothander tells you about the evil Marek has poisoned you with."}
{"id": "2426", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2426", "title": "Marl", "text": "Marl is a grumpy drunk found in &lt;a href=\"Feldepost%27s%20Inn\"&gt;Feldepost's Inn&lt;/a&gt;, along with his friend &lt;a href=\"Dunkin\"&gt;Dunkin&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe doesn't like adventurers because he blames them for his son's death. His son, Kennair Nethalin, aspired to be an adventurer but died doing so.\nYou can slay him without losing any &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt;, or calm him down for a significant experience reward, but with no way to kill him without losing the reputation. You can also pickpocket the &lt;a href=\"Andar%20Gem\"&gt;Andar Gem&lt;/a&gt; he carries."}
{"id": "2431", "revid": "163780", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2431", "title": "Marl's Loss", "text": "Known in \"classic\" &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; as Marl the Drunk, this is a chance to win a significant experience reward.\n&lt;a href=\"Marl\"&gt;Marl&lt;/a&gt; is an agressive drunk found in &lt;a href=\"Feldepost%27s%20Inn\"&gt;Feldepost's Inn&lt;/a&gt;. Depending on how you speak to him, he will most probably begin attacking you. If you choose the moral high ground and talk him out of a fight, you are rewarded 900 xp.\nTo calm him down, choose dialog options 1, 1, 3, 3, 1.\nAlternatively, when he attacks you can use a spell or ability such as &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Person\"&gt;Charm Person&lt;/a&gt; to pacify him.\nOn the other hand, he's worth 650 xp to kill, which is certainly easy enough and faster to do, and you get some minor loot to make up for the xp missed. To fight him, just be rude to him.\nIf you kill Marl \"after\" you have calmed him down, you will lose &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue.\nThe sequence of dialog responses needed to calm Marl down and win the 900 xp reward is:\nJournal.\nNote: These entries appear in the Journal section, not the Quests section."}
