{"id": "6736", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6736", "title": "Martial Staff", "text": "Martial Staff is an enchanted quarterstaff +3. It has the same properties as a &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff%20%2B3\"&gt;Quarterstaff +3&lt;/a&gt;, except it is more expensive. It deals 1d6 +3 points of crushing damage and it has -3 THAC0 bonus and a speed factor of 1.\nIt has the looks of &lt;a href=\"Aule%27s%20Staff\"&gt;Aule's Staff&lt;/a&gt;, which appeared in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and , but Aule's Staff does not appear in BG2.\nGameplay.\nThere's no obvious reason for the inflated price, however it does explain why these are preferred over the &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff%20%2B3\"&gt;Quarterstaff +3&lt;/a&gt; for starting equipment in , since it provides the party with more initial coin.\nLocations.\n\"Throne of Bhaal\".\nPart of the &lt;a href=\"Starting%20equipment\"&gt;Starting equipment&lt;/a&gt; for:\nBugs.\nIn the original the description read 6lbs. This has been corrected in the enhanced edition."}
