{"id": "13807", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13807", "title": "Mask", "text": "Mask, also known as the Lord of Shadows, is a &lt;a href=\"neutral%20evil\"&gt;neutral evil&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0intermediate\u00a0&lt;a href=\"deity\"&gt;deity&lt;/a&gt; of rogues, &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thieves&lt;/a&gt; and intrigue.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Time%20of%20Troubles\"&gt;Time of Troubles&lt;/a&gt;, Mask took the form of a powerful magic sword called Godsbane. The sword changed several mortal carriers during the period, eventually falling in the hands of\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Cyric\"&gt;Cyric&lt;/a&gt;, who used it to slay\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Bhaal\"&gt;Bhaal&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0on &lt;a href=\"Boareskyr%20Bridge\"&gt;Boareskyr Bridge&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-Game.\nSiege of Dragonspear.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Cyric\"&gt;Temple of Cyric&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Wyrms\"&gt;Forest of Wyrms&lt;/a&gt; contains a secret chamber that can only be opened through a puzzle made of a series of masks. It is strongly hinted at that Godsbane is hidden in the chamber, but it turns out to be the &lt;a href=\"Fractal%20Blade%20%2B3\"&gt;Fractal Blade +3&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and a &lt;a href=\"Godsbane%20%28book%29\"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; \"about\" Godsbane.\nAt the end of &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Nine%20%E2%80%93%20Boareskyr%20Bridge\"&gt;Chapter Nine&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; has a vision of Cyric\u00a0murdering Bhaal with Godsbane, when they cross &lt;a href=\"Boareskyr%20Bridge\"&gt;Boareskyr Bridge&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "51983", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51983", "title": "Mask guardian", "text": "The Mask guardian is a &lt;a href=\"Efreeti\"&gt;Efreeti&lt;/a&gt; that is bound to this plane in order to guard this maze and tomb area. It has several fire-based abilities, and will use its melee weapon, making it a potentially dangerous opponent if unprotected from fire, or a party member that is likely to get struck by melee attacks.\nGameplay.\nThere are six of these guardians placed in six different chambers, all behind a closed door. In order to obtain the six Pieces of Burial Mask needed to form the final &lt;a href=\"Mask%20of%20King%20Strohm%20III\"&gt;Mask of King Strohm III&lt;/a&gt;, each must be destroyed.\nEach guardian stands at the ready and will be neutral at first. Each one recites a line or two of unique cryptic prose regarding their duty towards guarding the King's tomb. Immediately afterwards will turn hostile.\nEach Efreeti will most likely force cast a &lt;a href=\"Fireshield%20%28Red%29\"&gt;Fireshield (Red)&lt;/a&gt; on self, then a force cast a &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt; spell at the closest opponent, and then force cast &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; on self.\nThe next two actions will probably be a force cast &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Arrow\"&gt;Flame Arrow&lt;/a&gt; and then a &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Strike\"&gt;Flame Strike&lt;/a&gt;. Fifteen game seconds will pass, and if the creature is able to function, will begin the cycle again. They never run out of spells, and can't be interrupted, silenced or affected by miscast magic effects (sorry Wizard Slayers). Note that their HD level is susceptible to &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt;.\nDuring that brief waiting period it may engage in melee combat if there is a detected enemy.\nOnce its physical form is defeated, the being will disappear into a swirling vortex portal, leaving behind only a Piece of Burial Mask.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod rewrites the AI script for the creature and includes a revised set of spells it can cast and a better ability to recognize opponent protections and certain items worn by its enemies.\nAdditionally, the creatures are raised to 12 HD Efreeti, with caster level 12/12 mage-cleric ability. The Efreeti will use &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; for protection several times, and &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Arrow\"&gt;Flame Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Strike\"&gt;Flame Strike&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Storm\"&gt;Fire Storm&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt; to attack with. Some of these can be used multiple times and others only once.\nThe guardian can instantly apply a &lt;a href=\"Fireshield%20%28Red%29\"&gt;Fireshield (Red)&lt;/a&gt; effect at will, even if removed it can reapply it.\nWhen damaged to a preset threshold the Efreeti will morph into a gaseous cloud form and rapidly regenerate. It is nearly invulnerable while gaseous. Once healed sufficiently, it reforms into an Efreeti and continues the fight. It can do this three times. Note that this creature will often turn invisible and move away from the chamber it is found in, and travel to backline party members. Closing the door after entering can prevent it from escaping, but all in the room will be exposed to AoE fire attacks."}
{"id": "6828", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6828", "title": "Mask of King Strohm III", "text": "The Mask of King Strohm III is a quest item needed in the side quest &lt;a href=\"Samia%27s%20Proposal\"&gt;Samia's Proposal&lt;/a&gt;, who wants the party to find some ancient manuscripts.\nAquisition.\nThis mask is not an individual item that is found. In fact, it is formed when six other pieces are collected, and those pieces will reconstitute into the Mask of King Strohm III. In order to attempt to collect these pieces, the player must either take &lt;a href=\"Samia%27s%20Key\"&gt;Samia's Key&lt;/a&gt; by force or agree to accept &lt;a href=\"Samia%27s%20Proposal\"&gt;Samia's Proposal&lt;/a&gt;. The second choice provides better role play, immersion, and experience point reward.\nGameplay.\nThe mask is assembled by collecting the six Piece of Burial Mask in &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Maze\"&gt;Firkraag's Maze&lt;/a&gt;. Each piece comes from defeating a &lt;a href=\"Mask%20guardian\"&gt;Mask guardian&lt;/a&gt;. After collecting the sixth piece, the completed mask will appear in the player's inventory.\nA Piece of Burial Mask is described as:\n&lt;br&gt;\nThis mask is needed to solve two issues: First it allows the party to open the door to King Strohm's tomb chamber. The Mask acts as a key. Second, it reveals the hidden Final mask guardian.\nThis mask can be worn by anyone. In the original game, only the PC would have to wear this Mask in order to reveal the Final mask guardian.\nBy equipping the mask on a helmet slot, the &lt;a href=\"Final%20mask%20guardian\"&gt;Final mask guardian&lt;/a&gt; in the northern room will stop force casting &lt;a href=\"Sunfire\"&gt;Sunfire&lt;/a&gt; and be revealed.\nAs of BG2EE 2.5, this mask does not provide critical hit protection.\nGallery.\nEach Piece of Burial Mask is assigned individual .ITM names, KEY14.itm, 15, 16, 17, 18 and 19."}
{"id": "56594", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56594", "title": "Mass Charm Person (SPIN553)", "text": "This Mass Charm Person (SPIN553) spell potentially affects any creatures (humanoid, animal, undead etc.) in the spell's area of effect that are not in the caster's party.\nThe spell's description in the game files is only \"Charm Person\", however, within creature spell use scripts the spell is also identified as \"Nalmissra Charm\".\nFrom an accuracy standpoint, this spell is actually better described as a Mass Dire Charm spell, as victims are affected by the Charm type \"Dire Charm\", and not the ordinary \"Charmed\" type that the &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Person\"&gt;Charm Person&lt;/a&gt; spell uses.\nThis spell is usable only by select non-player characters in the game.\nGameplay.\nThis spell is not assigned to any spell school, and has no secondary type classification, and therefore can't be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt;.\nLikewise, the spell doesn't have an assigned &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt;, and thus will bypass spell level immunity protections like &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe spell is subject to &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, and charmed victims can remove the charm with an appropriate &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nAny creature not in the caster's party in the area of effect of the spell will be exposed to several effects.\nThe first is a &lt;a href=\"Charmed\"&gt;Charmed&lt;/a&gt; effect, that can last 1 turn in duration - a successful &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spell, with a 2-point penalty will negate it.\nIf the victim is affected by the Dire Charm, then a text string will display on the combat log reading \"Charmed\", and that specific creature is now under control of the caster and will most likely become a \"Red circled\" sprite and an enemy of the player's party.\nThe second effect penalizes the victim's saving throw modifier vs. spells with a 2-point penalty lasting 10 seconds - a combat log text displays \"Saving Throws Lowered\".\nThe third effect is a -5% &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; penalty modifier lasting 10 seconds - a combat log text displays \"Magic Resistance Lowered\".\nNote that &lt;a href=\"Elf\"&gt;Elf&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Half-elf\"&gt;Half-elf&lt;/a&gt; creatures do get their racial charm resistance chance to possibly thwart this spell."}
{"id": "5467", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5467", "title": "Mass Cure", "text": "Mass Cure allows the priest to heal wounds and remove &lt;a href=\"Intoxicated\"&gt;Intoxication&lt;/a&gt; from multiple party members within the area of effect.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this Divine spell, revising its effects, scaling, and description. See below:\nMass Cure\nLevel: 5\nSchool: Necromancy\nSphere: Healing\nRange: Personal\nDuration: Permanent\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: Sight\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen casting this spell, the priest must picture the faces of his fellow party members clearly and focus on the unity of the group. Upon completion, all party members within sight of the caster are healed by 2d8 + 2/level hit points (up to a maximum of 2d8+20)."}
{"id": "6895", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6895", "title": "Mass Healing", "text": "Mass Healing is a Bhaalspawn ability that can be acquired in if one has either the &lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Unfinished Business (Baldur's Gate II)&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Ascension\"&gt;Ascension&lt;/a&gt; mods installed. It is essentially an improved version of the level 5 Cleric spell &lt;a href=\"Mass%20Cure\"&gt;Mass Cure&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen using this ability, the Bhaalspawn must picture the faces of his fellow party members clearly and focus on the unity of the group. \u00a0Upon completion, all party members within 30 foot radius of the caster are healed 2d8 + 2/level hit points. \u00a0Other conditions suffered by the party are cured, as well: fatigue, poison, disease, blindness and deafness."}
{"id": "5829", "revid": "285065", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5829", "title": "Mass Invisibility", "text": "Mass Invisibility is a powerful spell that applies the effects of the spell &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Invisibility\"&gt;Improved Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; to multiple friendly creatures.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a point on the explored area map and aims the spell at that point - use the target selection cursor to designate the target point.\nWhen casting is finished a projectile travels to the selected target point and immediately bestows the spell effects onto all party creatures in the 30-feet radius area of effect.\nAll party creatures are affected with an &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Invisibility\"&gt;Improved Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; spell effect as long as the spell is active.\nWhen the spell is cast, the combat log displays a text reading \"Invisible\".\nEach spell recipient initially renders the sprite with a brief color glow and a lighting effect - additionally a sound effect is audibled when the spell cast is complete, and another when the spell expires. \nThis spell effectively bestows 2 \"states\" on the spell recipient; invisible and \"undetected\" and invisible but \"detected\".\nThe spell's effects can be removed with any &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nLikewise, this spell can be removed using various Divination attacks, including a thief's Detect Illusion ability, and various spells that remove invisibility, such as &lt;a href=\"Invisibility%20Purge\"&gt;Invisibility Purge&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Oracle\"&gt;Oracle&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"True%20Sight\"&gt;True Sight&lt;/a&gt;.\nCreatures with the &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt; innate ability will be able to target a creature under the effects of Mass and improved invisibility, as if they were not invisible at all.\nOne caveat is that the divination attack Wizard spell &lt;a href=\"Detect%20Illusion\"&gt;Detect Illusion&lt;/a&gt; will not affect this spell, as \"Mass Invisibility\" is a 7 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; spell, and exceeds that particular divination attack's capability.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell's description. See below:\nMass Invisibility\nLevel: 7\nSchool: Illusion\nRange: Long\nDuration: 1 round/level\nCasting Time: 7\nArea of Effect: 30\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: None\nUpon casting this spell, the wizard causes all friendly creatures within the area of effect to be affected by the spell Improved Invisibility. Creatures leaving the area are still subject to the spell\u2019s effect; those entering the area after the casting is completed are not."}
{"id": "5830", "revid": "3983911", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5830", "title": "Mass Invisibilty", "text": ""}
{"id": "4775", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4775", "title": "Mass Raise Dead", "text": "This spell brings back up to 5 party members to life and heals 3D10 +1 hit points per level of caster.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this Divine spell, revising its effects, casting time and description. See below:\nMass Raise Dead\nLevel: Quest\nSchool: Necromancy\nSphere: Necromantic\nRange: Personal\nDuration: Permanent\nCasting Time: 4\nArea of Effect: Up to 5 party members\nSaving Throw: None\nA more powerful version of Raise Dead, this spell brings up to 5 party members back to life and heals 4d10+20 points of damage. Those affected can regain the rest of their hit points by natural healing or curative magic."}
{"id": "48651", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48651", "title": "Mastav", "text": "Mastav is a gypsy camped outside of the walls of &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign.\nGameplay.\nMastav is of the Rom gypsies, and his wife &lt;a href=\"Kveroslava\"&gt;Kveroslava&lt;/a&gt; tells fortunes.\n\"Greetings to you, good &lt;MAN/WOMAN&gt;. You are welcome amongst our family of Rom, and I offer you whatever hospitality I may. My name is Mastav... perhaps you wish to have your fortune told by my wife, yes?\"\nIf is son &lt;a href=\"Jidek\"&gt;Jidek&lt;/a&gt; says how he \"can't wait to get out of here...the Rom life is boring\" Mastav will interject, and the two have a back-n-forth dialog."}
