{"id": "53860", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53860", "title": "Matron's Guard", "text": "Matron's Guard is a type of drow warrior found in the city of &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt; and inside the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Lolth\"&gt;Temple of Lolth&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign. \nGameplay.\nThese male warriors are clad in adamantine full plate and wield the drow halberd. They are positioned in a few areas of the temple, mostly to the east and near the stairs.\nThey can be spoken to, don't have much to say other than perfunctory official comments. They have more to say if the matron mother is dead.\nThese guards will be neutral, but if the city alarm script is initiated, or if any in the temple are attacked, they will spring into action. They are trained to attack their nearest detected enemy and fight to the death in melee combat.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some minor changes these warriors. A fighter AI script is assigned for better tactical behavior. A &lt;a href=\"Berserker\"&gt;Berserker&lt;/a&gt; kit is added.\nSCS raises their ability scores to reflect their higher status. 18/76 for strength, and 19 dexterity.\nThree pips in Halberd weapon proficiency are assigned, and 2 pips in two-handed weapon fighting style. Also, a &lt;a href=\"HELMNOAN.ITM\"&gt;HELMNOAN.ITM&lt;/a&gt; is placed in their helmet slot, as well as some random SCS treasure, which are potions usable for quaffing to heal and boost abilities. They are scripted to do this.\nAt the beginning of the fight, they will use their &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt; class ability."}
{"id": "44988", "revid": "5305940", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44988", "title": "Matron Mother Ardulace", "text": ""}
{"id": "43602", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43602", "title": "Matron Mother Ardulace Despana", "text": "Matron Mother Ardulace Despana is a high-ranking Priestess of Lolth residing within &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Lolth\"&gt;Temple of Lolth&lt;/a&gt;. She is the Matron Mother of the House Despana.\nGameplay.\nFirst off, if the party enters the Temple of Lolth, and she is present there - and then dares to speak with the Matron Mother, the priestess will give a curt and harsh reply to NOT speak with her uninvited. This is a warning. If spoken to two more times, she will become hostile. So, don't speak with her unless you must through other dialogue introductions, such as if you are double-crossing Phaere, which is an option at a certain stage of the story line. The player will know they are headed in the wrong direction if she says: \"I have no interest in your questions, foolish &lt;MALEFEMALE&gt;. Begone! And do not interrupt me again!\"\nIn general, the Matron Mother gives the player character some quest actions and tasks relevant to the main plot of getting the protagonist and party back to the surface from the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;, part of the &lt;a href=\"The%20Drow%20Summoning%20Ritual\"&gt;The Drow Summoning Ritual&lt;/a&gt; quest line:\nAfter these quests have been completed, &lt;a href=\"Phaere\"&gt;Phaere&lt;/a&gt; will attempt to entice &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; into betraying the Matron Mother. If this option is selected, and &lt;a href=\"Solaufein\"&gt;Solaufein&lt;/a&gt; is still alive, he will then offer the player the option to triple-cross both of the drow women.\nThere is more intrigue potentially with these lines of gameplay. The party can even report Phaere's plot to betray the Matron Mother directly to her.\nNote that it is unlikely that the party will actually ever be in direct combat with the Matron Mother in this saga, as that would cause hostility of the entire city of Ust Natha, and prematurely end all open pending quest actions.\nHowever, assuming the party does face the Matron mother in battle (it is possible), then she will force-cast a group of protective buffs at the outset to include &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Mirror\"&gt;Physical Mirror&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20of%20the%20Archons\"&gt;Shield of the Archons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Regeneration%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Regeneration (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, and the use her &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Ring of Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt; to apply &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Minor Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe next spell attempted will be &lt;a href=\"Earthquake\"&gt;Earthquake&lt;/a&gt;. If her hit points fall to 40% or less, she'll regroup with a instant cast spell trio of &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Fire%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Protection From Fire (priest)&lt;/a&gt;. She can do this action another time if her HP again falls to 40%.\nAll of the other spells listed in the InfoBox are scripted for use, and she will attempt any of those spells when on the offensive.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; revises this cleric's memorized spells, assigns a new \"Smarter Priest\" default AI script, and sets up the Matron Mother with a large group of instantly applied protective buffs and two summoned creatures when hostilities break out, including:\n&lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Blades\"&gt;Globe of Blades&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spiritual%20Hammer\"&gt;Spiritual Hammer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Fire%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Protection From Fire (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Mirror\"&gt;Physical Mirror&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Blades%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Energy Blades (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20of%20the%20Archons\"&gt;Shield of the Archons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Aerial%20Servant\"&gt;Aerial Servant&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Animate%20Dead\"&gt;Animate Dead&lt;/a&gt;. Offensive spells will be selected based on the AI's vulnerability assessment of targets and other threats. She'll heal herself several times if able."}
{"id": "6662", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6662", "title": "Mauler's Arm", "text": "Mauler's Arm is an enchanted mace +2. This weapon has almost the same proterties as a &lt;a href=\"Mace%20%2B2\"&gt;Mace +2&lt;/a&gt;, as they both inflict the same amount damage, have the same &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;, speed factor and weight, but this weapon raises &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; to 18 and there is no Strength requirement. If the character's strength is above 18, it does not get lowered."}
