{"id": "24704", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24704", "title": "Meeting with Valen's mistress", "text": "Meeting with Valen's Mistress is a main quest which can be started in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt; once the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; accumulates .\nWalkthrough.\nTo start the quest, the party must have met with &lt;a href=\"Gaelan%20Bayle\"&gt;Gaelan Bayle&lt;/a&gt; and started &lt;a href=\"Collect%20the%20fee%20for%20Gaelan%20Bayle\"&gt;the quest to collect 20,000&lt;/a&gt; for him in order to get to &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;. Then, once the party has at least , a &lt;a href=\"vampire\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Valen\"&gt;Valen&lt;/a&gt; will appear and invite &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to meet her mistress at the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;graveyard&lt;/a&gt; at dusk.\n&lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; will greet the party at the entrance of the area and offer to take them to &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt; for only (i.e. a discount to Gaelan's first offer - however it's possible that the party has received Gaelan Bayle's second offer of before meeting Bodhi). Accepting her offer outright and paying the fee will start &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;Chapter 3&lt;/a&gt; and award each party member with 36,750 XP.\nHowever, if the party has less than on them when the meeting with Bodhi commences, she will berate the party for their spending habits and ask them to come back when they've gathered the money.\nQuest Restrictions.\nBodhi will refuse to help a single class &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt;, or a &lt;a href=\"Human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; dual-classed to thief, whose original class hasn't been reactivated yet, claiming that those characters are too closely aligned to the Shadow Thieves.\nConsequences.\nChoosing to side with Bodhi will make the Shadow Thieves hostile towards the players. This will eliminate all chances to work for &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt;.\nAdditionally, good-aligned &lt;a href=\"companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; will complain of Gorion's Ward's choice and &lt;a href=\"Keldorn%20Firecam\"&gt;Keldorn Firecam&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mazzy%20Fentan\"&gt;Mazzy Fentan&lt;/a&gt; will leave the party for good.\nRefusing Bodhi's offer will break her quest, after which Gorion's Ward's only option to advance the main quest will be to work for the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt;. However simply meeting with Bodhi will cause &lt;a href=\"Brus\"&gt;Brus&lt;/a&gt; to appear again and invite the party to &lt;a href=\"Gaelan%20Bayle%27s%20Home\"&gt;Gaelan Bayle's Home&lt;/a&gt; where Gaelan will offer to lower his fee to . In some cases, the meeting with Valen already causes Brus to appear, without meeting Bodhi."}
{"id": "45448", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45448", "title": "Meiala", "text": ""}
{"id": "28870", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28870", "title": "Meiala the Sirine", "text": "Meiala the Sirine is a &lt;a href=\"warrior\"&gt;warrior&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"enchanter\"&gt;enchanter&lt;/a&gt; who, in her current state, is a stone statue in the bestiary room located on &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Labyrinth%20Level%20Three%29\"&gt;labyrinth level 3&lt;/a&gt; below &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;. She can be released from her predicament without the need for a &lt;a href=\"Stone%20to%20Flesh%20Scroll\"&gt;Stone to Flesh Scroll&lt;/a&gt; and will serve &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; for a while before becoming mutinous.\nBiography.\nAn ancient hero, Meiala the Sirine undertook the unwise and foolish venture of looking for &lt;a href=\"Durlag%20Trollkiller\"&gt;Durlag Trollkiller&lt;/a&gt;'s treasures \u2013 only to end up standing vigil over the bestiary down in the dwarf's dungeons, forever frozen in stone.\nInvolvement.\nWhen entering the bestiary by way of the fireball room, the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; will be greeted by a &lt;a href=\"skeleton\"&gt;skeleton&lt;/a&gt; who introduces five \"foolish men and women \u2013 ancient hero[s]\" who \"came to find Durlag's treasure\" and now are \"forever &lt;a href=\"Petrified\"&gt;frozen in stone&lt;/a&gt;\" and then offers a preview of the creatures to be encountered within the room.\u2009\nThese statues can be released by clicking on each of them and they will help the party for a limited time to defeat those &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Wyvern\"&gt;creatures&lt;/a&gt; the skeleton spoke of, but then turn against the person who dared to &lt;a href=\"Charmed\"&gt;command&lt;/a&gt; them.\u2009\nMeiala the Sirine is one of these statues. Once turned back to flesh, she greets the party and offers her exceptional abilities as a warrior and enchanter in the forthcoming battles.\nHowever, as the skeleton mentioned, her oath doesn't last long \u2013 only fifteen rounds, after which she turns hostile towards the party.\nCombat.\nMeiala speaks the truth when saying, she had no peer among her people \u2013 her stats can only be compared with those of the &lt;a href=\"sirine%20queen\"&gt;sirine queen&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;Isle of Balduran&lt;/a&gt;:\nIt should also be mentioned that her is not \"&lt;a href=\"Monsters\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;\", but \"&lt;a href=\"Humanoids\"&gt;humanoid&lt;/a&gt;\" instead. So, any &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;equipment&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"spell\"&gt;spell&lt;/a&gt; with specific abilities related to these types will not behave the same as in other fights against sirines.\nNotes.\nRather than Improved Invisibility, which is the first spell usually cast by members of her kin, Meiala has a &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; memorized. Unfortunately she's unable to use it.\n&lt;a href=\"Item\"&gt;Item&lt;/a&gt;s cannot be &lt;a href=\"pickpocket\"&gt;pickpocket&lt;/a&gt;ed from the statue: first Meiala has to be resurrected. Though she turns hostile after fifteen rounds anyway, pickpocketing is still useful to obtain a quiver of twenty arrows of biting which otherwise might be fired off by her.\nAs with the other resurrected statue creatures, the party can choose to attack her before she turns hostile. She will not fight back, and will be easily killed."}
{"id": "7705", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7705", "title": "Meilum", "text": "Meilum is a fighter in the &lt;a href=\"Firewine%20Bridge\"&gt;Firewine Bridge&lt;/a&gt; area (&lt;a href=\"Coordinates\"&gt;4850.700&lt;/a&gt;) that claims to be famous for being \"the Sword Coast's most skilled swordsman.\" Insult him if you wish to contest his claim and win &lt;a href=\"Gauntlets%20of%20Weapon%20Expertise\"&gt;Gauntlets of Weapon Expertise&lt;/a&gt;, and other loot. He deals 1d8+12 &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; per hit."}
