{"id": "8173", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8173", "title": "Mekrath", "text": "Mekrath is a powerful &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;wizard&lt;/a&gt; who &lt;a href=\"Mekrath%27s%20Laboratory\"&gt;lives below&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Temple\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nSpeak with the neutral Mekrath in his workshop to initiate certain quest actions. He won't necessarily become hostile if engaged in civil discourse. He is willing to make a deal with the party regarding Haer'Dalis.\nIf you accept his quest deal, or if the party agrees to leave Mekrath alone - be aware that this mage's script has a timer, and if the party is within his visual range for too long, he gets impatient and becomes hostile. Leave when you are told to and get moving when you have his quest - don't just stand around - get cracking.\nBe aware that He starts out with Stoneskin already active. So, a backstabbing attack will likely be absorbed.\nShould the party decide to commence hostilities, Mekrath will be able to initiate a chain of force cast buffs initially.\nIf Mekrath's stoneskins drop to zero, he'll attempt to reapply another &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Mantle\"&gt;Mantle&lt;/a&gt;.\nMekrath will try and retaliate with a &lt;a href=\"Ruby%20Ray%20of%20Reversal\"&gt;Ruby Ray of Reversal&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Maze\"&gt;Maze&lt;/a&gt; if the target has a mage class and if certain HP conditions are met.\nAll of the spells listed in the InfoBox are scripted for use. Some of these aren't interruptible and are force cast.\nIf wounded to a certain threshold, he'll quaff his potion of healing.\nSide quests.\n&lt;a href=\"Free%20Haer%27Dalis%20from%20Imprisonment%20by%20Mekrath\"&gt;Free Haer'Dalis from Imprisonment by Mekrath&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Raelis%20Shai\"&gt;Raelis Shai&lt;/a&gt;, the leader of the performers known as the Sigil Troupe, will ask &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and their party to rescue a member of their cast, Haer'Dalis, from Mekrath's clutches.\nIf you do not anger him, you can say that you are looking for adventure and he will give you \"Mekrath's mirror\" quest.\nAn imp has stolen a magical mirror from Mekrath, and now resides in the southeast section of the &lt;a href=\"Sewers%20%28Temple%20District%29\"&gt;sewers&lt;/a&gt;, accompanied by a lesser earth elemental, likely summoned by the mirror.\nOnce dispatched, take the now broken mirror back to Mekrath and you will be rewarded 18,750 &lt;a href=\"XP\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt; and his \"slave\" Haer'Dalis. If you are quick enough you can cast Breach and then kill Mekrath before he teleports away, yielding 14,000 XP when defeated.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; assigns a \"Smarter Mages\" AI script for better spell casting usage and targeted behavior. As of SCS version 35, Mekrath's Level is raised to a more appropriate experience level (level 12 is too low). \nMekrath has scripted abilities to instantly launch his prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trigger\"&gt;Spell Trigger&lt;/a&gt;.\nA new repertoire of memorized spells is provided commensurate with his XP level.\nExpect more challenge and staying power if directly fighting the mage with this mod installed. "}
{"id": "42075", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42075", "title": "Mekrath's Laboratory", "text": "This area is a secret series of interconnected chambers attached to the &lt;a href=\"Sewers%20%28Temple%20District%29\"&gt;Sewers (Temple District)&lt;/a&gt;. The complex is used by the mage &lt;a href=\"Mekrath\"&gt;Mekrath&lt;/a&gt; - a wizard dedicated to his craft, who seems to be studying the elemental planes. Surrounded by mephits from various elemental origins to aid in his quest for knowledge. The area has a library, bed chambers, a strange chapel, storage rooms with provisions and materials, and some laboratory facilities. \nThe collective area contains books, scrolls, coin and various other treasure - and as long as you don't hinder Merkrath's progress he will\u00a0not punish you for taking some of it. Anything of value to him he has warded magically anyway. That does not mean that other creatures in the area will not be hostile and attack the party, because they will.\nThis area is best explored when the party has accepted the &lt;a href=\"Free%20Haer%27Dalis%20from%20Imprisonment%20by%20Mekrath\"&gt;Free Haer'Dalis from Imprisonment by Mekrath&lt;/a&gt; quest. Doing the quest and visiting Mekrath's Laboratory with the quest properly initiated will make better sense and have improved story/roleplaying flow and journal entries.\nIf you are looking for more information of what to do and plot details, visit the Haer'Dalis quest page linked above.\nLevel dependent spawn point.\nA trigger ranging from top left to bottom right spawns the following creatures, depending on experience:\nGallery.\n\"Portraits from &lt;a href=\"Portraits%20Portraits%20Everywhere\"&gt;Portraits Portraits Everywhere&lt;/a&gt;\"\nMod content.\nInstalling &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises the SPWNMON.bcs file that generates creatures based on the game difficulty setting, rather than just the party leaders experience level. Basically, it looks at both XP and game difficulty to determine what spawned creatures will be placed by the proximity trigger. Suffice to say, it is much more likely that the maximum difficulty level spawns in the unmodified game will be present for a visiting party even if party XP is only moderate. So, expect the highest spawn challenge with SCS installed.\nSCS revises all the creatures in the game to some extent, especially with smarter scripts. The Yuan-ti mages are a real eye opener for those not accustomed to facing SCS mages. Be advised, they are legit Level 14 spell casters, and thus are quite the challenge. Your party will be facing three of these most likely all at once. These creatures will do a much better job seeking out the party and pursing it. For example - Just launching a cloudkill into their spawn chamber will probably not be the final action needed to win the encounter, as they are scripted to chase down the party. Think through your tactics carefully."}
{"id": "30124", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30124", "title": "Mekrath's Mirror", "text": "Mekrath's Mirror is an item belonging to &lt;a href=\"Mekrath\"&gt;Mekrath&lt;/a&gt;, an evil mage found in his &lt;a href=\"Mekrath%27s%20Laboratory\"&gt;secret laboratory&lt;/a&gt; beneath the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt;. Upon first meeting, if the party doesn't provoke him and mentions searching for adventure, he will request the party retrieve his mirror from a renegade &lt;a href=\"imp\"&gt;imp&lt;/a&gt; in the southeastern portion of the &lt;a href=\"Sewers%20%28Temple%20District%29\"&gt;sewers&lt;/a&gt;. The imp is accompanied by a &lt;a href=\"Lesser%20Earth%20Elemental\"&gt;lesser earth elemental&lt;/a&gt;, and will drop the mirror upon death."}
