{"id": "37040", "revid": "273139", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37040", "title": "Memories of Battles Past", "text": "Memories of Battles Past is a sidequest that can be acquired in Chapter 10 of \"\".\nObtaining.\nSpeak to &lt;a href=\"Simonetta%20Twoedged\"&gt;Simonetta Twoedged&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Coalition%20Camp\"&gt;Coalition Camp&lt;/a&gt; to be given this quest, which requires you to speak to multiple individuals around the camp to learn more about why the Coalition exists.\nCompletion.\nThe player must speak to the following NPCs around the Coalition Camp, and then report back to Simonetta:\nReward.\nOnce all three individuals have been spoken to, the player can return to Simonetta again. Upon hearing their analysis, the party gains 6000 EXP and the &lt;a href=\"Medal%20of%20Valor\"&gt;Medal of Valor&lt;/a&gt;.\nAdditionally, completing this quest allows the player to coax Simonetta into revealing a clue pointing to &lt;a href=\"Malden%20Col\"&gt;Malden Col&lt;/a&gt; as the guilty party for the quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Traitor\"&gt;The Traitor&lt;/a&gt;.\nNote.\nA counterpart quest to this exists in the form of the quest &lt;a href=\"Understanding%20the%20Crusade\"&gt;Understanding the Crusade&lt;/a&gt;, which can be acquired at &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Exterior\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Exterior&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Deneld\"&gt;Deneld&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "7376", "revid": "283615", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7376", "title": "Mencar Pebblecrusher", "text": "Mencar Pebblecrusher is the leader of an adventuring party that is comprised of a somewhat diverse group of individuals, including an &lt;a href=\"Pooky\"&gt;Imp&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Smaeluv%20Orcslicer\"&gt;Half-orc&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nMencar and his band are found on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"Den%20of%20the%20Seven%20Vales\"&gt;Den of the Seven Vales&lt;/a&gt;. He will try to provoke &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party by disparaging by their race, which ever member of the party comes into his sight first. Mencar is joined by the others in his band of adventurers including &lt;a href=\"Brennan%20Risling%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;Brennan Risling&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Smaeluv%20Orcslicer\"&gt;Smaeluv Orcslicer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sorcerous%20Amon\"&gt;Sorcerous Amon&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pooky\"&gt;Pooky&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"Hah! If it daren't be a puny &lt;RACE&gt;, dressed up as a mighty adventurer, I'd say! Har har! Did yer mama let ye out from under her skirt, little one? Best ye be runnin' back, now!\"\nAny aggressive response will cause him and his band to attack.\n\"Ye'll take whate'er I have to give ye! Come, my friends... let's teach the whelp what it be to cross Mencar and his band, eh! Have at ye!!\"\nIf &lt;a href=\"Korgan%20Bloodaxe\"&gt;Korgan Bloodaxe&lt;/a&gt; is in the party, Mencar will call him out, claiming that Korgan pulled some type of double-cross and he owes Mencar some gold. This dialogue automatically ends with fighting.\nMencar is a close quarters melee fighter that packs a wallop - especially for a party not far removed from the entry into Shadows of Amn. He may be more powerful than any warrior in the player's party - so beware.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some minor changes to Mencar. He is assigned a default SCS AI script for smarter tactical decision making, including threat recognition and opponent vulnerability assessment. Mencar now has 5 pips in war hammer weapon proficiency. He also has 2 pips in the single weapon fighting style. This will boost mencar's THAC0, melee damage and get his &lt;a href=\"Attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;Attacks per round&lt;/a&gt; to 4.5. The weapon fighting style gives a +2 &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; bonus and will now &lt;a href=\"Critical%20hit\"&gt;Critical hit&lt;/a&gt; more often. A random SCS treasure is added to his inventory. "}
