{"id": "50205", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50205", "title": "Mercenary (Archer)", "text": "Mercenary (Archer) are hired by &lt;a href=\"Balthazar\"&gt;Balthazar&lt;/a&gt; as part of the Army he is building in his conflict with the other Bhaalspawn. The mercenary archers are present in one area northwest of the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Waukeen%20%28Amkethran%29\"&gt;Temple of Waukeen (Amkethran)&lt;/a&gt;. They are assembled and being put through archery drills by &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Erelon\"&gt;Captain Erelon&lt;/a&gt;. There are at least five of these archers. \nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some very minor changes to the mercenary archers in this area. First, they get a new SCS Fighter script. SCS corrects the weapon proficiency to match what a Berserker kit is allowed, and thus the Longbow Proficiency goes to 1 pip, and the Short Sword to 3."}
{"id": "50204", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50204", "title": "Mercenary (Balthazar)", "text": "Mercenary (Balthazar) are hired by &lt;a href=\"Balthazar\"&gt;Balthazar&lt;/a&gt; as part of the Army he is building in his conflict with the other Bhaalspawn. The mercenaries are present in the streets and areas of &lt;a href=\"Amkethran\"&gt;Amkethran&lt;/a&gt;, normally in small groups. They are not overtly hostile to the party when you first visit the village. You'll find that they are a confident and somewhat arrogant bunch and treat the local inhabitants with little respect or compassion. In general, if a mercenary initiates hostility, you are free to defend yourself and kill them without repercussions. If however, the party starts the fight, then there is a risk of making all the mercenaries in the village turn hostile towards you, so beware. The mercenaries are similarly dressed and armed, as if they are in a uniform army. At the moment, the mercenaries are loyal to Balthazar's cause, as he is paying for their service. At a point later in the questline, if you are spotted by the mercenaries in the village, they will be hostile and attack on sight. \nFor some reason, the mercenaries are provided with Grandmastery with axes and 2 pips in Two-weapon style yet wield longswords and shields (oversight?). \nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some minor changes to the mercenaries in this area. First, there may be a few more of them, and they get a new SCS Fighter script. There is a little bit of variety between some, and they may wield an enchanted short sword. instead of a long sword. SCS gives them 3 or 5 pips in the appropriate weapon proficiency as well. If the unmodded game assigned a Berserker kit, it will sometimes be removed, but it depends on the creature. Experience awards for the mercenaries will depend on their level which is between 12-14 Fighter Class. The most recent version of SCS did away with the blanket 63% magic resistance given to these mercs in a previous version."}
{"id": "48414", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48414", "title": "Mercenary (Flaming Fist HQ)", "text": "Five Mercenaries are summoned by &lt;a href=\"Benjy\"&gt;Benjy&lt;/a&gt; when &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party attempt to re-enter the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Headquarters\"&gt;Flaming Fist Headquarters&lt;/a&gt; during the events of &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Seven\"&gt;Chapter Seven&lt;/a&gt;.\nKilling them results in no loss of &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "48939", "revid": "50459896", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48939", "title": "Mercenary (Galvarey Estate)", "text": "Mercenaries at Galvarey Estate have presumably been hired by a &lt;a href=\"Harpers\"&gt;Harper&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Dermin%20Courtierdale\"&gt;Dermin Courtierdale&lt;/a&gt; and await &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Galvarey%20Estate\"&gt;Galvarey Estate&lt;/a&gt; (aka Harper Hold) in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Docks District&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;, during the \"\" campaign. These hired killers will only be encountered during Jaheira's &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;Companion&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Quests\"&gt;Quest&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Summoned%20to%20the%20Harper%20Hold\"&gt;Summoned to the Harper Hold&lt;/a&gt;, and are immediately hostile to &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party upon entering the estate.\nDermin's Mercenaries.\nOn Dermin's instructions, Jaheira returned to Galvarey Estate to await the judgement of the Harpers regarding the actions that Gorion's Ward took against &lt;a href=\"Galvarey\"&gt;Galvarey&lt;/a&gt; and other, fellow Harpers. However, when the party returns there to find out what happened to her, they are intercepted, and must fight to free Jaheira from the estate.\nThere are two groups of mercenaries:\nAll five types of mercenary share one thing in common; they are all of 12th Level. The entire group is worth .\nNone of Dermin's Mercenaries have been given names by the game developers, so they will be referred to by the Number from their Creature Codes, a summary of which, is outlined below:\nMercenary 1.\nAltogether there are four Mercenaries of Type 1. These fight without ranged weapons, closing to melee with &lt;a href=\"Two-handed%20Sword\"&gt;Two-Handed Swords&lt;/a&gt;. They wear &lt;a href=\"Splint%20Mail\"&gt;Splint Mail&lt;/a&gt; and are protected against Critical Hits by &lt;a href=\"Basic%20Helmets%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Open-Faced Helmets&lt;/a&gt;. Each has one &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Extra%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Extra Healing&lt;/a&gt;, and will quaff it if needed. Each is worth and carry &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23Well-off%20treasure\"&gt;Well-Off Random Treasure&lt;/a&gt;.\nMercenary 2.\nMercenary 2 is also a Fighter, but equipped differently. Protected by an Undroppable Helmet (codice_6) and &lt;a href=\"Studded%20Leather%20Armor%20%2B1\"&gt;Studded Leather Armor +1&lt;/a&gt;, he can either melee with a &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword\"&gt;Bastard Sword&lt;/a&gt; or attack at range with a &lt;a href=\"Composite%20Longbow\"&gt;Composite Longbow&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20%2B1\"&gt;Arrows +1&lt;/a&gt; and mundane arrows .\nLike the others, he too has one Potion of Extra Healing and Well-Off Random Treasure.\nUnlike the others, he is worth .\n&lt;a href=\"%23Top\"&gt;Back\u00a0to\u00a0the\u00a0Top&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TERMER01\"&gt;Mercenary\u00a01&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TERMER03\"&gt;Mercenary\u00a03&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TERMER04\"&gt;Mercenary\u00a04&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TERMER05\"&gt;Mercenary\u00a05&lt;/a&gt;\nMercenary 3.\nMercenary 3 (codice_3) is a Female Human &lt;a href=\"Cleric\"&gt;Cleric&lt;/a&gt; protected by &lt;a href=\"Plate%20Mail\"&gt;Plate Mail&lt;/a&gt; and a High &lt;a href=\"Dexterity\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;. She melees with a &lt;a href=\"Flail%20%2B1\"&gt;Flail +1&lt;/a&gt;, but can also attack at range with a &lt;a href=\"Sling%20%2B1\"&gt;Sling +1&lt;/a&gt; and either &lt;a href=\"Bullet%20%2B1\"&gt;Bullets +1&lt;/a&gt; or mundane bullets.\nAmong her offensive spells are &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Strike\"&gt;Flame Strike&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Hold Person&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Fear\"&gt;Cloak of Fear&lt;/a&gt;.\nShe can also cast &lt;a href=\"Strength%20of%20One\"&gt;Strength of One&lt;/a&gt; to increase, not only her own &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, but also those of her fellow mercenaries, to 18/75.\nShe is worth and can be looted for &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23Wealthy%20treasure\"&gt;Wealthy Random Treasure&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"%23Top\"&gt;Back\u00a0to\u00a0the\u00a0Top&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TERMER01\"&gt;Mercenary\u00a01&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TERMER02\"&gt;Mercenary\u00a02&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TERMER04\"&gt;Mercenary\u00a04&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TERMER05\"&gt;Mercenary\u00a05&lt;/a&gt;\nMercenary 4.\nAs a &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;Thief&lt;/a&gt;, Mercenary 4 (codice_4) focuses on disappearing and backstabbing for quadruple damage with a &lt;a href=\"Dagger%20%2B2\"&gt;Dagger +2&lt;/a&gt;, using either stealth, or &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invisibility\"&gt;Potions of Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; .\nHowever, his very first backstab will be while using an NPC version of &lt;a href=\"MAGE01.ITM\"&gt;Sandthief's Ring&lt;/a&gt;. With this item, he will not be seen by the party entering the room; he can only be spotted after he strikes.\nGiven a chance, he will also quaff his &lt;a href=\"Oil%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Oil of Speed&lt;/a&gt; for faster attacks and movement.\nHe wears &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Armor%20%2B1\"&gt;Leather Armor +1&lt;/a&gt; and is protected against Critical Hits by an Undroppable Helmet (codice_9), despite that Thieves are normally barred from wearing helmets.\nHe is worth and can be looted for Wealthy Random Treasure, and any potions he was unable to use during combat.\n&lt;a href=\"%23Top\"&gt;Back\u00a0to\u00a0the\u00a0Top&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TERMER01\"&gt;Mercenary\u00a01&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TERMER02\"&gt;Mercenary\u00a02&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TERMER03\"&gt;Mercenary\u00a03&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TERMER05\"&gt;Mercenary\u00a05&lt;/a&gt;\nMercenary 5.\nMercenary 5 (codice_5) is a Male Elf &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt; with a complement of offensive and defensive spells.\nHe wears &lt;a href=\"Bracers%20of%20Defense%20AC%207\"&gt;Bracers of Defense AC 7&lt;/a&gt; and is also protected against Critical Hits by an Undroppable Helmet (codice_9), despite that Mages are normally barred from wearing helmets. A Quarterstaff is used if you close to melee range.\nHe is worth and can be looted for Wealthy Random Treasure.\n&lt;a href=\"%23Top\"&gt;Back\u00a0to\u00a0the\u00a0Top&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TERMER01\"&gt;Mercenary\u00a01&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TERMER02\"&gt;Mercenary\u00a02&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TERMER03\"&gt;Mercenary\u00a03&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0\u00a0|\u00a0\u00a0&lt;a href=\"%23TERMER04\"&gt;Mercenary\u00a04&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "54980", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54980", "title": "Mercenary (North Forest)", "text": "Mercenary is a fighter class male orc with an Orog-Elite appearance encountered during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"North%20Forest%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;North Forest (Shadows of Amn)&lt;/a&gt; area.\nGameplay.\nThis mercenary is part of an unknown mixed group of adventurers or perhaps mercenaries encountered in about the center of the area map. The whole group is hostile to any intruders that are detected.\nThe fighter will try and close to melee distance and strike with his enchanted great sword. \nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a new default Fighter AI script for potion use, and smarter ranged and melee combat targeting. Weapon proficiencies are redesignated to 3 pips in two-handed sword and 2 in two-handed weapon fighting style.\nThe fighter is assigned a &lt;a href=\"Berserker\"&gt;Berserker&lt;/a&gt; kit and is scripted to the &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt; ability at the beginning of hostilities.\nTwo potions are available for scripted use during the battle - for ability boosting/protection and one for healing."}
{"id": "50160", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50160", "title": "Mercenary (The Zephir)", "text": "Mercenary Fighter (The Zephir) are inside the only tavern and Inn available in &lt;a href=\"Amkethran\"&gt;Amkethran&lt;/a&gt;. They are not menacing or hostile and are just going about their business. Two of them are clad in Chainmail with golden helms, with a longsword and shield. The third is dressed in a Mage robe. After your party has returned from journeys to defeat &lt;a href=\"Abazigal\"&gt;Abazigal&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sendai\"&gt;Sendai&lt;/a&gt;, these mercenaries will have been informed of your deeds, and find that you are now wanted for death. They will become hostile to you if you enter the Inn.\nMercenary Fighters.\nMercenary Fighter (Creature AMSC02), and essentially a duplicate Mercenary (AMSC03) are both armed with the same equipment and have identical stats. The second fighter is only worth 1,000 XP. Both are protected from &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt;. Both are under a &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Haste effect&lt;/a&gt;, although it is Haste type 2 in &lt;a href=\"IESDP\"&gt;IESDP&lt;/a&gt;. Both are immune to non-magical weapons as well. Although they are level 14 Fighter Class, the game developers have given them no exceptional strength percentages, nor did they provide any weapon proficiencies.\nThey are worth should you defeat both of the Fighters.\nMercenary Mage.\nMercenary, Mage (codice_1) is a Male Human &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt; with an abbreviated complement of offensive and defensive spells. If a non-mage party member tries to speak with him, you will be verbally rebuffed, saying \"\"Begone, fool. I care not for your worries\", or \"Unless you are a mage, I have nothing to say to you\"\". In fact, since the mage's tone is quite abrasive, one of the mercenary fighters even tells the mage to be careful speaking in such a manner to the \"strangers\", as your party is already known. However, if a mage in your party speaks with him there is some interesting dialogue, and more about the &lt;a href=\"Twisted%20Rune\"&gt;Twisted Rune&lt;/a&gt; and ties to &lt;a href=\"Balthazar\"&gt;Balthazar&lt;/a&gt;. The mage even asks you, \"\"You seem the learned type. Are you part of the Twisted Rune hired by Balthazar? I don't recognize you...\"\"\nHe is equipped with a Dagger. The mage has less memorized spells than permitted by experience level and has no proficiency with dagger. \nHe is worth and can be looted for Average Random Treasure.\nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes a few revisions to the two fighters (and most mercenaries in general throughout ToB). No statistics or abilities are changed except as noted. They get an SCS combat script. They get proper fighter weapon proficiencies (grandmastery in long swords, two pips in Sword and Shield fighting style). The Haste effect is now set to &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Haste\"&gt;Improved Haste&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"IESDP\"&gt;IESDP&lt;/a&gt; effect 16 or &lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;Opcode&lt;/a&gt;, type 1. They also receive 63% Magic Resistance.\nThe Mage mercenary gets a properly memorized full gamut of spells commensurate with the experience level and has an Enchanter kit. One pip in dagger proficiency is given. If the SCS \"Smarter Mages\" component is selected, the Mage's AI and spell use will be, well, smarter. Starting with defensive spells then offensive spells afterwards."}
{"id": "46556", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46556", "title": "Mercenary of Riatavin", "text": "Mercenary of Riatavin is a a troupe of two fighters, a Necromancer and a Cleric following the leadership of &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Dennis\"&gt;Captain Dennis&lt;/a&gt;. They're found on the 2nd floor of &lt;a href=\"Delosar%27s%20Inn\"&gt;Delosar's Inn&lt;/a&gt;, located in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; as part of \"\" campaign. When first encountered they are neutral towards Gorion's Ward and party.\nEach Mercenary type has its own labelled information box to the right and below (scroll down if needed). As soon as hostilities begin both the Necromancer and the Cleric are scripted to at least launch uninterupptible contingency spell casts off. After that, any other attempted spell casts can be interrupted as normal.\nThe Fighters will engage in missile attacks until an opponent gets in melee range, then they'll use their greatswords.\nIf you speak with one of the Fighters they may say, \"\"You should have heard of us around here. We're famous all over Amn.\"\nConverse with the Necromancer and he will remark, \"I am the mage of this mercenary troupe... I get paid well, and I'll thank you to leave me be.\"\nAddress the Cleric and he'll surmise, \"Have you perchance been to the temple of Helm here in Athkatla? It is a fine marvel, I think, truly.\"\"\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes the usual adjustments to the fighters, Mage and cleric, by assigning smarter default AI scripts to improve tactical decisions, spell casting, and counter measure behavior. Slight changes to weapon proficiencies and added weapon fighting styles are in place for the fighters and Cleric. Both the Mage and Cleric get mostly different spell choices with revised opening protective buffs. The mage can use a &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; with double &lt;a href=\"Ray%20of%20Enfeeblement\"&gt;Ray of Enfeeblement&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Armor\"&gt;Spirit Armor&lt;/a&gt; if needed, as they are prepared and ready to launch. The Necromancer leans toward Necromancy spells for attack options. SCS random treasures are placed in some creature inventories."}
