{"id": "48407", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48407", "title": "Meredath", "text": "Meredath is a young female &lt;a href=\"Fledgling%20Vampire\"&gt;Fledgling Vampire&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; and a loyal member of &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Vampire%20Coven\"&gt;Bodhi's Vampire Coven&lt;/a&gt;. She is one of the few vampires who is only found in &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Hideout\"&gt;Bodhi's Hideout&lt;/a&gt; within the &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;Lower Tombs&lt;/a&gt;.\nEncounters.\nChapter three.\nDuring &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;3&lt;/a&gt;, if you have decided to &lt;a href=\"Perform%20Bodhi%27s%20Tasks%20to%20Receive%20Her%20Aid\"&gt;side with Bodhi&lt;/a&gt;, she'll be down below the graveyard in Bodhi's base of operations. Speak with her if desired.\nAttacking her doesn't appear to upset Bodhi in the least, although if wounded sufficiently she'll escape actual destruction in gas cloud form, presumably to reform again somewhere in the future, and appearing again later in the game.\nChapter six.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; Meredath will be in Bodhi's Hideout, along with &lt;a href=\"Hareishan%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;Hareishan&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Salia\"&gt;Salia&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Tanova\"&gt;Tanova&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Valen\"&gt;Valen&lt;/a&gt;, five &lt;a href=\"Fledgling%20Vampire\"&gt;fledgling vampires&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Guard%20%28Vampire%29\"&gt;vampire guard&lt;/a&gt;; all of whom are defending Bodhi's inner sanctum from being accessed by &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party (and some helpful allies).\nGameplay.\nMeredath will attack detected enemies with melee ranged touch attacks, inflicting &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt;.\nShe will normally launch a &lt;a href=\"Domination%20%28Innate%29\"&gt;Vampire Domination&lt;/a&gt; at the start of hostilities at the nearest opponent.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod changes to this creature in a few ways. In the unmodded game Meredath is configured as a &lt;a href=\"Fledgling%20Vampire\"&gt;Fledgling Vampire&lt;/a&gt;. SCS makes her a proper vampire and more experienced and powerful opponent worthy of Chapter 6. She is a level 12/12 Fighter/Thief class vampire, with 20 Strength, Dexterity and 19 Constitution. She has 145 HP and her APR, THAC0 and AC are improved.\nHer combat AI script is new, and she will do a better job evaluating targets and know if they are protected vs. level drain and charm. She has other ways to attack if so.\nSee the &lt;a href=\"Vampire\"&gt;Vampire&lt;/a&gt; article and \"Mod content\" section for the additional vampire abilities furnished with this mod."}
{"id": "38862", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38862", "title": "Merella", "text": "Merella is a female &lt;a href=\"ranger\"&gt;ranger&lt;/a&gt; who operated in the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; near &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;. Living in her &lt;a href=\"Ranger%20Cabin\"&gt;cabin&lt;/a&gt; near the village of &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale\"&gt;Imnesvale&lt;/a&gt;, she was the assigned protector of the region, charged with preserving the balance of civilization versus nature and seeking to protect people from monstrous depredations. Unfortunately, when the &lt;a href=\"Shade%20Lord\"&gt;Shade Lord&lt;/a&gt; escaped into the material plane in the &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple\"&gt;Ruined Temple&lt;/a&gt;, Merella's attempts to defeat the otherworldly monster were foiled and it possessed her body, using her as a host for its own malign spirit until it was destroyed by &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;. Merella regained her half-elven form long enough to attempt a thank you to her rescuers but she didn't possess the strength and died with the words on her lips.\n\"(The ranger's words trail off. She is dead.)\""}
{"id": "5309", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5309", "title": "Merella's Journal", "text": "Merella's Journal is the journal of the ranger &lt;a href=\"Merella\"&gt;Merella&lt;/a&gt; and it can be found in her &lt;a href=\"Ranger%20Cabin\"&gt;cabin&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;. It details the recent deaths of several townspeople from the village of &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale\"&gt;Imnesvale&lt;/a&gt;, her suspicions about the culprits being wolves, and the faint whispering of voices in her mind."}
