{"id": "35212", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35212", "title": "Mereth's hairband", "text": "Mereth's hairband is a quest introduced in the &lt;a href=\"Hidden%20Refuge\"&gt;Hidden Refuge&lt;/a&gt; area amid the &lt;a href=\"Neera%27s%20Hidden%20Refuge\"&gt;Neera's Hidden Refuge&lt;/a&gt; quest in .\nAquisition.\nMereth's hairband is a quest provided by &lt;a href=\"Mereth\"&gt;Mereth&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Hidden%20Refuge\"&gt;Hidden Refuge&lt;/a&gt;. It is aquired via dialogue with the child and agreeing to look for the hairband she lost.\nGameplay.\nMereth had been rescued by &lt;a href=\"Neera\"&gt;Neera&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; in a cutscene and had left her &lt;a href=\"Hairband\"&gt;Hairband&lt;/a&gt; behind.\nThe hairband can be found in the crates in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; near where the cutscene took place. Upon return of the item, Mereth rewards &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; with a &lt;a href=\"Wooden%20Horse%20Necklace\"&gt;Wooden Horse Necklace&lt;/a&gt;.\nLike the other quests taking place within the Neera's Hidden Refuge quest, it's recommended that this quest is completed before &lt;a href=\"Neera%27s%20Hidden%20Refuge%23Finding%20Daxus\"&gt;Finding Daxus&lt;/a&gt;.\nNotes.\nThe hairband won't be in place, by script, within the crate until the quest is acquired. It can't be found earlier."}
{"id": "8517", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8517", "title": "Merinid", "text": "Merinid was a drow who lived in the city of &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt;. He sometimes told stories of the city's and the drow's history, although this sometimes angered other drow who believed his stories to be untrue. When Gorions Ward speaks with him, he tells a story about the first matriarch which causes &lt;a href=\"Tathlyn\"&gt;Tathlyn&lt;/a&gt;, another Drow, to attack him.\nWhat was really notable about him was that he had red skin, whereas most drow have dark skin."}
