{"id": "47979", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47979", "title": "Messenger (Aerie)", "text": "This Messenger will appear a few days after &lt;a href=\"Aerie\"&gt;Aerie&lt;/a&gt; has joined the party. He either delivers a verbal message that her &lt;a href=\"Quayle\"&gt;Uncle Quayle&lt;/a&gt; is in need of her help or he will hand her a letter he was commissioned to deliver by &lt;a href=\"Raelis%20Shai\"&gt;Raelis Shai&lt;/a&gt;, if Quayle was killed during the &lt;a href=\"Investigate%20the%20circus%20tent\"&gt;Investigate the circus tent&lt;/a&gt; quest. Following this exchange he'll disappear.\nDialogue.\n\"Excuse me, miss... but you would be named Aerie, yes? The young elven lass that was Quayle's apprentice in the circus?\"\nIf Quayle is alive:\n\"Oh, no, no. Nothing's happened to him, miss. He gave me a very good description of you, in fact, and asked me to track you down.\"\n\"He mentioned that you and your new companions may be able to help him out with something, and asks that you return to the circus to see him as soon as you can, miss.\"\n\"Well, I've done as I were asked, miss, so I really should be going. A good day to you all.\"\nIf Quayle is dead:\n\"Well... it is just that I were commissioned to deliver a letter to Quayle, and with him being... with him being dead and all, I was told you should receive it...\"\n\"Yes, miss. I hereby deliver it into your hands. Now, I really must be on my way. Good day to you all.\""}
{"id": "47977", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47977", "title": "Messenger (Nalia)", "text": "This Messenger will appear when the party returns to &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;, following the liberation of the &lt;a href=\"De%27Arnise%20Keep\"&gt;de'Arnise Keep&lt;/a&gt;, if &lt;a href=\"Nalia%20de%27Arnise\"&gt;Nalia de'Arnise&lt;/a&gt; is a member of the party. He hands her a message regarding her fathers funeral and disappears. He'll reappear when the party reaches the graveyard and lead the them to the funeral location, then disappear for good.\nDialogue.\n\"Miss Nalia? Miss Nalia de'Arnise?\"\n\"I have a message for you, Miss Nalia, from the residents of the de'Arnise estate. I must get an imprint of your signet ring to prove I found you.\"\n\"Thank you, Miss Nalia, though I do hate to be the bearer of somber news. Here is your message. Safe travels to you.\""}
{"id": "20244", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20244", "title": "Metaspell Influence Amulet", "text": ""}
{"id": "4786", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4786", "title": "Meteor Swarm", "text": "Meteor Swarm grants a wizard the ability to pull down meteors upon the battlefield, striking all in the area of effect.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a targeting point for the central impact area desired by the meteor swarm. Then begins the long casting time. If successfully cast, an instant later a meteor swarm visual\neffect plays over the area centered on the caster's target point. This continues for the spell's 4 round duration.\nThe meteors inflict 4d10 &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt; upon all creatures in the area of effect, and this occurs each round of the spell's duration. If a creature leaves the AoE, then no further damage will occur.\nThe fire damage can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;. A &lt;a href=\"Spell%20protections%20type\"&gt;Spell protections type&lt;/a&gt; defense won't provide any mitigation as the meteor swarm is an AoE spell.\nDespite the colorful language in the spell description, the caster won't be performing any random hurling of meteors.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset Wizard spell \"Meteor Swarm\" is quite different in its application than the BG game version. The Wizard can choose to create four or eight spheres, that have different overlapping patterns of destruction and other variable rules. This would have been very difficult to implement in the Infinity Engine, so it is no surprise the spell was changed for the video game.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its saving throw, magic resistance applicability, effects, and description. See below:\nMeteor Swarm\nLevel: 9\nSchool: Evocation\nRange: Long\nDuration: Instant\nCasting Time: 1 round\nArea of Effect: 30\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: Breath half\nUpon completion of this spell, a swarm of minute meteors bombards the affected area, dealing devastating damage to friend and foe. Any creature caught in the destructive path of the meteors will suffer 40d4 points of fire damage, with a save vs. breath at -4 allowed for half damage. The caster is well advised to be careful in his use of this spell. Magic resistance does not affect this spell."}
{"id": "14950", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14950", "title": "Methild's Harp", "text": "Methild's Harp is a musical instrument usable only by the &lt;a href=\"bard\"&gt;bard&lt;/a&gt; class and is introduced only in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%205\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 5&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nUnidentified item description\nIdentified description\nGameplay.\nThis harp is used by placing it in the bard's \"Quick item slot\" (like a wand or potion is normally activated), and then click on the harp to initiate one of its use charges.\nWhen activated, a targeting cursor will appear so that the user can apply the harp's spell effect upon the designated target. Click on the creature (or party portrait) to release the effect.\nThe harp's spell effect has a range of 25-feet and will briefly render a lighting effect on the selected recipient, as well as a sound effect.\nThe result of this spell will:\nThese actions also clear the recipient from any associated status effect portrait icons or graphic animations tied to those status effect.\nThis harp has three uses of the spell effect per 8-hour rest period, upon which it will recharge.\nNotes.\nMethild's Harp exists in the game code of \"\" but does not make an appearance during its events.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced D&amp;D 2nd Edition Dungeon's Master Guide (DMG) doesn't list this harp. This item may have been invented for the game by Bioware."}
{"id": "47990", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47990", "title": "Metigo the Butler", "text": "Metigo the Butler is found on the ground floor of the &lt;a href=\"De%27Arnise%20Keep\"&gt;de'Arnise Keep&lt;/a&gt; if &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; is a fighter and has accepted the keep as a &lt;a href=\"Ruling%20the%20de%27Arnise%20Keep%20and%20Lands\"&gt;stronghold&lt;/a&gt; following it's &lt;a href=\"The%20de%27Arnise%20Keep%20has%20been%20Invaded\"&gt;liberation&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"TorGal\"&gt;TorGal&lt;/a&gt; and his trolls. Most of his dialogue is focused on introducing himself as new help. Later on he may quit if Gorion's Ward is hard on the locals."}
{"id": "50542", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50542", "title": "Metrich Footman", "text": "Metrich Footman can be found within the &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale%20Inn\"&gt;Imnesvale Inn&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Baron%20Metrich\"&gt;Baron Metrich&lt;/a&gt;. This Footman functions as one of the Baron's guards.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a default SCS AI Fighter script for smarter tactical behavior. The mod also revises weapon proficiency to 5 pips for halberd and 2 pips in two-handed weapon fighting style. The warrior will thus strike with more damage, have a better THAC0, additional weapon speed and attacks per round. SCS random treasures are added to the inventory."}
{"id": "50543", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50543", "title": "Metrich Yeoman", "text": "Metrich Yeoman can be found within the &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale%20Inn\"&gt;Imnesvale Inn&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Baron%20Metrich\"&gt;Baron Metrich&lt;/a&gt;. This Yeoman functions as one of the Baron's guards. He will engage with missile fire if hostilities breakout. The developers did not assign a melee weapon he is proficient in, so will strike with a THAC0 penalty.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a default SCS AI Fighter script for smarter tactical behavior. The mod also revises weapon proficiency to 4 pips for Longbow and 2 pips in short sword. This fixes the error on the unmodded creature. The warrior will thus strike with more damage, have a better THAC0, additional weapon speed and attacks per round. SCS random treasures are added to the inventory."}
{"id": "9542", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9542", "title": "Meym", "text": "Meym is a &lt;a href=\"Wolfwere\"&gt;Wolfwere&lt;/a&gt; who can be found on the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Balduran%20North\"&gt;northern&lt;/a&gt; half of the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;Isle of Balduran&lt;/a&gt;. He will try to dissuade &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party from exploring the remains of the &lt;a href=\"Wandering%20Eye\"&gt;Wandering Eye&lt;/a&gt;. Depending on the selected dialogue options, he might attack the party. Otherwise, he will leave the party to their fate, assuring them that &lt;a href=\"Karoug\"&gt;Karoug&lt;/a&gt; will make short work of them.\nIf the conversation ends peacefully he can be talked to again, which will initiate a fight."}
