{"id": "12234", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12234", "title": "Mimic's Blood", "text": "Mimic's Blood is a quest item that consists of a small vial filled with the blood of a shapechanging &lt;a href=\"Killer%20Mimic%23Shadows%20of%20Amn\"&gt;mimic&lt;/a&gt;.\nRelated quest.\n&lt;a href=\"Find%20mimic%27s%20blood%20for%20Jermien%20the%20Cowled%20Wizard\"&gt;Find mimic's blood for Jermien the Cowled Wizard&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Cowled%20Wizard\"&gt;Cowled Wizard&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Jermien\"&gt;Jermien&lt;/a&gt; is building a &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Golem\"&gt;stone golem&lt;/a&gt; to protect his &lt;a href=\"Colette\"&gt;daughter&lt;/a&gt; when he is away, and requires one more ingredient - the blood of a mimic - to complete it."}
{"id": "56154", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56154", "title": "Mimic Acid", "text": "Mimic Acid is an innate spell ability possessed and used by &lt;a href=\"Killer%20Mimic\"&gt;Killer Mimic&lt;/a&gt; creatures encountered in the , , and the .\nEffects.\nThe mimic will cast this spell at a detected party member when within spell range, and the launched projectile follows and strikes the target creature automatically.\nAn acid splash effect plays over the target, and the character is exposed to 3d12 &lt;a href=\"Acid%20damage\"&gt;Acid damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe effect can't be blocked and is unaffected by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nAny protective item, spell, or innate ability that provides acid resistance can mitigate the damage."}
{"id": "56160", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56160", "title": "Mimic Fire", "text": "Mimic Fire is an innate spell ability possessed and used only by a &lt;a href=\"Killer%20Mimic%23Fire%20Mimic\"&gt;Killer Mimic&lt;/a&gt; that is encountered on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Machine%20of%20Lum%20the%20Mad\"&gt;fourth level&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffects.\nThe mimic will cast this spell at a detected party member when within spell range, and the launched projectile follows and strikes the target creature automatically.\nAn acid splash effect plays over the target, and a fire burst animation, and the character is exposed to 3d12 &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe effect can't be blocked and is unaffected by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nAny protective item, spell, or innate ability that provides fire protection can mitigate the damage."}
{"id": "56153", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56153", "title": "Mimic Glue", "text": "Mimic Glue is an innate spell ability possessed and used by &lt;a href=\"Killer%20Mimic\"&gt;Killer Mimic&lt;/a&gt; creatures encountered in the , , and the .\nEffects.\nThe mimic will cast this spell at a detected party member when within spell range, and the launched projectile follows and strikes the target creature automatically.\nA lighting effect plays over the target, and the character is exposed to a &lt;a href=\"paralyze\"&gt;paralyze&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nA &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Breath will negate the effect.\nIf the save is missed, the target creature is paralyzed for 30 seconds (five rounds) and made immobile and &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt; - the character also has a \"Grease\" overlay placed on their sprite and a \"Held\" icon on the portrait.\nThis innate spell is unaffected by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt; protections.\nThe effect can't be dispelled.\nThe internal spell &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; of the effect is 10, and thus certain spell protections can block/reflect it, such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20of%20the%20Archons\"&gt;Shield of the Archons&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;.\nAny protective item, spell, or innate ability that prevents the paralyze status effect will ensure that this glue won't cause a problem.\nNotes.\nThe chickens encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; have this spell in their spellbook but possess no method of utilizing said spell.\nAn Imp that is encountered in the \"Siege of Dragonspear\" campaign and the creatures &lt;a href=\"T%27alcor\"&gt;T'alcor&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Air%20Elemental%20%28BPII%29\"&gt;Greater Air Elemental&lt;/a&gt; encountered during the campaign are provided immunity to this spell's effects. The reasoning behind this is indiscernible at the present time."}
{"id": "56158", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56158", "title": "Mimic Poison", "text": "Mimic Poison is an innate spell ability possessed and used by a &lt;a href=\"Killer%20Mimic%23Poison%20Mimic\"&gt;Killer Mimic&lt;/a&gt; that is encountered on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Machine%20of%20Lum%20the%20Mad\"&gt;fourth level&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt;. A door (Joker's door) located in the &lt;a href=\"Staging%20Area\"&gt;Staging Area&lt;/a&gt; of the also utilizes the spell as a defensive mechanism if the trap is triggered.\nEffects.\nWhen the spell is cast at a detected party member when within spell range, the launched projectile follows and strikes the target creature automatically.\nAn acid splash effect plays over the target, and the character is exposed to 3d12 &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe effect can't be blocked and is unaffected by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nAny protective item, spell, or innate ability that provides poison resistance or immunity to the &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; effect can mitigate the damage."}
{"id": "56164", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56164", "title": "Mimic Web", "text": "Mimic Web is an innate spell ability possessed and used only by a &lt;a href=\"Killer%20Mimic%23Web%20Mimic\"&gt;Killer Mimic&lt;/a&gt; that is encountered on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Machine%20of%20Lum%20the%20Mad\"&gt;fourth level&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffects.\nThe mimic will cast this spell at a detected party member when within spell range, and the lunched projectile follows and strikes the target creature automatically.\nA lighting effect plays over the target, and the character is exposed to a &lt;a href=\"paralyze\"&gt;paralyze&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nA &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spell with a 2-point penalty will negate the effect.\nIf the save is missed, the target creature is paralyzed for 21 seconds and made immobile and &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt; - the character also has a \"Web\" overlay placed on their sprite and a \"Held\" icon on the portrait.\nThis innate spell ca be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; but not by &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt; protections.\nThe effect can be dispelled.\nThe internal spell &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; of the effect is 0, and thus no Spell Protections can stop it.\nNotes.\nThe creatures &lt;a href=\"T%27alcor\"&gt;T'alcor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Air%20Elemental%20%28BPII%29\"&gt;Greater Air Elemental&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Earth%20Elemental%20%28BPII%29\"&gt;Greater Earth Elemental&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Fire%20Elemental%20%28BPII%29\"&gt;Greater Fire Elemental&lt;/a&gt; encountered during the campaign are provided immunity to this spell's effects, but the reasoning behind this is indiscernible at the present time."}
