{"id": "23427", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23427", "title": "Mind Flayers in Underdark", "text": "You\u2019ll be captured by mind flayers after trasnitioning from the Underdark through the Eastern Tunnels exit. The party can only regain their freedom by destroying &lt;a href=\"The%20Master%20Brain\"&gt;The Master Brain&lt;/a&gt;. \nDescription.\nThis area is an alien system of passages and chambers constructed by the illithids. There is a distinct architecture and design to their lair. Doors, strange furnishings, decor and lighting are present within - including various machinery, vats of strange liquids, tadpole breeding pools, prisoner and slave cells and other chambers are present. At the heart of the complex is the Master brain and attendants.\nExpect a number of hostile illithid creatures as well as their Umber Hulk pets."}
{"id": "46532", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46532", "title": "Mind Key", "text": "The Mind Key is the reward from the &lt;a href=\"Globe%20Machine\"&gt;Globe Machine&lt;/a&gt; after each specific-colored globe is placed in the corresponding colored tube containers.\nThis key, as well as the &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Key\"&gt;Spirit Key&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Heart%20Key\"&gt;Heart Key&lt;/a&gt; are needed to unbar the wheel device, which can then be turned to open the final seal, leading to a portal to the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Imprisoned%20One\"&gt;Lower reaches&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nOnce this key is obtained, it may be used to open one of the pedestal locks adjacent to the final seal in the center of this dungeon level.\nThere is no requirement to have all three keys in order to utilize a key and unlock the matching pedestal. The choice is up to the party. \nUsing the key with the cursor results in a text display, reading:\nWhen the key is turned, each party member receives quest points, as well as an instant appearance of the guardians.\nSee the gallery screenshots."}
