{"id": "8159", "revid": "284530", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8159", "title": "Minister Lloyd", "text": "Minister Lloyd Wainwright is the mayor of &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale\"&gt;Imnesvale&lt;/a&gt; located in the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign. &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; first encounters the Minister near the village fountain, with townsfolk pressuring him to solve the crisis of their missing villagers. Afterwards he can be found in his home.\nAfter the opening scene at the fountain plays out, you can talk to him in his home. He will give you more detail on the crisis and warn you that he \"\"already hired the famous knight, &lt;a href=\"Mazzy%20Fentan\"&gt;Mazzy Fentan&lt;/a&gt;, and her troupe...but they haven't been back.\"\" He also suggests a few leads to follow, including:\nFor killing the &lt;a href=\"Shade%20Lord\"&gt;Shade Lord&lt;/a&gt;, he will reward the party with &lt;a href=\"The%20Night%27s%20Gift\"&gt;The Night's Gift&lt;/a&gt; armor and .\nBugs.\ncodice_1 and he will appear."}
