{"id": "5009", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5009", "title": "Minor Globe of Invulnerability", "text": "The Minor Globe of Invulnerability spell creates a magical sphere around the wizard that is impenetrable to 1st-3rd level spells.\nThe more powerful version is &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this spell to self only.\nWhen the spell is finished, a semi-translucent globe surrounds the caster, and their sprite will have a subtle color change effect for the spell's duration.\nA text display reads \"Shielded\", and a character will have an icon (No. 122) titled \"Minor Globe of Invulnerability\" on their portrait.\nAdditionally, a sound effect is audibled when the spell is cast, and another when the spell duration elapses.\nThe globe will prevent any &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 1 through 3 spell or effect from penetrating from outside the globe to the caster inside the globe, whether from friend or foe.\nLike &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Shield\"&gt;Spell Shield&lt;/a&gt;, and unlike spells such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;, the Globe protects against &lt;a href=\"Game%20Terminology%23A\"&gt;AoE&lt;/a&gt; attacks.\n&lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt; are not stopped by the Globe, they simply ignore it. They also don't dispel the Globe itself, but they can still dispel all other effects on the target.\nIt also blocks friendly spells by allies, such as &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Paralysis\"&gt;Remove Paralysis&lt;/a&gt;, but does not block the caster's own spells unless they would deal damage to themselves (so the caster can &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt; themself but is protected against their own &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt;).\nWhere to obtain its scroll.\n\"Shadows of Amn\".\nTreasure\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Minor Globe of Invulnerability\" can be taken down by a successful Dispel magic. See the External links for further reading.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects and description. See below for description:\nMinor Globe of Invulnerability\nLevel: 4\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 1 round/level\nCasting Time: 4\nArea of Effect: Caster\nSaving Throw: None\nThis spell creates a faintly shimmering magical sphere around the caster that prevents any 1st-, 2nd-, or 3rd-level spell effects from penetrating (i.e., the area of effect of any such spells does not include the area of the globe of invulnerability). This includes innate abilities and effects from devices. However, any type of spell can be cast out of the magical sphere, and these pass from the caster of the globe to their subject without affecting the globe. Fourth and higher-level spells are not affected by the globe. The globe can be brought down by a successful dispel magic."}
{"id": "20503", "revid": "978785", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20503", "title": "Minor Globe of Invulneribility", "text": ""}
{"id": "4893", "revid": "285451", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4893", "title": "Minor Sequencer", "text": "The Minor Sequencer spell allows a caster to store two spells and activate them both at the same time as though they were an innate ability. The casting time for this ability is 1.\nGameplay.\nThe caster creates a \"Minor Sequencer\" by casting the spell on self.\nA brief casting animation plays out, and then a Minor Sequencer menu screen is displayed - the instruction reads \"ADD SPELLS TO YOUR SEQUENCER\".\nThe player may select up to two memorized spells from the 1st and 2nd level spell book(s) to add. If the caster has both Wizard and Priest spells, then any of those applicable spell choices can be selected (e.g. a &lt;a href=\"Cleric%20/%20Mage\"&gt;Cleric / Mage&lt;/a&gt; multiclass can also put Cleric spells in the Sequencer.)\nWhen all the spells desired are \"clicked\" on and entered, select the \"DONE\" button, and the minor sequencer creation animation graphic renders over the caster's sprite Additionally, an icon is placed on the character's portrait titled \"Minor Sequencer Active\". If you changed your mind about a spell you have selected, you can click on the selected spell to cancel it and choose another one in its place (before clicking \"DONE\").\nIn case a player has forgotten what spells have been placed inside the sequencer, they can find out by opening their Spell Book and clicking on the button \"CONTINGENCY\". This will display a list with all their spell sequencers, triggers and contingencies, showing which spells have been selected for each one.\nTo use the sequencer, for instance during a battle, select the character and the Special Abilities button (F12), which displays all the current abilities that can be selected. Click on the \"Minor Sequencer\" icon to activate it and designate a target.\nA mage can have one Minor Sequencer, one &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; and one &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trigger\"&gt;Spell Trigger&lt;/a&gt; each active at the same time but can't have two of the same type active at the same time.\nMoreover, if the required range of the two spells differs significantly, one of them will likely fail. In other words, the range at which the sequencer is released must be such that satisfies both spells' effective range. Also, the target of the sequencer must be an eligible target for both spells. For example, if a mage tries to cast Web followed by Invisibility with the same Minor Sequencer targeting the ground, only the Web part of the sequencer will work - however, if the mage targets themself, then both spells will work (the caster will be invisible with a Web centered on him). A player may have to practice this a few times to appreciate the dynamic of different ranged spells in a sequencer, so as to get them both to work.\nSince the duration is permanent until triggered, you can memorize the sequencer and the spells you want to put in it, cast it, then replace the used spells and rest. That way, you still have the trigger active after rest but also have more spell slots for the next encounter.\nSeveral spells that require the same type of &lt;a href=\"saving%20throw\"&gt;saving throw&lt;/a&gt; roll with the same modifier within the same short time frame will share a single roll instead of each having their own. This might be intended rather than a bug. Either way, sharing the same roll, they will fail or succeed in sync. If the player is trying to inflict a status effect like &lt;a href=\"Horror\"&gt;Horror&lt;/a&gt; for instance, two of the same spells shoved into a Minor Sequencer are no more likely to succeed than one. Note that persistent spells like &lt;a href=\"Web\"&gt;Web&lt;/a&gt; will share a roll only in the first round. Subsequent rounds will force a save roll for both spells.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset has no spell titled \"Minor Sequencer\" - although there is a rare \"The Simbul's Spell Sequencer\" mentioned. This spell is a creation from Bioware for the BG game.\nMod content.\nRegarding this type of spell, the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod will do the following, but only if you do not install &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt;:\nMake spell sequencers, spell triggers, and contingencies learnable by all mages&lt;br&gt;\nIn the unmodded game, spell sequencers, contingencies etc. are in the Evocation school, making them unavailable to Enchanters; this is a serious weakness for the class. This component moves them to be in both the Conjuration and Evocation schools (like Wish), so that all mages may use them. The affected spells are Minor Sequencer, Spell Sequencer, Spell Trigger, Contingency, and Chain Contingency. This will not take effect if you have Spell Revisions installed (as SR takes care of this already by making them \"Universal\" School).\nWith &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; installed, this is the equivalent spell description:\nSimbul\u2019s Spell Matrix\nLevel: 4&lt;br&gt;\nSchool: Universal&lt;br&gt;\nRange: Personal&lt;br&gt;\nDuration: Special&lt;br&gt;\nCasting Time: 1 round&lt;br&gt;\nArea of Effect: Special&lt;br&gt;\nSaving Throw: None&lt;br&gt;\nThis spell allows a mage to prepare a magical matrix that can store spells to be used later in a single swift action. The matrix can store two spells to be released simultaneously, all of which must be of 2nd level or lower. A mage can only possess one spell matrix at a time, and the matrix will remain active until the spells contained within it are released."}
{"id": "5864", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5864", "title": "Minor Spell Deflection", "text": "Minor Spell Deflection protects the caster in a field of magical energy that deflects incoming spells.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this spell to self only.\nWhen the spell is finished, a swirling white animation graphic surrounds the caster (for the duration of the spell), and their sprite will have a subtle color change effect for a few seconds.\nA text display reads \"Protected by Minor Spell Deflection\", and a character will have an icon (No. 67) titled \"Spell Deflection\" on their portrait.\nAdditionally, a sound effect is audibled when the spell is cast.\nThe spell protects against some spells that are aimed as a single-target attack directed at the caster. However, the caster can cast spells on itself.\nThe limits of the Minor Spell Deflection and its capacity to withstand spells is as stated in the description, which is accurate.\nThe spell doesn't protect against area of effect spells such as fireball or Abi-Dalzim's Horrid Wilting.\nIt also blocks single-target beneficial spells by allies - so for example a touch range &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Critical%20Wounds\"&gt;Cure Critical Wounds&lt;/a&gt; by a party member is not possible!\nAny spell removing magic attack can cancel the Minor Spell Deflection - the most basic being &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Thrust\"&gt;Spell Thrust&lt;/a&gt;.\nA &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Shield\"&gt;Spell Shield&lt;/a&gt; can defend the Minor Spell Deflection from being removed by spell removing magic.\nMinor Spell deflection is not touched by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects - those effects go past the spell deflection, and don't interact with the deflection at all.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; is also active, it will override Minor Spell Deflection. They are not cumulative, negating an incoming spell will drain both at the same time. If both a deflection spell and a turning spell (&lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Minor Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;) are active, then the turning will take priority; while charges of spell turning remain, the spell deflection will not be drained. The spell deflection will only trigger and be drained once the turning effect is exhausted.\nList of spells that can be deflected (innate abilities and enemy-only abilities not included).\nDivine spells:\nLevel 1: Command, Doom, Magic Stone\nLevel 3: Call Lightning (even when you're not the original target), Summon Insects\nLevel 4: Mental Domination, Poison\nLevel 5: Cause Critical Wounds (including from beholder rays), Flame Strike, Slay Living\nLevel 6: Harm, Dolorous Decay, Sol's Searing Orb\nLevel 7: Ether Gate, Finger of Death, Implosion\nArcane Spells:\nLevel 1: Blindness, Charm Person, Chill Touch (not the fist damage), Chromatic Orb, Larloch's Minor Drain, Magic Missile, Shocking Grasp (not the fist damage), Spook\nLevel 2: Agannazar's Scorcher (even when you're not the original target), Deafness, Ghoul Touch (not the fist damage), Melf's Acid Arrow, Power Word: Sleep, Ray of Enfeeblement\nLevel 3: Dire Charm, Flame Arrow, Lightning Bolt (only if you're the original target), Melf's Minute Meteors (only the fire damage), Vampiric Touch\nLevel 4: Contagion, Fireshield: Blue and Red, Polymorph Other\nLevel 5: Domination, Feeblemind\nLevel 6: Chain Lightning (only if you're the original target), Disintegrate, Flesh to Stone, Power Word: Silence\nLevel 7: Finger of Death, Power Word: Stun\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset has no Wizard spell titled \"Minor Spell Deflection\" - the nearest equivalent would be \"Minor Spell Turning\", a 4th level Wizard spell. It appears Bioware created this spell for the BG game.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects and duration. See below for description:\nMinor Spell Deflection\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 5 turns\nCasting Time: 3\nArea of Effect: Caster\nSaving Throw: None\nThis abjuration spell causes any spells cast against the wizard to be absorbed and consumed. This affects a total of 6 spell levels but having 1 level left of protection means a 1st level spell would get absorbed, as well as a 4th level spell. Spells greater than 4th level will not be affected. This spell will not protect the caster from a dispel magic. However, it will not be affected by a dispel magic, either.\nThis spell absorbs spells cast from scrolls and innate spell-like abilities but will not protect against area effect spells that are not centered directly upon the wizard (such as Fireball), or stationary area effect spells (such as Cloudkill and Stinking Cloud)."}
{"id": "5852", "revid": "285146", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5852", "title": "Minor Spell Turning", "text": "Minor Spell Turning reflects spells that directly target the wizard, sending them directly back to their original source.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this spell to self only.\nWhen the spell is finished, a white disc animation graphic is underfoot of the caster (for the duration of the spell), and their sprite will have a subtle color change effect for a few seconds.\nA text display reads \"Protected by Minor Spell Turning\", and a character will have an icon (No. 65) titled \"Spell Turning\" on their portrait.\nAdditionally, a sound effect is audibled when the spell is cast.\nThe spell protects against some spells that are aimed as a single-target attack directed at the caster. However, the caster can cast spells on itself.\nThe limits of the Minor Spell Turning and its capacity to withstand and bounce spells back is as stated in the description, which is accurate.\nThe spell doesn't protect against area of effect spells such as &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Abi-Dalzim%27s%20Horrid%20Wilting\"&gt;Abi-Dalzim's Horrid Wilting&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt also bounces single-target beneficial spells by allies - so for example a &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Critical%20Wounds\"&gt;Cure Critical Wounds&lt;/a&gt; by a party member is rebounded on the caster.\nAny spell-removing magic attack can cancel the Minor Spell Deflection - the lowest-level one being &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Thrust\"&gt;Spell Thrust&lt;/a&gt;.\nA &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Shield\"&gt;Spell Shield&lt;/a&gt; can defend the Minor Spell Turning from being removed by spell-removing magic.\nMinor Spell Turning is not affected by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects - those effects go past the spell, and don't interact with the turning at all.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt; is also active, it will override Minor Spell Turning. They are not cumulative, any turned spell will drain both. If both a turning spell and a deflection spell (&lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;) are active, then the turning will take priority; while charges of spell turning remain, the spell deflection will not be drained. The spell deflection will only trigger and be drained once the turning effect is exhausted.\nThis spell can't rebound a &lt;a href=\"Magic%20attack%20type\"&gt;Magic attack type&lt;/a&gt; spell (such as Spell Thrust) back at the originator.\nList of spells that can be turned (innate abilities and enemy-only abilities not included).\nDivine spells:\nArcane Spells:\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Minor Spell Turning\" has some significant differences from the BG game's version. For example, one to four (1d4) spell levels may be turned. The exact number is secretly rolled by the DM; the player never knows how effective the spell is. Also, ff the protected wizard and a spellcasting attacker both have spell turning effects operating, a resonating field is created that has variable bizarre side-effects, from fairly benign to catastrophic.\nBug.\nThis spell's coding has an error and is set to execute a \"Webbed\" portrait icon on the caster's portrait - fortunately the spell coding overrides this by the correct internal icon placement configured by Beamdog, which is \"hard coded\" into the actual spell. So, not a noticeable bug actually.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced the spell \"Minor Spell Turning\" with \"Spell Deflection\". See below for description:\nSpell Deflection\nLevel: 5\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 5 turns\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: Caster\nSaving Throw: None\nThis abjuration spell causes any spells cast against the wizard to be absorbed and consumed. This affects a total of 9 spell levels but having 1 level left of protection means a 1st level spell would get absorbed, as well as a 7th level spell. Spells greater than 7th level will not be affected. This spell will not protect the caster from a dispel magic. However, it will not be affected by a dispel magic, either.\nThis spell absorbs spells cast from scrolls and innate spell-like abilities but will not protect against area effect spells that are not centered directly upon the wizard (such as Fireball), or stationary area effect spells (such as Cloudkill and Stinking Cloud).\nWith &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mods installed, Spell Deflection will absorb a Breach spell, just like any other single-target spell effect with a &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; rating between 1 and 9."}
{"id": "29047", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29047", "title": "Minotaur", "text": "Minotaur are &lt;a href=\"chaotic%20evil\"&gt;chaotic evil&lt;/a&gt; tall and muscular humanoid &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt;s with coarse fur-covered bodies and bull-like heads. They tend to favor axes as weapons.\nThese beasts are able to get into melee range and commence close quarters combat, swinging their battle Axe with great strength. In the original game, it looks as if the monster was modeled on the &lt;a href=\"Ogre\"&gt;Ogre&lt;/a&gt; and given a different animation. The creature has 3 pips in \"Spiked Weapon\" proficiency assigned, like the Ogre, but none of the in-game Minotaur actually use this weapon category. This is likely an oversight. \nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes modest revisions to the basic 4 HD versions of these minotaur creatures. A default SCS Fighter Script is assigned for better and smarter tactical AI behavior. The Minotaur is also provided with 2 pips in Axe weapon proficiency and 2 pips in single weapon fighting style. This improves THAC0, damage, critical hit chances and armor class slightly."}
{"id": "35451", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35451", "title": "Minotaur (Umar Hills)", "text": "A minotaur, &lt;a href=\"lawful%20evil\"&gt;lawful evil&lt;/a&gt; in the original ' and &lt;a href=\"true%20neutral\"&gt;true neutral&lt;/a&gt; in ', can be found amongst &lt;a href=\"Madulf\"&gt;Madulf&lt;/a&gt;'s followers in the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "39642", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39642", "title": "Minotaur Horn", "text": "These two items are found in &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Bodhi%27s%20Hunt%20Level%203\"&gt;Spellhold Bodhi's Hunt Level 3&lt;/a&gt; by way of exploration and searching all containers. No clues are provided in-game as to their existence or whereabouts.\nGameplay.\nFind both horns in two separate containers in different rooms within the labyrinth. Eventually the party will come across a large Minotaur Statue. \nIf the statue is examined (using the cursor), a text message displays \"This statue is missing its horns.\"\nWith that clue, and seemingly no other way to open the sealed door in the same room as the statue, interact with the statue with both horns in the inventory to open the door. Additionally, each party member receives an XP reward. \nSee the screenshot in the gallery below."}
