{"id": "2829", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2829", "title": "Mithral Chain Mail", "text": "Mithral Chain Mail +4 (also known as Mithril Chain Mail +4 in original games), is the armor of &lt;a href=\"Drizzt%20Do%27Urden\"&gt;Drizzt Do'Urden&lt;/a&gt;. It is one of the best sets of armor in the game as, despite being almost as strong as &lt;a href=\"Full%20Plate%20Armor\"&gt;Full Plate Armor&lt;/a&gt;, it is lighter than any other armor available. In fact it is so light, that it allows the wearer to use &lt;a href=\"Thieving%20Abilities\"&gt;thieving skills&lt;/a&gt; without any penalty, a quality which makes it a great choice of armor for &lt;a href=\"Cleric%20/%20Thief\"&gt;cleric / thieves&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Fighter%20/%20Thief\"&gt;fighter / thieves&lt;/a&gt;, especially in .\nTo obtain it, one must kill Drizzt. This is extremely difficult, and will reduce &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt;. It will also have consequences if the &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; gets imported into Baldur's Gate II."}
