{"id": "7369", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7369", "title": "Mithrest Inn", "text": "The Mithrest Inn is an upscale full service Inn located within &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". It is an establishment for the nobility and the rich merchants.\nTry their fine beverages, some of which are quite rare. The more expensive and of high quality, the better chance of getting a good Rumor and possibly useful insight into occurrences, city politics, and local scuttlebutt. Drinking too many in one session may lead to becoming &lt;a href=\"Intoxicated\"&gt;Intoxicated&lt;/a&gt;, but that's one reason the party is quaffing booze, right?\nAs this establishment caters to the wealthy, it is a prime area for some five fingered discounts should the party have a rogue.\nQuests.\n&lt;a href=\"Keldorn%20Wishes%20to%20Visit%20His%20Wife%20and%20Family\"&gt;Keldorn Wishes to Visit His Wife and Family&lt;/a&gt;"}
