{"id": "8119", "revid": "275813", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8119", "title": "Mitsu", "text": "Mitsu is a female &lt;a href=\"halfling\"&gt;halfling&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thief&lt;/a&gt; who works under the Shadowmaster &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thief%20Guildhall\"&gt;Shadow Thief Guildhall&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Athkatla Docks&lt;/a&gt; district. She is found inside the &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail%27s%20Hideout\"&gt;secret hideout&lt;/a&gt; in the lounge that's located near the entrance from the guildhall.\nEngaging her in conversation provides a bit of background on couple of other characters found within the hideout, as well as a few of her recent escapades, but nothing of any real importance. She doesn't like it when people make fun of her size, due to her being a halfling and she'll warn you that it would be wise not to annoy Aran. She'll also have a couple of short back and forth dialogues with &lt;a href=\"Cuchul\"&gt;Cuchul&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"Hoi, greetings to ya. Me name's Mitsu, an' don't go tryin' to make it rhyme with any funny nicknames, now, because I'm small an' such. I'm a Shadow Thief, just as you are.\"\n\"Cuchul, you'll keep yer wanderin' eyes t' yerself if ya knows what's best for ya...\"\n\"I knows what it stirs, boy. Jus' keep it locked up, and there won't be any need for me dagger to get itchy.\""}
{"id": "15201", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15201", "title": "Mizhena", "text": "Mizhena is a &lt;a href=\"true%20neutral\"&gt;true neutral&lt;/a&gt; human &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;. She is a priest of &lt;a href=\"Tempus\"&gt;Tempus&lt;/a&gt; and joins the fight against &lt;a href=\"the%20Crusade\"&gt;the Crusade&lt;/a&gt;. Throughout \"\" she functions as a mobile temple who will travel along with the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; and later the &lt;a href=\"Coalition\"&gt;Coalition&lt;/a&gt;.\nHer father is &lt;a href=\"Urold\"&gt;Urold&lt;/a&gt;.\nBuy and Sell.\nShe only offers regular temple services. The shop is handled by Quartermaster &lt;a href=\"Belegarm\"&gt;Belegarm&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue.\nThe player can choose to engage Mizhena in a series of dialogues.\n\"I am Mizhena, faithful of Tempus. Praise the Lord of Battles!\"\n\"Tempus, the lord of strength at arms and military might, will lead us to victory!\"\n\"Quartermaster Belegarm handles supplies. I may be able to help with cleric services though. The Lord of Battle's favor is a handy thing to have, especially in times like these.\" \u2192 (Opens temple shop)\n\"When I was born, my parents thought me a boy and raised me as such. In time, we all came to understand I was truly a woman. I created my new name from syllables of different languages. All have special meaning to me, it is the truest reflection of who I am.\""}
{"id": "38776", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38776", "title": "Mizhena's Amulet (item)", "text": "Mizhena's Amulet is an of sentimental value only available in \"\". \nIt was lost by &lt;a href=\"Mizhena\"&gt;Mizhena&lt;/a&gt; in a skirmish against &lt;a href=\"Shining%20Crusade\"&gt;Shining Crusade&lt;/a&gt;rs, and she asks to return it to her.\nAcquisition.\nIt is gained during the &lt;a href=\"Mizhena%27s%20Amulet%20%28quest%29\"&gt;\"Mizhena's Amulet\" quest&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River%20Entrance\"&gt;Underground River Entrance&lt;/a&gt; map. Near the northeastern corner of the map a pack of &lt;a href=\"BDDISPBE.CRE\"&gt;Displacer Beast&lt;/a&gt;s can be found. When slain, the amulet can be retrieved from the bodies."}
{"id": "51880", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51880", "title": "Mizhena's Amulet (quest)", "text": "Mizhena's Amulet is a given by &lt;a href=\"Mizhena\"&gt;Mizhena&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". \nAcquisition.\nThis quest may be gained by speaking to &lt;a href=\"Mizhena\"&gt;Mizhena&lt;/a&gt; several times after discussing her faith in &lt;a href=\"Tempus\"&gt;Tempus&lt;/a&gt;. This can happen in at the camp at the &lt;a href=\"Coast%20Way%20Crossing\"&gt;Coast Way Crossing&lt;/a&gt;, at the &lt;a href=\"Troll%20Claw%20Woods\"&gt;Troll Claw Woods&lt;/a&gt;, or in at the &lt;a href=\"Coalition%20Camp\"&gt;Coalition Camp&lt;/a&gt;.\nWalkthrough.\n&lt;a href=\"Mizhena\"&gt;Mizhena&lt;/a&gt; has lost &lt;a href=\"Mizhena%27s%20Amulet%20%28item%29\"&gt;her amulet&lt;/a&gt; while in a skirmish with &lt;a href=\"Shining%20Crusade\"&gt;Crusaders&lt;/a&gt;. As it is of sentimental value to her, she asks &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to retrieve it.\nIt can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River%20Entrance\"&gt;Underground River Entrance&lt;/a&gt; map. Near the northeastern corner of the map, north of the ogre bandit camp, there is a cave (around 4449.1082) that will spawn several &lt;a href=\"BDDISPBE.CRE\"&gt;Displacer Beast&lt;/a&gt;s, which, at harder difficulties, may include a &lt;a href=\"BDDISPBP.CRE\"&gt;Pack Lord&lt;/a&gt;. When slain, the amulet can be retrieved from the bodies.\nOnce the amulet is returned, the party may choose to inquire about Mizhena's background over a short back and forth. Through her answers, she will suggest that she is transgender and explain how the amulet marked her family's acceptance, as her mother carved it with the initials of both her birth name and her chosen name Mizhena. As long as she is asked to confide all the way through and the reaction to her confidences is not \"None of that makes any sense to me\" or \"There are far stranger things in this world, I suppose\", Mizhena will start to see the party as friends.\nAll dialogue paths lead to the same reward for returning the amulet and per party member. Having Mizhena's friendship will alter some of her lines going forward, but should not provide the party with any special benefit or opportunity except in the case of &lt;a href=\"Mizhena%27s%20father\"&gt;Mizhena's Father quest&lt;/a&gt; \u2014 obtained and rewarded in the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Exterior\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Exterior&lt;/a&gt; area. This quest requires completion of the Amulet quest, which can be started in Chapter Ten at the latest. But to receive Mizhena's father quest without her friendship, the party must postpone returning the amulet until right after &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Eleven%20%E2%80%93%20Dragonspear%20Castle%20Battle\"&gt;Chapter Eleven&lt;/a&gt;'s battle outside the castle. See the &lt;a href=\"Mizhena%27s%20father%23Acquisition\"&gt;acquisition conditions&lt;/a&gt; for the \"Mizhena's father\" quest for details."}
{"id": "55626", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55626", "title": "Mizhena's father", "text": "Mizhena's Amulet is a given by &lt;a href=\"Mizhena\"&gt;Mizhena&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nAcquisition.\nMizhena may talk about an issue regarding her father &lt;a href=\"Urold\"&gt;Urold&lt;/a&gt; when she is in the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Exterior\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Exterior&lt;/a&gt; area. Two mutually exclusive scenarios may lead her to raise the topic with &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;. The scenario that will effectively unfold in any given playthrough depends on the moment in time when the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; returned &lt;a href=\"Mizhena%27s%20Amulet%20%28item%29\"&gt;Mizhena's Amulet&lt;/a&gt;, as part of an &lt;a href=\"Mizhena%27s%20Amulet%20%28quest%29\"&gt;earlier quest&lt;/a&gt;. If the amulet is returned in the Dragonspear Castle Exterior area after &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Eleven%20%E2%80%93%20Dragonspear%20Castle%20Battle\"&gt;Chapter Eleven&lt;/a&gt;'s big battle, then Mizhena will immediately follow with her father's quest. If, on the other hand, the amulet was returned earlier, Mizhena will only hand out this quest if she sees the party as friends. Mizhena's friendship can only be secured outside of the Dragonspear Castle Exterior area \u2014 see the &lt;a href=\"Mizhena%27s%20Amulet%20%28quest%29\"&gt;Mizhena's Amulet quest&lt;/a&gt; walkthrough for details.\nWalkthrough.\nOnce the battle outside Dragonspear Castle is over, Mizhena will wander around the castle courtyard so, initially, players won't be able to talk to her until she stops walking for the first time. If the &lt;a href=\"%23Acquisition\"&gt;conditions for quest acquisition&lt;/a&gt; are met, she will trust the party to find her father, Urold, who must be imprisoned somewhere on the map.\nUrold is located northwest of the area (1682, -137). The entrance is guarded by a group of hostile level 12 mercenaries. Up ahead, there will be a dead end where there are four prisoners, one of these being Mizhena's father. They are all guarded by two dogs and a level 8 fighter named &lt;a href=\"Therli\"&gt;Therli&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce Therli and her dogs are eliminated, Urold approaches the player to thank him for the rescue. No matter which option Gorion's Ward chooses, it will end up asking him about his identity, linking him to Mizhena. Urold can become hostile if at the end of the conversation you choose the third dialogue option that states: \"I think not. A follower of Tempus proud of wasting in a cage? You disgust me and you shall not live to see my day's end.\"\nKilling Urold in any way, even after finishing neutral dialogue with him, will lose the rewards of the quest in exchange for 420 XP for his death (in addition to 5,000 XP for his release if he is not verbally attacked). \nHead to the central area of the castle courtyard to speak to Mizhena, who may be standing somewhere or wandering around the area, and notify her that her father has been freed to receive a reward of 2500 XP and the &lt;a href=\"Blazing%20Glory%20%2B3\"&gt;Blazing Glory +3&lt;/a&gt;."}
