{"id": "48734", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48734", "title": "Mogadish", "text": "Mogadish is a vicious, cannibalistic Halfling &lt;a href=\"Cleric\"&gt;Cleric&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Athas\"&gt;Athas&lt;/a&gt; who has been abducted along with his fellow halflings and now resides within the &lt;a href=\"Inside%20the%20Planar%20Sphere%23The%20Caverns\"&gt;Caverns&lt;/a&gt; inside of the &lt;a href=\"The%20Planar%20Sphere\"&gt;Planar Sphere&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlong with his fellows, &lt;a href=\"Kayardi\"&gt;Kayardi&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Entu\"&gt;Entu&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Togan\"&gt;Togan&lt;/a&gt;, Mogadish can present even a high-level party with quite a challenge.\nGameplay.\nUpon initiation of hostilities (usually because Mogadish has been attacked or detects a party member), the cleric has a scripted array of protective buffs that are forced-cast as a group of applied spells (can't be interrupted) including a &lt;a href=\"Regeneration%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Regeneration (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Defensive%20Harmony\"&gt;Defensive Harmony&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;.\nFrom then on. the response to local conditions will vary depending on what the cleric can detect and certain threats. If the party sends forward any skeletons or undead summpns the priest will attempt a &lt;a href=\"Sunray\"&gt;Sunray&lt;/a&gt;. The first nearest enemy/party member will be targeted with a &lt;a href=\"Confusion%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Confusion (priest)&lt;/a&gt; spell cast.\nFurther into the battle the Priest may attempt a &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt; on self or other halflings that are &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt;, and offensively may try &lt;a href=\"Symbol%2C%20Fear%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Symbol, Fear (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Strike\"&gt;Flame Strike&lt;/a&gt; and others. If allied halflings are injured to a certain level will attempt &lt;a href=\"Mass%20Cure\"&gt;Mass Cure&lt;/a&gt;. The list of memorized spells in the InfoBox are not the only spells available, and the quantity of spells memorized in most cases is factual, but not all inclusive as the script determines what spells are cast. \nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises this creature with a new default AI script, and especially with the \"Smarter Priest\" component installed. An entire reworked spell book is memorized, and spell choices are changed as well. \nMogadish will open up with a group of (previously cast) protective buffs including: &lt;a href=\"Regeneration%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Regeneration (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Resistance%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Magic Resistance (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Fire%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Protection From Fire (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Mirror\"&gt;Physical Mirror&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;.\nImmediately afterwards an &lt;a href=\"Aerial%20Servant\"&gt;Aerial Servant&lt;/a&gt; will be cast for support.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod installed the cleric's spells will be the SR versions."}
{"id": "51879", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51879", "title": "Mohad Flintborn", "text": "Mohad Flintborn is a &lt;a href=\"dwarf\"&gt;dwarf&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Berserker\"&gt;Berserker&lt;/a&gt; residing in the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Wyrms\"&gt;Forest of Wyrms&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; can meet him in the &lt;a href=\"ruined%20Temple%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;ruined Temple of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign.\nInvolvement.\nMohad Flintborn is one of the people guarding the &lt;a href=\"mind%20flayer\"&gt;mind flayer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Darskhelin\"&gt;Darskhelin&lt;/a&gt; in the Reliquary room, together with &lt;a href=\"Jhan%20Redmoons\"&gt;Jhan Redmoons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Teth%20Se-Nehi\"&gt;Teth Se-Nehi&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Shallen\"&gt;Shallen&lt;/a&gt; (plus &lt;a href=\"Umber%20Hulk\"&gt;Umber Hulk&lt;/a&gt;s in higher difficulties).\nGameplay.\nLike his other companions, he is hostile from the very beginning and will attack any &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; member he notices. This opponent uses only his battle axe, inflicting 10-17 &lt;a href=\"slashing%20damage\"&gt;slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; when he is not &lt;a href=\"enrage\"&gt;enrage&lt;/a&gt;d, at a rate of five attacks per two rounds. During the fight he will use this special ability though, and he will also drink the &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Power\"&gt;Potion of Power&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Extra%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Extra Healing&lt;/a&gt; he has when needed. He is the \"tankiest\" among this group of enemies, and his helmet protects him from critical hits.\nQuests.\nThis group isn't necessary to be confronted in order to proceed with the main story, but dealing with the mind flayer who has invaded the temple with his company is required in order for &lt;a href=\"The%20Eyeless%20Priestess\"&gt;The Eyeless Priestess&lt;/a&gt; quest to be completed, giving more clues about the temple's current state and extra dialogue options with &lt;a href=\"Madele\"&gt;Madele&lt;/a&gt;, unless she has already been freed. Also, defeating Darskhelin and his company provides the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; with the opportunity to loot some notable &lt;a href=\"magical%20items\"&gt;magical items&lt;/a&gt;, and with the option to get the &lt;a href=\"Wardstone%20%28Siege%20of%20Dragonspear%29\"&gt;wardstone&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Cyric\"&gt;Cyric&lt;/a&gt;'s High Priestess &lt;a href=\"Akanna\"&gt;Akanna&lt;/a&gt; without a fight, if they haven't dealt with her already in another way and are still able to speak with her."}
{"id": "7021", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7021", "title": "Molkar", "text": "Molkar is the leader of a group of assassins that attack &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party in &lt;a href=\"Gullykin\"&gt;Gullykin&lt;/a&gt;. They are found far from the village, in the south of the area (&lt;a href=\"Coordinates\"&gt;3636.3631&lt;/a&gt;). The others in his party are &lt;a href=\"Morvin\"&gt;Morvin&lt;/a&gt; (warrior), &lt;a href=\"Drakar\"&gt;Drakar&lt;/a&gt; (priest) and &lt;a href=\"Halacan\"&gt;Halacan&lt;/a&gt; (wizard). They are worth a total of 3,700 XP, and their most notable loot is:\nDialogue.\nAs usual, the lead assassin introduces himself and you get three dialogue options, none of which affect the outcome in the least.\n\"So, we finally meet. Poor little &lt;Gorion's Ward&gt;, I assume you're completely clueless as to why you must die. I'm sure you've already had problems with an assortment of incompetent bounty hunters. Well, those days are done. Today, you will die.\""}
{"id": "42712", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42712", "title": "Molzahn of Tymora", "text": "Molzahn is one of the clerics residing in the House of Worship, part of the staging area in &lt;a href=\"Dennaton\"&gt;Dennaton&lt;/a&gt;'s mansion. He's the only one providing temple services and sells a few scrolls. A slightly different version is also available in &lt;a href=\"Destroying%20the%20Order%20of%20Eight%20Staves\"&gt;Neera's visit to the mansion&lt;/a&gt;.\nBuy and Sell.\nThe shop ignores reputation in Black Pits II only. Cheapest prices are about 67% higher than the values displayed below because of this.\nNeera's version.\nThe version encountered in Neera's companion quest is killable and lost all his smart fighting scripts. Now he has the standard \"Attack my nearest enemy\" philosophy, but being a level 14 cleric with no spell script and weak armor, he poses no threat.\nHis curing services are identical to the Gladiators of Thay counterpart, including some of the inflated prices. His stock differs slightly in the number of items available, but the same items are offered."}
