{"id": "2205", "revid": "281373", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2205", "title": "Montaron", "text": "Montaron is a neutral evil halfling &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Multi-class\"&gt;multi-class&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Fighter%20/%20Thief\"&gt;Fighter / Thief&lt;/a&gt; and a potential &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt; in .\nBackground.\nMontaron and his companion &lt;a href=\"Xzar\"&gt;Xzar&lt;/a&gt; are Zhentarim sent to the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt; to investigate the causes of the recent &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Crisis\"&gt;Iron Crisis&lt;/a&gt;. As the plot evolves, it becomes clear that &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne\"&gt;someone's&lt;/a&gt; trying to frame the Zhentarim for the events occurring around &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;the city of Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt;. Since the Zhentarim are not particularly benevolent and have a fearsome reputation, the duo prefers to work undercover, pretending to be mere adventurers.\n&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; &amp;.\nRecruitment.\nMontaron is available during &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20One\"&gt;Chapter One&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Two\"&gt;Two&lt;/a&gt;, travel to the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Coastway\"&gt;Candlekeep Coastway&lt;/a&gt;. You will find him with &lt;a href=\"Xzar\"&gt;Xzar&lt;/a&gt; along the path on the eastern side of the area (&lt;a href=\"Coordinates\"&gt;4515.2705&lt;/a&gt;). Invite them to join, then agree to travel with them to &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt;.\nMontaron has to pair with Xzar.\n\nMontaron does not appear in Shadows of Amn, but Xzar wants you to search in the Harper Headquarter in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Athkatla Docks&lt;/a&gt; for him during a &lt;a href=\"Find%20out%20What%20Happened%20to%20Montaron\"&gt;side-quest&lt;/a&gt;. You will soon find out that he has been polymorphed into a bird, which you give to Xzar, but when the bird is transformed in human form, you find out this is a trick, as the bird was not Montaron, but an assassin of the &lt;a href=\"Harpers\"&gt;Harpers&lt;/a&gt; who kills Xzar. You can find Montaron's body in a chest in Harper Headquarters when visiting the building later.\nPersonality.\nMontaron is a very psychotic and aggressive character, threatening all his companions with bodily harm. He is also very reserved and secretive, using the usual threats to discourage nosing around.\nDespite travelling with Xzar, Montaron despises the Necromancer and will express relief over his eventual demise. He also holds no respect to anyone in his party, looking at potential companions as \"pack-mules\" and potential victims rather than peers."}
