{"id": "4700", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4700", "title": "Heal", "text": "The Heal spell enables the priest to completely cure all disease and/or injuries afflicting the target creature.\nEffects and states cured are &lt;a href=\"Intoxicated\"&gt;Intoxicated&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Blindness\"&gt;Blindness&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Feeblemindedness\"&gt;Feeblemindedness&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Disease\"&gt;Disease&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Deafness%20effect\"&gt;Deafness&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this Divine spell, revising its casting time, effects, and description. See below:\nHeal\nLevel: 6\nSchool: Necromancy\nSphere: Healing\nRange: Touch\nDuration: Instant\nCasting Time: 6\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nThe very potent Heal spell enables the priest to wipe away any injury in the creature who receives its benefits. It completely cures the recipient of all diseases, poisons, and conditions such as blindness and deafness. It heals all points of damage suffered due to wounds or injury and dispels a Feeblemind spell. Naturally, the effects can be negated by later wounds, injuries, and diseases."}
{"id": "55939", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55939", "title": "Healing Lick (SPIN699)", "text": "Healing Lick (SPIN699) is an innate ability available to &lt;a href=\"Cerebus\"&gt;Cerebus&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Aranthis\"&gt;Aranthis&lt;/a&gt;. The ability is initiated via script by the AI, or by player activation if it is from the Moon Dog. \nEffects.\nThe effect is directed at one creature only. The spell range is only one foot. \nThe ability is cast as normal or by other means by script (such as \"ApplySpell\", \"ForceCast\" or \"ReallyForceCast\"). \nThe targeted creature of the Healing Lick is healed for 20 hit points.\n&lt;a href=\"Disease\"&gt;Disease&lt;/a&gt; effects are cured.\n&lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; effects are cured.\n&lt;a href=\"Deafness%20effect\"&gt;Deafness effect&lt;/a&gt; is cured.\n&lt;a href=\"Blindness\"&gt;Blindness&lt;/a&gt; is cured."}
{"id": "30119", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30119", "title": "Heart Key", "text": "The Heart Key is the reward from the &lt;a href=\"Helmite%20Ghost\"&gt;Helmite Ghost&lt;/a&gt; after you visit the three challenge rooms, and successfully resolve each. \nThis key, as well as the &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Key\"&gt;Spirit Key&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Key\"&gt;Mind Key&lt;/a&gt; are needed to unbar the wheel device, which can then be turned to open the final seal, leading to a portal to the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Imprisoned%20One\"&gt;Lower reaches&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nOnce this key is obtained, it may be used to open one of the pedestal locks adjacent to the final seal in the center of this dungeon level.\nThere is no requirement to have all three keys in order to utilize a key and unlock the matching pedestal. The choice is up to the party. \nUsing the key with the cursor results in a text display, reading:\nWhen the key is turned, each party member receives quest points, as well as an instant appearance of the guardians.\nSee the gallery screenshot."}
{"id": "56606", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56606", "title": "Heart key pedestal", "text": "The \"Heart key pedestal\"' is a \"clickable\" map feature located adjacent to the Final Seal in the center of the main dungeon area.\nIt can be interacted with using the player's cursor to generate certain actions necessary to advance the &lt;a href=\"Unlocking%20the%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Unlocking the Final Seal&lt;/a&gt; questline.\nThe Heart key pedestal is positioned on the western side of the Final Seal, although it isn't labelled or identified in any way.\nGameplay.\nThe pedestal can only be unlocked if the party is in possession of the &lt;a href=\"Heart%20Key\"&gt;Heart Key&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf a party member clicks on the pedestal and doesn't have the correct key, then a text displays in the dialogue box reading:\nIf the party has lost track and already unlocked the pedestal and clicks on it, a message displays:\nIf the Heart Key is possessed by the party, then a different text is displayed:\nClicking again initiates an award of to each party member, and the spawning of the guardians on the area map. \nThe guardians are hostile and ready to initiate action almost immediately.\nThey are positioned in various spots around the Final Seal.\nThe guardians spawned by unlocking the Heart key pedestal are listed below - read more about each individual guardian on their article page, for stats, abilities and other details.\nGuardians.\nNote that several of these creatures carry treasure/loot which is dropped when they are defeated. \nSome of these items can be destroyed if the player has the \"Gore\" option enabled and kills a creature in certain ways, such as with the &lt;a href=\"Disintegrate%20effect\"&gt;Disintegrate effect&lt;/a&gt; and a few other methods."}
