{"id": "50978", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50978", "title": "Heart of the Wood", "text": "Heart of the Wood A mod hosted by Spellhold Studios for Baldur's Gate II, Throne of Bhaal (classical and EE games), Baldur's Gate Trilogy and EET\nOverview.\nThis mod adds a magic druidic wand that summons some powerful forest monsters and creatures (with some new ones from the monsters compendium) to aid your druid in combat, although the overall HD of the summoned creatures is limited to 13. This item can be acquired from &lt;a href=\"Kyland%20Lind\"&gt;Kyland Lind&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Druid%20Grove\"&gt;Druid Grove&lt;/a&gt;. You must kill him first for it of course.\n\u26a0\ufe0f Kyland Lind will use the branch against your party!\nNote: Only druids can use it!\nCompatibility.\nThis mod is designed to work on the following Infinity Engine games: the original Baldur's Gate II (BG2 or just SoA) with the Throne of Bhaal (ToB) expansion, Baldur's Gate II: Enhanced Edition (BG2:EE), the conversion projects Baldur's Gate Trilogy (BGT) and Enhanced Edition Trilogy (EET).\nThis is a WeiDU mod, and therefore should be compatible with all WeiDU mods. If you encounter any bugs, please report them on the forum!\nAlthough it is not required for the Heart of the Wood mod to function properly, classical game players are strongly recommended to download and install the latest version of the BG2 Fixpack before proceeding with the installation of this mod.\nComponents.\nThe installer includes one single component, the main component.\nFor more information see the links."}
{"id": "5880", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5880", "title": "Heartseeker", "text": "Heartseeker is an enchanted composite longbow +3. It has a +4 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus and it has +2 bonus to damage. The bow weighs 7 lbs. and has a speed factor of 4. The charge ability of this bow is that THAC0 can be improved by 7 points for nine seconds, in which three arrows can be shot from this bow.\nNote that the Heartseeker's special ability simply applies a missile-only THAC0 bonus to the user, meaning it need not be used with this weapon specifically. Therefore, you can, for example, keep it in a secondary weapon slot to use its ability while wielding the Boomerang Dagger (or another throwing weapon that does missile damage) instead or you can switch out the bow for another bow after using the ability (because the game doesn't allow you to put two bows in weapon slots)."}
