{"id": "2867", "revid": "268584", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2867", "title": "Heavy Crossbow", "text": "A is a mounted crosswise on a wooden or metal shaft, the latter called a tiller. The bow is usually made of ash or yew. The crossbow fires a quarrel (also called a &lt;a href=\"bolt\"&gt;bolt&lt;/a&gt;).\nThe Heavy Crossbow is a two-handed, ranged weapon and a weapon type in all of the \"Baldur's Gate\" series.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Heavy Crossbow is a heavier, larger and more intricately to handle variant of . Due to its size and the long time it needs to be readied to fire, &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;Thieves&lt;/a&gt; don't use this and refer to instead. &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Class%20group\"&gt;Warriors&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bard\"&gt;Bard&lt;/a&gt;s with a sufficient &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; of twelve, may use this weapon.\nThe usual weight of 14 lb requires a Strength of 12 to be able to use the crossbow. As , crossbows also need two hands for the handling. Heavy Crossbows need double the time to be readied to fire as their lighter kin, and are the slowest ranged weapon to be found on the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt; and in &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt;: they come with a speed factor of 10. In addition, they never have more than one attack per round, due to the complicated process of reloading.\nWeight and speed are their disadvantages, compared to Light Crossbows, but these also bring an advantage: deal the highest base damage of all ranged weapons, adding a +2 damage bonus to every fired from them.\nEnchanted and unique variants may differ from these characteristics."}
{"id": "5792", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5792", "title": "Heavy Crossbow +1", "text": "Heavy Crossbow +1 is an enchanted weapon. It has a +1 bonus to THAC0\u00a0and damage and the speed factor is one lower when compared to a normal &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Crossbow\"&gt;heavy crossbow&lt;/a&gt;. With a weight of 12 lbs, it's also 2 lbs lighter. You can't harm enemies immune to normal weapon if you are using non-enchanted &lt;a href=\"bolt\"&gt;bolt&lt;/a&gt;s, the bolts determine that. This item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, and and it will also appear in .\nIn the original Baldur's Gate it can only be gained through the console as it's not for sale at any store. Only in this game it's in the Missile weapon proficiency. In the other games, it's in Crossbows proficiency."}
{"id": "5822", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5822", "title": "Heavy Crossbow +2", "text": "The Heavy Crossbow +2 is an enchanted &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Crossbow\"&gt;heavy crossbow&lt;/a&gt;. It has +2 bonus to &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;, damage and speed factor. It is 3 lbs. lighter than a non-enchanted heavy crossbow."}
