{"id": "7490", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7490", "title": "Helm", "text": "Helm, also known as the Watcher or the\u00a0Vigilant One, is a &lt;a href=\"lawful%20neutral\"&gt;lawful neutral&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0intermediate\u00a0&lt;a href=\"deity\"&gt;deity&lt;/a&gt; of guardians, protectors and protection.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Time%20of%20Troubles\"&gt;Time of Troubles&lt;/a&gt; Helm was the only god to not be cast down on &lt;a href=\"Toril\"&gt;Toril&lt;/a&gt;. Instead Lord &lt;a href=\"Ao\"&gt;Ao&lt;/a&gt; entrusted him with keeping the other gods from returning to their divine realms before having found the &lt;a href=\"Tablets%20of%20Fate\"&gt;Tablets of Fate&lt;/a&gt;. When the goddess of magic &lt;a href=\"Mystra\"&gt;Mystra&lt;/a&gt; tried to return, Helm slew her. She was reincarnated shortly after in the body of the then-mortal mage Midnight, but Helm came to be disliked by mortal races for his actions.\u00a0\nThe &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt; was built in his name."}
