{"id": "3435", "revid": "78773", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3435", "title": "Helm and Cloak", "text": "The Helm and Cloak inn can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Northwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;northwest&lt;/a&gt; district of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, on the southeast part of the area. &lt;a href=\"Degrodel%27s%20Home\"&gt;Degrodel's Home&lt;/a&gt; is to the west, &lt;a href=\"Quinn%27s%20Home\"&gt;Quinn's Home&lt;/a&gt; is to the northeast, and &lt;a href=\"Laerta%20and%20Louise%27s%20Home\"&gt;Laerta and Louise's Home&lt;/a&gt; is located directly north above the inn.\nIt's a luxurious inn that provides drink and beds for their patrons. The name originates from the fact that the &lt;a href=\"Helm%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;Helm of Balduran&lt;/a&gt; is hidden somewhere in the inn. The &lt;a href=\"Band%20of%20Merry%20Fools\"&gt;Band of Merry Fools&lt;/a&gt; can be found inside. After talking to them, the group called the &lt;a href=\"Maulers%20of%20Undermountain\"&gt;Maulers of Undermountain&lt;/a&gt; moves in and will attack the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt;, after demanding they clear the way (this will happen regardless of which conversation response the player chooses.)\nThe locked chest in the kitchen contains , a &lt;a href=\"Black%20Opal\"&gt;Black Opal&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Garnet%20Gem\"&gt;Garnet Gem&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere is a \"special guest\" in the rooms upstairs (front steps), being guarded by two guards that block the way and will not let you past. If the player kills the guards, or gets past by some other means, the guest turns out to be &lt;a href=\"Sarah\"&gt;Sarah&lt;/a&gt;, an emissary from Amn sent to ease tensions between Amn and Baldur's Gate. There is a locked chest in the room which contains and an &lt;a href=\"Angel%20Skin%20Ring\"&gt;Angel Skin Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe back set of stairs leads to an office/apartment for the owner, where the Helm of Balduran is hidden behind a painting, in a trapped and locked wall safe.\nServices.\nThe party can either rest here or have some drinks (ranging from to ) and hear some gossip, rumors and news. All four qualities of rooms can be rented.\nTrivia.\nThe name of the tavern, Helm and Cloak, alludes to two of &lt;a href=\"Balduran\"&gt;Balduran&lt;/a&gt;'s relics - his &lt;a href=\"Helm%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;helm&lt;/a&gt; and his &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;cloak&lt;/a&gt;. Fittingly, the helm is hidden inside the building."}
{"id": "2157", "revid": "51290140", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2157", "title": "Helm of Balduran", "text": "Helm of Balduran is a powerful relic that once belonged to the famous explorer and founder of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Balduran\"&gt;Balduran&lt;/a&gt;. It is one of the most sought after pieces of headgear in the game. Aside from offering protection from critical hits, it also provides a -1 bonus to armor class, lowers THAC0 by 1, increases the hit points of the wearer by five points, and gives the wearer a -1 bonus for all saving throws. \nIn classic , it's the only helm besides the &lt;a href=\"Helm%20of%20the%20Noble\"&gt;Helm of the Noble&lt;/a&gt; that boosts AC.\nAchievements.\nIn Balduran's Image.\nDon the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20of%20Balduran%20%28BG2%29\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;, helm, and &lt;a href=\"Plate%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;plate&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Balduran\"&gt;Balduran&lt;/a&gt;."}
