{"id": "6277", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6277", "title": "Helm of the Rock", "text": "Helm of the Rock is a magical item which grants the wearer, who must be a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt;, 25% resistance to fire, cold, electricity, acid and poison, as well as the standard protection from critical hits. The helmet has a weight of 2 lbs. This item appears in and . \nAquisition.\nThe helm can be found as loot from a creature within the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt;, where the &lt;a href=\"horn\"&gt;horn&lt;/a&gt; items can also be found, which are required to upgrade the helm. The Helm is worn by the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Giant%20%28Guardian%20of%20Fire%29\"&gt;Fire Giant (Guardian of Fire)&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgraded Helm.\nWith all the two &lt;a href=\"Horn\"&gt;Horn&lt;/a&gt; items collected, &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt; can craft and upgrade the basic helm to an upgraded version (for a fee of 5,000 gold). \nWhen the horns are added to the helmet, it can be used thrice per day to cast \"Aura of Command\", a spell effect which forces any single target creature to make a save vs spells at -2 penalty or flee in terror. \nThis effect uses a sparkle projectile and applies a &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; effect with a duration of 5 rounds. If the target fails a saving throw, a lighting effect and a color fade visual effect plays over the target's sprite, and the combat screen log displays a text string reading \"Morale Failure\".\nThe spell effect has no assigned spell school or secondary type and is considered non-magical. It can't be blocked by spell protections or magic resistance, and the effect can target creatures with &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; immunities, such as a &lt;a href=\"Rakshasa\"&gt;Rakshasa&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe effect can't be removed by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects."}
