{"id": "56414", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56414", "title": "Helmite Ghost", "text": "The Helmite Ghost is encountered during or .\nHe can be found on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Final Seal&lt;/a&gt; dungeon level, which is part of the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt; adventure.\nThis creature is essential to the Watcher's Keep plot and necessary to advance the &lt;a href=\"Unlocking%20the%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Unlocking the Final Seal&lt;/a&gt; questline.\nThe creature can't be harmed under normal gameplay conditions and will never turn hostile. If somehow the creature is destroyed (through cheats/exploits, console commands etc.), the player's storyline will be shuttered, and the plot broken.\nThere are a total of four different creature files named \"Helmite Ghost\" used to deliver dialogue and animation in different sections/locations of the adventure. \nGameplay.\nWhen the party decides to move towards the southern section of the area map, you'll observe a set of closed metallic door gates. \nOpen the double doored gate, and the Helmite Ghost will initiate dialogue with the party, appearing as a wispy and translucent \"air elemental\". The ghost will be able to do this even if the party is hidden/invisible.\nThe party is allowed to reply or ask questions after the initial greeting from the ghost, who will then address those words.\nIf the party asks about the Imprisoned One, the ghost replies:\nIf the party says, \"That sounds rather ominous\", the ghost retorts:\nIf the party threatens the ghost, it will say:\nIf the party states \"I am prepared for whatever lies ahead\", the ghost says:\nAt this time the player's Journal registers a quest, stating:\nThe ghost continues:\nThe party must open and enter through each gate behind the ghost when they are ready to do. They may be entered in whichever order is desired. Once the party enters, they may not return until the challenge is resolved. \nAfter a challenge room is finished, the party may speak with the Helmite Ghost, (but it isn't required until all three are completed). It may say:\nWhen all three challenge rooms are finished, the ghost concludes the challenges by saying:\nThe party will receive the &lt;a href=\"Heart%20Key\"&gt;Heart Key&lt;/a&gt; and another journal entry is registered:\nThe challenge rooms.\nThe three gates stand before the party. In terms of which gate to choose, that is up to the player, but there aren't any indications given as to what lies ahead when transitioning through any of them. \nIf the player wishes to read ahead, which is obviously a spoiler, then below are links to those challenges:\nNotes.\nThe party will probably encounter the Helmite Ghost in each challenge room after the particular challenge is resolved successfully - quest experience points are awarded for each challenge that is completed, as well as an additional when the Heart Key is bestowed."}
