{"id": "22664", "revid": "284134", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22664", "title": "Help Korgan Recover the Book of Kaza", "text": " Don't tarry too long before completing this quest lest Korgan leaves.\nThis is &lt;a href=\"Korgan%20Bloodaxe\"&gt;Korgan&lt;/a&gt;'s companion quest in \"Shadows of Amn\" campaign.\nAquisition.\nInitiate dialogue with the dwarf in\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt; near &lt;a href=\"Surly\"&gt;Surly&lt;/a&gt; and listen to his tale. Questions can be asked, for further information. Paraphrased below is some of what Korgan tells of this proposed enterprise:\nIf the party asks where this tome is and agrees to help Korgan hunt for this tome, he'll say:\nWhen departing the Copper coronet, the player's Journal should update:\nWalkthrough.\nDespite Korgan's enthusiasm to immediately go to the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Athkatla Graveyard&lt;/a&gt; and enter one of the &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;Lower Tombs&lt;/a&gt;, it may prove better to first visit this &lt;a href=\"Pimlico\"&gt;Pimlico&lt;/a&gt; book collector that has offered a reward to find this rare tome. Is the reward still offered? What additional information might Pimlico have to help find it? And what about the bloodbath and vile words that Korgan referred to? \nBecause of the way this quest will unfold, the party only has one chance to speak with this Pimlico fellow before that opportunity will be shuttered later. It is up to the player if that opportunity will be taken. Of course, Pimlico can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Pimlico%20Estate\"&gt;Pimlico Estate&lt;/a&gt;.\nRegardless of whether the party visits Pimlico, &lt;a href=\"The%20Book%20of%20Kaza\"&gt;The Book of Kaza&lt;/a&gt; is the actual tome sought. Korgan believes it to be somewhere in an area beneath &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; Graveyard. For details on navigating that area, and what creatures to expect, see the page for &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;The Lower Tombs&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce in the Lower Tombs, check for traps and containers to loot for a &lt;a href=\"Mislead\"&gt;Mislead&lt;/a&gt; spell scroll and &lt;a href=\"Wooden%20Stake\"&gt;Wooden Stakes&lt;/a&gt;. The center of the area is dominated by a central structure called &lt;a href=\"Pai%27Na\"&gt;Pai'Na's Lair&lt;/a&gt;. To south is the entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Southern%20Dungeons\"&gt;crypt&lt;/a&gt; the party seeks. For a more detailed walkthrough, see the page for the &lt;a href=\"Southern%20Dungeons\"&gt;Southern Dungeons&lt;/a&gt;.\nWithin the Southern Dungeon, proceed to the southernmost room, and Korgan will notice that the tomb has already been looted, granting 11,250 XP shared by the party. If Korgan is within sight of the Mummy, there will be an exchange of dialogue between he and the animated undead creature. After clearing out the undead, you will want to hurry back to the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt; and to the home of the Book Collector. The player's Journal will update:\nGo to &lt;a href=\"Pimlico%20Estate\"&gt;Pimlico Estate&lt;/a&gt; (just past the Temple of Lathander). As you approach, Korgan tells you that the place has been looted.\u00a0Go inside, take Korgan into the bedroom and the murdered corpses of Pimlico and the two guards are seen. He'll mention that this looks like the work of &lt;a href=\"Shagbag\"&gt;Shagbag&lt;/a&gt;, who can probably be found on the roof of the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt; (8,750 exp shared by the party). Onward to the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Slums&lt;/a&gt;! The player's Journal will update:\nThe stairs that lead to the roof are at (x 1530 y 2815), you'll find Shagbag and his party (5,000 exp). As soon as Korgan is in sight range of Shagbag and band of goons a terse and insult filled exchange of dialogue will occur, leading to an inevitable fight. If you defeat them, search Shagbag's corpse to find &lt;a href=\"The%20Book%20of%20Kaza\"&gt;The Book of Kaza&lt;/a&gt; which can then be sold for a tidy sum of gold.\nAchievements.\nThe Book of Kaza.\nTrack down the Book of Kaza for &lt;a href=\"Korgan\"&gt;Korgan&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"BuTcHeRy\"&gt;BuTcHeRy&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some changes to Shagbag and his goons. It provides some arms and armor commensurate with a band of adventuring tomb raiders with some experience under their belt. These changes will slightly increase their melee attack and defense ability, and lead to some moderately improved loot compared to the vanilla game.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod alters all the creatures in the Southern Dungeons and Lower Tombs, as well as Shagbag's band of adventuring group. Most of these changes relate to improving the creatures AI, and especially for spell casters. Weapon proficiencies are corrected and added as needed. This will be a noticeable change from the vanilla game. This mod works with the &lt;a href=\"BuTcHeRy\"&gt;BuTcHeRy&lt;/a&gt; mod mentioned above as well with no conflicts."}
{"id": "28304", "revid": "282659", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28304", "title": "Help Viekang", "text": "Help Viekang is an unmarked side quest in &lt;a href=\"Saradush\"&gt;Saradush&lt;/a&gt;.\nStarting the Quest.\nTalk to &lt;a href=\"Viekang\"&gt;Viekang&lt;/a&gt; in the tavern, and ask him how you can help him regain his teleportation power. You need 18 &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; to begin the quest. But you dont need 18 &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; to cast panic for him and finish the quest.\nFinishing the Quest.\nCast any spell that causes fear or panic (e.g., Spook) &lt;a href=\"Horror\"&gt;Horror&lt;/a&gt; or other hostile only spells will work too. Viekang will flee and teleport accordingly. All party members receive 2000 XP."}
{"id": "48303", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48303", "title": "Helpful Man", "text": "The Helpful Man is an unnamed individual who is found in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Docks District&lt;/a&gt; within the city of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;. He will approach the first member of the party that enters his line of sight and offer a friendly word or two in regards to the guild war between the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Vampires&lt;/a&gt;. When the conversation is over he'll leave and disappear.\nDialogue.\n\"Hello there, friend. Sorry if I disturbed your chain of thought, but you looked new to the city, and I wondered if I might lend you a hand?\"\n\"I didn't mean anything bad by that. You just don't have the look of one of the locals. Shows in the way you wear your tunic, or maybe how you stand.\"\n\"Just thought I'd offer a friendly word or two before you experienced otherwise. This place can treat newcomers quite rude sometimes.\"\n\"Oh, not much. I don't claim to be an authority or anything. Just like meeting new people. I say one thing though, I don't go out much at night.\"\n\"We've got this thieves' guild, see? They ain't so bad, but there's another guild that's fighting them. I've seen people get caught in the middle, and it isn't pretty.\"\n\"Mostly only happens at night though, and the city is so much more impressive during the day anyway.\"\n\"Nope. Have a good stay in Athkatla. Safe travels, friend.\""}
