{"id": "9699", "revid": "51239487", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9699", "title": "Helping Irenicus's captive dryads", "text": "Helping Irenicus' Captive Dryads is a side quest in .\nWalkthrough.\nFree the Dryads from Captivity.\nThis concludes the Helping Irenicus' Captive Dryads quest.\nMod content.\nPeople involved.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Quest%20Pack\"&gt;Quest Pack&lt;/a&gt; Mod and the \"New Fate for the Dryad's Acorns\" component adds a twist to the quest to return Irenicus' dryads' acorns to the Windspear Hills. Players may find some optional content in the new opportunities afforded here including an evil solution to the quest. The quest begins with a new encounter which will take place in the south of the De'Arnise Hold if you have not already returned the acorns."}
{"id": "5954", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5954", "title": "Helping Tiris in Trademeet", "text": "Helping Tiris in Trademeet is a &lt;a href=\"side%20quest\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt;. It can be started if the quests &lt;a href=\"Animal%20trouble%20in%20Trademeet\"&gt;Animal trouble in Trademeet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dealing%20with%20the%20Trademeet%20genies\"&gt;Dealing with the Trademeet genies&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Solve%20the%20%22skinner%22%20murders%20in%20the%20Bridge%20District\"&gt;Solve the \"skinner\" murders in the Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; have been completed. &lt;a href=\"Jenia\"&gt;Jenia&lt;/a&gt; will approach your party and ask you to help her son &lt;a href=\"Tiris\"&gt;Tiris&lt;/a&gt;.\nGo to Tiris' home in the north-west part of town and speak to Tiris. He will tell you that he and his girlfriend Raissa were attacked by a skinless man and by &lt;a href=\"Rejiek\"&gt;Rejiek&lt;/a&gt;, the murderer you drove out of the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Bridge\"&gt;Athkatla Bridge&lt;/a&gt; District. He will also tell you that they still have &lt;a href=\"Raissa\"&gt;Raissa&lt;/a&gt;.\nGo to the south-west gate where you will meet a man named &lt;a href=\"Darsidian%20Moor\"&gt;Darsidian Moor&lt;/a&gt; who is hunting the skinless creature. He will invite you to join in attacking them on the east side of town.\nGo to the walled area where you will meet Darsidian again. The east gate referred to in the journal is the southern east gate near the big circle mosaic. Darsidian will be just northeast of the mosaic. He will tell you to quickly kill Rejiek before he regains consciousness.\nDeal With The Trap.\nSee Through The Trap.\nTalk to Rejiek, who thinks you are Tiris. You realize that \"Rejiek\" is actually Raissa (wearing Rejiek's skin) and \"Raissa\" is actually Rejiek (wearing Raissa's skin). Darsidian Moor is revealed to be Rejiek's accomplice. They attack. Alternatively, you can also see through the trap by using the &lt;a href=\"Detect%20Evil\"&gt;Detect Evil&lt;/a&gt; spell and then attack the imposters first, which will lead to the same outcome.\nRaissa removes Rejiek's skin and puts hers back on. Rejiek turned her into a Skin Dancer and asks your party to cast &lt;a href=\"Lesser%20Restoration\"&gt;Lesser Restoration&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Restoration\"&gt;Greater Restoration&lt;/a&gt; on her to cure her. If you are in need of a scroll, you can buy one at the temple of Waukeen in Trademeet.\nFall For The Trap.\nKill Rejiek. Darsidian Moor and Raissa thank you. He says that he is going to walk her home.\nTiris' Home.\nGo to Tiris' Home."}
{"id": "24911", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24911", "title": "Helpless", "text": "Helpless is a state applied to creatures victim of certain &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;status effects&lt;/a&gt;. It is often mentioned in game descriptions.\nAny physical attack against a \"Helpless\" defender will not be required to go through an attack roll in order to land a blow: The to-hit calculation is bypassed and the defender's &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; ignored. Physical attacks therefore always result in a normal hit \u2014 without an attack roll, &lt;a href=\"Critical%20hit\"&gt;Critical hit&lt;/a&gt;s and misses are impossible. \nDefences other than Armor Class and penalties to attacker &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; do still apply, such as &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Damage%23Resistance\"&gt;damage resistance&lt;/a&gt;, etc.\nThe following status effects are able to cause the \"Helpless\" state:\nCreatures affected by &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt; suffer the same consequences as \"Helpless\", but they don't actually get the state proper.\nSimilarly, a weapon with a natural THAC0 bonus of 32,767 bypasses attack rolls as if the defender were Helpless, even though they are not \u2014 it cannot critical hit, cannot miss, but can still bump into defences other than Armor Class. &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20of%20Detonation\"&gt;Arrows of Detonation&lt;/a&gt; have such a THAC0."}
{"id": "8701", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8701", "title": "Helshara", "text": "Helshara is one of three daughters of the &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Shandalar\"&gt;Shandalar&lt;/a&gt;. She is found on the third floor of &lt;a href=\"Oberan%27s%20Estate\"&gt;Oberan's Estate&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Central%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Central&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, along with her sisters, &lt;a href=\"Delorna\"&gt;Delorna&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ithmeera\"&gt;Ithmeera&lt;/a&gt;. They are guarding a special set of spell components needed to create &lt;a href=\"Halruaa\"&gt;Halruaan&lt;/a&gt; skyships.\nSide quests.\n&lt;a href=\"Alatos%20and%20the%20Thieves%27%20Guild\"&gt;Alatos and the Thieves' Guild&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Alatos\"&gt;Alatos&lt;/a&gt;, the leader of the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Guild\"&gt;Thieves' Guild&lt;/a&gt;, has been contacted by the Halruaan &lt;a href=\"Mage%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Resar\"&gt;Resar&lt;/a&gt;, who wants the former to arrange the theft of three artifacts used to create skyships. The Halruann's do not wish to see the secret of their creation spread beyond the borders of Halruaa, and Alatos has concluded that &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party would be the best choice for the job.\nObtaining the components.\nIf you attempt the direct route, she will immediately initiate dialogue upon sight with the party, which then begins a brief back and forth conversation with her and Ithmeera. All three dialogue routes lead to hostilities. Should harm come to the three daughters, Shandalar will be none to pleased, and you just might end up on a &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Island\"&gt;spit of rock&lt;/a&gt; you're not prepared to visit quite yet.\nIf you attempt to &lt;a href=\"Charmed\"&gt;charm&lt;/a&gt; any of the three daughters, they all give the same reply:"}
