{"id": "38233", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38233", "title": "Helvdar", "text": "Helvdar is a male dwarf warrior who was part of the coalition forces against the Shining Crusade of &lt;a href=\"Caelar%20Argent\"&gt;Caelar Argent&lt;/a&gt;. He is superstitious, an incorrigible gambler, and something of a drunkard.\nEncountering.\nHelvdar can be found at the northern entrance of the &lt;a href=\"Coalition%20Camp\"&gt;Coalition Camp&lt;/a&gt; in Chapter 10.\nQuests.\nHelvdar gives out the quest &lt;a href=\"Helvdar%27s%20Lucky%20Charm\"&gt;Helvdar's Lucky Charm&lt;/a&gt; and is involved in the quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Traitor\"&gt;The Traitor&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "39142", "revid": "283208", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39142", "title": "Helvdar's Lucky Charm", "text": "Helvdar's Lucky Charm is a side quest in .\nAcquisition.\nIf you speak to &lt;a href=\"Helvdar\"&gt;Helvdar&lt;/a&gt; in the Coalition Camp, he will ask you to commission him some new boots to bring him good luck, in order to replace the lucky pebble that he lost. He feels that that the &lt;a href=\"Fine%20Bearskin\"&gt;pelt&lt;/a&gt; of a &lt;a href=\"Cave%20Bear\"&gt;Cave Bear&lt;/a&gt; would be perfect, and asks you to investigate rumors of one haunting &lt;a href=\"Dead%20Man%27s%20Pass\"&gt;Dead Man's Pass&lt;/a&gt;. He instructs you to take the pelt to &lt;a href=\"Belegarm\"&gt;Belegarm&lt;/a&gt; to have it turned into boots for him once you acquire it. The &lt;a href=\"Lucky%20Boots\"&gt;Lucky Boots&lt;/a&gt; will take Belegarm one day to make.\nCompletion.\nIn addition to simply doing as Helvdar asks, which will reward the player with 6,000 EXP and a couple of potions, the player can take a pair of &lt;a href=\"Ordinary%20Boots\"&gt;Ordinary Boots&lt;/a&gt; from Belegarm. This can be done either to get out of chasing down the cave bear pelt, or if you feel like taking the Lucky Boots for yourself. For honest dwarf protagonists, there is an additional payment for the genuine Lucky Boots; a &lt;a href=\"Periapt%20of%20Life%20Protection\"&gt;Periapt of Life Protection&lt;/a&gt;.\nTo dupe Helvdar into accepting the Ordinary Boots, you need to pass a &lt;a href=\"Charisma\"&gt;Charisma&lt;/a&gt; check. If you succeed, you will get the reward for successfully completing the mission (and also keep the Lucky Boots, if you had them made). If you fail, Helvdar will curse you and vow to let everyone know what a scumbag that you are; you receive no EXP and you lose 1 &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt;.\nYou can also create the Lucky Boots and then simply tell Helvdar that you will keep them for yourself. This will result in the same Reputation penalty as trying to cheat him with the Ordinary Boots."}
{"id": "6595", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6595", "title": "Hendak", "text": "Hendak is a proud warrior from the North until his capture by slavers during the \"\" campaign. He's currently locked up in a cell in the rear of the tavern's restricted area. Apparently he's forced to fight in the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt; in the fighting pit on a routine basis.\nGameplay.\nHe has been imprisoned longer than any of the other men and survived, though only barely, while trying to aid the other slaves in pit-battles for the amusement of noblemen as best he could.\nHe is found among the slave cells inside the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt;, owned by &lt;a href=\"Lehtinan\"&gt;Lehtinan&lt;/a&gt; (whom he refers to as a fiend). \nHe requests help from the protagonist's party to free the slaves in the side quest, &lt;a href=\"Free%20Hendak%20and%20the%20slaves\"&gt;Free Hendak and the slaves&lt;/a&gt;. A party member need only get nearby his cell to have him initiate dialogue.\nIn the southeastern corner of the Copper Coronet you will find the &lt;a href=\"Beastmaster\"&gt;Beastmaster&lt;/a&gt; whom you must kill to obtain the &lt;a href=\"Beastmaster%20Key\"&gt;Beastmaster Key&lt;/a&gt; that unlocks the slave cell doors. \nFreeing Hendak will initiate he and the other gladiators to advance through the Tavern, attacking the guards. Eventually Hendak will confront and kill Lehtinan, taking over the Copper Coronet for himself.\nAfter the take-over, he will request further aid in ridding the city of slavers. If the party accepts and puts the slavers out of business, return to Hendak (he'll know if you did it) for a reward, and a nice discount in &lt;a href=\"Bernard\"&gt;Bernard's&lt;/a&gt; shop (plus a slew of fantastic items for sale - especially for a beginning party in the Shadow's of Amn campaign)."}
{"id": "7553", "revid": "4651983", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7553", "title": "Hentold", "text": "Hentold is a grave robber in the &lt;a href=\"Valley%20of%20the%20Tombs\"&gt;Valley of the Tombs&lt;/a&gt; area east of &lt;a href=\"Carnival\"&gt;Carnival&lt;/a&gt;, who is trying to run away from an undead &lt;a href=\"Revenant%20%28Valley%20of%20the%20Tombs%29\"&gt;Revenant&lt;/a&gt; that he disturbed by taking its dagger.\nWhen you first come within sight of Hentold, he will call out for help. He is very near a random spawn point that can produce between three to four &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Dog\"&gt;wild dog&lt;/a&gt;s or &lt;a href=\"kobold\"&gt;kobold&lt;/a&gt;s, or the occasional &lt;a href=\"Ankheg\"&gt;Ankheg&lt;/a&gt;. It's possible that you may initially take the spawning of these monsters as the cause of his distress, but they are not. He has broken into a nearby tomb and angered its undead occupant by stealing a dagger. Now he begs you to take the dagger and return it. He'll permanently leave after the dialogue has finished, no matter what dialogue options you choose and whether or not you take his dagger.\nAlthough this seems very much like a typical side quest setup, but nothing is recorded in your journal.\nDialogue.\n\"Please, no! Don't let him get me... please...\"\n\"AHHH! Who are you?! Don't kill me! Please! I'm so sorry! I'll give it back, just don't kill me!\"\nother replies to dialogue attempts:\nIf you haven't returned the dagger to the Revenant:\nCharmed Dialogue:.\n\"If you're my friend, you'll let me get away from this place! A ghoulish creature pursues me in my head. I canna sleep a wink of restful sleep. I didn't mean to steal from its grave! Well, maybe i did... But I'm still sorry! Please take it back to his lonely grave for me, friend. Pal?\""}
