{"id": "49962", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49962", "title": "Herath", "text": "The Monk Herath is a character from and part of the &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%27s%20Journey\"&gt;Rasaad's Journey&lt;/a&gt; quest line.\nGameplay.\nShe is located about a hundred feet South down the road from where you arrive on the &lt;a href=\"Heretic%20Temple\"&gt;Heretic Temple&lt;/a&gt; map. She is a supposedly wounded and distressed heretic monk with some insightful dialogue regarding her recent failure to join the Twofold Trust. If Rasaad is in party, he\u2019ll attempt to help her; you may:\nIgnore her.\nTalk with her to learn some information about the Hidden Temple and let her go on her way. Perhaps offer some help.\nAsk questions to learn some insight about the temple and then kill her (as she is obviously a 'heretic') before she tries to walk away and leave the map. \nIf Rasaad is not in the party, Herath will wait indefinitely and not engage in dialogue. Rasaad's presence in your party is adds dialogue content.\nHerath has all the abilities, immunities and special bonuses afforded to a Monk commensurate with her 8th Level experience. She appears in a wounded state at this time."}
