{"id": "27779", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27779", "title": "Hidden Refuge", "text": "The Hidden Refuge is an adjacent area to the &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Forest\"&gt;Wild Forest&lt;/a&gt; where a band of wild\u00a0mages hide from the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Wizards%20of%20Thay\"&gt;Red Wizards of Thay&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\n&lt;a href=\"Neera\"&gt;Neera&lt;/a&gt; marked the party's world map with the location of this refuge. You found Neera in the wild forest, and eventually made it through the hazards, illusions and traps.\nThe party is introduced to the camp's refugees - and various dialogue and side quests can be gathered by doing so. See the Related Quest links below.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Neera%27s%20Hidden%20Refuge\"&gt;Neera's Hidden Refuge&lt;/a&gt; quest and after &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; goes to &lt;a href=\"Delosar%27s%20Inn\"&gt;Delosar's Inn&lt;/a&gt; to speak with &lt;a href=\"Daxus%20Taralom\"&gt;Daxus Taralom&lt;/a&gt;, the Red Wizards will attack the refuge leaving it destroyed and with &lt;a href=\"Telana\"&gt;Telana&lt;/a&gt; alone in the camp."}
