{"id": "3771", "revid": "264440", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3771", "title": "Hide Armor", "text": "Hide Armor is a piece of armor made for almost every class and has a armor class two points lower than &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Armor\"&gt;leather armor&lt;/a&gt;, giving better defense, but it weighs a lot more and it will decrease thieving abilities. It lowers pickpocketing, disarm/find traps and lockpicking by 10% and lowers stealth by 20%, making it unfavorable armor for &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;thieves&lt;/a&gt; and it will lower stealth for &lt;a href=\"ranger\"&gt;ranger&lt;/a&gt;s as well. It first appeared in the expansion pack.\nLocations.\n\"Baldur's Gate\".\nIn Baldur's Gate, it's sold at &lt;a href=\"Sorcerous%20Sundries\"&gt;Sorcerous Sundries&lt;/a&gt;, by &lt;a href=\"Erdane\"&gt;Erdane&lt;/a&gt; outside &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt; and at the &lt;a href=\"Ulgoth%27s%20Beard%20Inn\"&gt;Ulgoth's Beard Inn&lt;/a&gt;, because it was added by Baldur's Gate: Tales of the Sword Coast and not the original game.\n\"Shadows of Amn\".\nIn Baldur's Gate II, this armor is for sale at more stores."}
