{"id": "22673", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22673", "title": "Higgold", "text": "Higgold is a famous director that shows up at the &lt;a href=\"Five%20Flagons%20Theatre\"&gt;Five Flagons Theatre&lt;/a&gt; at the beginning of the &lt;a href=\"Bard\"&gt;Bard&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Stronghold\"&gt;Stronghold&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Running%20the%20Five%20Flagons%20Playhouse\"&gt;Running the Five Flagons Playhouse&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"Greetings, greetings, greetings! I am Higgold, director of fine theatricals, musicals and other entertainments. Most recently from Calimport, where I needn't return quickly due to the sensitivity of one particular huzzah...\"\nAfter his initial greeting, he gets down to business by assessing the theatre and musing one what will be required, leading up to the question of whether &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; will invest in the theatre or not.\n\"...but we needn't get into that. Goodman Thunderburp has told me your situation, and I would be pleased to offer my service as director of this fine concern!\"\n\"Now, let's see... yes, mm-hm... yes, this looks like a fine playhouse. Athkatla hasn't had many of these. Traveling troupes? Yes. Permanent playhouses? No.\"\n\"I know a few actors that aren't working, but it'll take some time to find them, as well as a worthy play to put into production. A week for that, I think\"\n\"About six weeks after that for rehearsing and then this playhouse of yours should start making decent coin, so long as all goes well.\"\n\"Your part, my good &lt;Man/Woman&gt;, is to provide the investment to stage the play as well as make important decisions. You'll also reap the majority of the profits.\"\n\"So... what do you say, then? Do we have a deal?\""}
{"id": "15044", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15044", "title": "High-level class ability", "text": "High-level class abilities, or High level abilities (HLAs) are epic powers gained through long time pursuit of one\u2019s career. They were first introduced in the original \"\". Mastering these epic abilities is crucial for survival when battling God-like creatures that appear in the finale of the Bhaalspawn saga.\nRequirements.\nHLAs are available to characters with more than 3,000,000 &lt;a href=\"Experience%20Tables\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt; in total for multi and single-class characters, or the same 3,000,000 XP in the current class for dualed-class characters (i.e., the XP of the original class doesn't count). These characters get one point to spend on their HLA pool every time they level up. \nNote that: \nSome HLAs may be picked only once when leveling and accordingly only used one time per rest. Others are combat skills which can be selected multiple times when leveling and used that same number of times per rest.\nQuick chart.\nLegend:\nReq.: Requirements. F(20): Fighter (level 20). R: Ranger. P: Paladin. Bl: Blackguard. Mo: Monk. C: Cleric. D: Druid. Sh: Shaman. Ma:Mage. So: Sorcerer. T:Thief. Sw: Swashbuckler. \nSd: Shadowdancer. Ba: Bard.\n1 May only be selected once.\n2 May only be selected once, except for Paladins who can select it multiple times."}
{"id": "13564", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13564", "title": "High Hall of the Radiant Heart", "text": "The High Hall of the Radiant Heart is a building in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt;. It replaces the &lt;a href=\"Most%20Noble%20Order%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart%20building\"&gt;Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart building&lt;/a&gt; once &lt;a href=\"Dorn%20Il-Khan\"&gt;Dorn Il-Khan&lt;/a&gt; is recruited."}
{"id": "2696", "revid": "34829028", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2696", "title": "High Hedge", "text": "The High Hedge area is the location of &lt;a href=\"High%20Hedge%20Estate\"&gt;High Hedge Estate&lt;/a&gt;, which is the abode of the mage &lt;a href=\"Thalantyr%20the%20Conjurer\"&gt;Thalantyr the Conjurer&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "2717", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2717", "title": "High Hedge Estate", "text": "High Hedge Estate is the home of the mage &lt;a href=\"Thalantyr%20the%20Conjurer\"&gt;Thalantyr the Conjurer&lt;/a&gt; and it also doubles as a store, offering numerous scrolls, potions, and magical items for sale.\nFlesh Golems.\nThe building is patrolled by two &lt;a href=\"Flesh%20Golem\"&gt;Flesh Golems&lt;/a&gt; which appear hostile on sight and are very dangerous for low level parties. Instead of fighting them (be aware of &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; members' AI attacks) you can avoid them and head straight to talk to Thalantyr, upon which they turn neutral and continue to patrol the premises. Alternatively, you can kill them for 2000 XP each, with no side effects.\nStore Inventory.\nEven though he says that he is interested in buying magical items, Thalantyr will, in fact, buy pretty much anything that you are carrying except ammunition and some quest items."}
