{"id": "48994", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48994", "title": "High Mornmaster Arval", "text": "High Mornmaster Arval is a Head Priest of &lt;a href=\"Lathander\"&gt;Lathander&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign. \nGameplay.\nHe is only encountered if &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; is of Good &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;Alignment&lt;/a&gt;, during the cut-scene with the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District%23The%20Eyeless%20Prophet\"&gt;\"Eyeless Prophet\"&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Gaal\"&gt;Gaal&lt;/a&gt; upon first entering the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt;; otherwise, the protagonist will either encounter &lt;a href=\"High%20Watcher%20Oisig\"&gt;High Watcher Oisig&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Helm\"&gt;Helm&lt;/a&gt; as a Neutral Ward, or &lt;a href=\"Stormherald%20Nallabir\"&gt;Stormherald Nallabir&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Talos\"&gt;Talos&lt;/a&gt; as an Evil Ward.\nRelated Quests.\n&lt;a href=\"Investigate%20and%20Destroy%20the%20Cult%20of%20the%20Eyeless\"&gt;Investigate and Destroy the Cult of the Eyeless&lt;/a&gt;\nNotes.\nIn the Classic game, the following creature values are inconsistent with his role as a leader of the Priesthood in the Temple of Lathander:"}
{"id": "56089", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56089", "title": "High Priestess (card)", "text": "The High Priestess card, can be drawn from the deck of many things when agreeing to play a game with &lt;a href=\"Aesgareth\"&gt;Aesgareth&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis page is to document the potential spell effects of this card when it is drawn.\nGameplay.\nWhen a party member character engages in the third card draw contest with Aesgareth, there is an even chance of drawing the High Priestess card, or the &lt;a href=\"Emperor%20%28card%29\"&gt;Emperor (card)&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf this card is drawn, the script controlled by Aesgareth's dialogue will apply this spell to the party member who drew the card.\nThe spell will animate a graphic visual effect and color glow over the character, and a sound effect will be audibled.\nA \"Silence\" icon is placed in the character's portrait.\nThe target is now affected by a &lt;a href=\"Silence\"&gt;Silence&lt;/a&gt; effect. This effect will not expire.\nThis spell is unaffected by magic resistance, and all of its internal components have a 0 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs the effect is coded to be a curse, a &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Curse\"&gt;Remove Curse&lt;/a&gt; is needed to eliminate it. \nA &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect won't work on this spell."}
{"id": "51897", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51897", "title": "High Priestess Tlyysixxous", "text": "High Priestess Tlyysixxous is a &lt;a href=\"sahuagin\"&gt;sahuagin&lt;/a&gt; located in the &lt;a href=\"City%20of%20Caverns\"&gt;City of Caverns&lt;/a&gt; in \"Shadows of Amn \"campaign.\nGameplay.\nThis Priestess is nearby the &lt;a href=\"King%20Ixilthetocal\"&gt;King Ixilthetocal&lt;/a&gt;, and along with &lt;a href=\"Baron%20Thelokassyil\"&gt;Baron Thelokassyil&lt;/a&gt;, she is vehemently opposed to the notion that the party are actually the ones spoken of in Sekolah's prophecy. \nThere is little chance the party will ever face this creature in battle, as the King will order her sacrifice before the party has a chance to take actions that are going to spark a fight. \nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some changes. But it won't matter, as the creature will be sacrificed before any hostilities could commence."}
