{"id": "13578", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13578", "title": "High Watcher Oisig", "text": "High Watcher Oisig is a priest of Helm who is first encountered during the in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt; following &lt;a href=\"Gaal\"&gt;Gaal&lt;/a&gt;'s spiel to some townsfolk. After a brief discussion with &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;, he will return to the nearby &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Helm%20%28Temple%20District%29\"&gt;Temple of Helm&lt;/a&gt; where he will reside for the remainder of the campaign.\nGameplay.\nHe may invite &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Investigate%20and%20Destroy%20the%20Cult%20of%20the%20Eyeless\"&gt;Investigate and Destroy the Cult of the Eyeless&lt;/a&gt;, depending on the Ward's alignment (neutral and non-evil).\nIn the party can ask the High Watcher for assistance with the planned battle to destroy the vampire coven and &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "36772", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36772", "title": "Hill Giant", "text": "Hill Giants are the smallest and weakest of the true giants in the Forgotten Realms. Unlike their more powerful cousins, such as &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Giant\"&gt;Fire Giant&lt;/a&gt;s, they have no special abilities beyond their massive strength and endurance; they are essentially a bigger, nastier version of the common &lt;a href=\"ogre\"&gt;ogre&lt;/a&gt;, and with a similar MO: hunt down whatever looks tasty or which has annoyed them and beat it into a pulp."}
