{"id": "30594", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30594", "title": "Hold Person (divine)", "text": ""}
{"id": "5007", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5007", "title": "Hold Person (priest)", "text": "Hold Person is a 2nd level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; only usable by &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt;s. It holds humans, demihumans, or humanoid creatures rigidly immobile and in place for 1 turn.\nIt is almost identical to its 3rd level &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;wizard counterpart&lt;/a&gt;, but has a longer casting time and does not impose a save penalty.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this divine spell, revising the description. See below:\nHold Person\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Enchantment\nSphere: Charm, Law\nRange: Long\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: Target, and enemies within 5\u2019\nSaving Throw: Spell negates\nThis spell holds one or more humans, demihumans, or humanoid creatures rigidly immobile and in place for one turn. The effect is centered on the victim selected by the caster. Every enemy within 5 feet of the target is also affected. Those who succeed at a saving throw vs. spell are totally unaffected by the spell. Undead creatures cannot be held with this spell.\nHeld creatures cannot move or speak, but they remain aware of events around them even though they are helpless to change them. Time passes at a normal rate for the targets and hence being held does not stop any worsening of their condition due to wounds, disease, or poison."}
{"id": "16219", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16219", "title": "Hold Person (wizard)", "text": "Hold Person holds humans, demihumans, or humanoid creatures rigidly immobile and in place for\u00a0the duration of the spell.\nGameplay.\nThe caster directs this spell at a single hostile humanoid creature using the targeting cursor.\nWhen the spell casting is finished a projectile is sent speedily to the creature and applies the spell effects onto it, and any other persons within about 5-feet of the initial target.\nDespite the description indicating that 1d4 humanoid persons can be affected, this isn't implemented. As long as there are humanoids within 5-feet of the initial target, all can be exposed.\nAn eligible exposed creature is allowed a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spell to resist it, with a 1-point penalty.\nIf a creature fails its save, then a text display reads \"Held\", and the victim has a 3D graphic effect rendered over their sprite for the spell's duration.\nIf a player character is affected, an icon (No. 13) titled \"Held\" is shown on their portrait while the spell is active.\nAdditionally, a sound effect is audibled when the spell expires.\nVictims of the spell are affected by the &lt;a href=\"Held\"&gt;Hold creature&lt;/a&gt; status effect, which makes them motionless and &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis spell can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, as well as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Enchantment&lt;/a&gt;.\nAny &lt;a href=\"Spell%20protections%20type\"&gt;Spell protections type&lt;/a&gt; defenses upon the initially targeted creature can absorb or turn this spell, for example, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Minor Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt; etc.\nHowever, other creatures caught in the spell's AoE are only afforded spell defense if under the protection of globe spells, or spell immunity.\nThe spell's effects can be removed with an applicable &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; source.\nSee the status effect page for other counters and cures.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its saving throw. See below for description:\nHold Person\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Enchantment\nRange: Long\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: Target, and enemies within 5\u2019\nSaving Throw: Spell negates\nThis spell holds one or more humans, demihumans, or humanoid creatures rigidly immobile and in place for one turn. The effect is centered on the victim selected by the caster. Every enemy within 5 feet of the target is also affected. Those who succeed at a saving throw vs. spell at -2 are totally unaffected by the spell. Undead creatures cannot be held with this spell.\nHeld creatures cannot move or speak, but they remain aware of events around them even though they are helpless to change them. Time passes at a normal rate for the targets and hence being held does not stop any worsening of their condition due to wounds, disease, or poison."}
{"id": "6082", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6082", "title": "Hold Undead", "text": "The Hold Undead spell holds undead creatures rigidly immobile and in place for the duration of the spell.\nGameplay.\nThe caster directs this spell at a single undead creature using the targeting cursor.\nWhen the spell casting is finished a projectile is sent speedily to the creature and applies the spell effects onto it, and any other undead within about 5-feet of the initial target.\nDespite the description indicating that 1d4 undead can be affected, this isn't implemented. As long as there are undead within 5-feet of the initial target, all can be exposed.\nAn exposed creature is allowed a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spell to resist it.\nIf a creature fails its save, then a text display reads \"Held\", and the victim has a 3D graphic effect rendered over their sprite for the spell's duration.\nAdditionally, a sound effect is audibled when the spell expires.\nVictims of the spell are affected by the &lt;a href=\"Hold%20creature%202\"&gt;Hold creature 2&lt;/a&gt; status effect, which makes them motionless and &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis spell can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, as well as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Necromancy&lt;/a&gt;.\nAny &lt;a href=\"Spell%20protections%20type\"&gt;Spell protections type&lt;/a&gt; defense can block this spell as well, for example, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Minor Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt; etc.\nThe spell's effects can be removed with an applicable &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; source.\nSee the status effect page for other counters and cures.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset Wizard spell \"Hold Undead\" differs in several ways from the game's implemented spell version. The caster can hold up to three undead creatures in range. Undead of a mindless nature (skeletons, zombies, or ghouls) are automatically affected. Other forms of undead are allowed a saving throw to negate the effect.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, with a new name. revising its saving throw and duration. See below for description:\nHalt Undead\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Necromancy\nRange: Long\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 3\nArea of Effect: Target, and enemies within 5\u2019\nSaving Throw: Spell negates\nThis spell stops undead creatures in their place for the duration of the spell. The effect is centered on the victim selected by the caster. Any undead creatures within 5 feet of the target are also affected. Those who succeed at a saving throw vs. spell at -2 are totally unaffected by the spell.\nThose affected become unable move or groan, but they remain aware of events around them even though they are helpless to change them. Time passes at a normal rate for the targets and hence the effect does not stop any worsening of their condition due to injury or rot."}
{"id": "47041", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47041", "title": "Hold creature", "text": ""}
{"id": "47042", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47042", "title": "Hold creature 2", "text": "Hold creature 2 is one of the \"held\" status effects, and works exactly like &lt;a href=\"Hold%20creature\"&gt;Hold creature&lt;/a&gt;: Any held creature is unable to move or take any action whatsoever and is considered &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt; \u2014 physical attacks against it will always connect as &lt;a href=\"Combat%23The_attack_roll\"&gt;attack rolls&lt;/a&gt; are skipped entirely, which incidentally means no critical hits either.\nWhile functionally identical to Hold creature, it is an entirely separate effect, and few things in the game cause or protect from it. &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Paralysis\"&gt;Remove Paralysis&lt;/a&gt; cannot cure it.\nIn-game labels.\nThe Baldur's Gate series is inconsistent in providing accurate labels for each of the \"held\" effects which all share the same portrait icon: &lt;a href=\"Held\"&gt;Hold creature&lt;/a&gt;, Hold creature 2 and &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;Paralyze&lt;/a&gt;. Such labels may be found in an affected character's \"Record\" screen, in-game combat logs, or simply spell, item or ability descriptions.\nTypically, we could expect that a \"held\" affecting a party member should refer to the Hold creature effect, and \"paralyzed\" to the Paralyze effect, but don't bet your house on it.\nIf unsure, take a look at this page's infobox. It only contains sources that really do inflict the Hold creature 2 effect.\nTrivia.\nPrevious versions of IESDP titled the &lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;Opcode&lt;/a&gt; 185 effect code as STATE: Hold Creature III. The Hold effect states were at one time 109 STATE: Hold Creature I, and 175 was STATE: Hold Creature II.\nMod content.\nThe upcoming release of &lt;a href=\"https%3A//www.gibberlings3.net/mods/fixes/eefp/\"&gt;Enhanced Edition Fix Pack (EEFP)&lt;/a&gt; has already beta coded a large overhaul pertaining to Hold Creature 2, as follows:\nRevamp of Hold, Paralysis, and Web \nIn the original Baldur's Gate, there were four internal methods to make an NPC freeze: paralysis (used in undead melee attacks), web (used by the spell of the same name and spiders), and two forms of hold (one for Hold spells and a second, special one reserved for special cases like cutscenes).\nAs the series progressed through the BG expansion, into BG2, and concluding with Throne of Bhaal, these were used more and more freely, and muddled--you had web spells using paralysis, abilities that blocked the special hold (which nothing should) to the point where there was little distinction, if any, between these effects from a player's point of view. \nEEFP is re-establishing the scheme, going all the way back to the original Baldur's Gate, of trying to use these effects in a way that differentiates them and fixes a number of bugs along the way. Paralysis is, once again, the domain of undead attacks, and from which elves have some protection. Web is no longer paired by default with paralysis, meaning items which protect you from web no longer provide paralysis protection by accident, and the special hold will now always take effect."}
