{"id": "13373", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13373", "title": "Horn House", "text": "Horn House is a house in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; during \"\". This house in the northeast part of the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; does not have an official name. It is called \"Horn House\" because it contains the famous &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Horn%20of%20Valhalla\"&gt;Silver Horn of Valhalla&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere are several floor traps on both levels of the house and some containers are also trapped.\nMod content.\nThe \"&lt;a href=\"Fade%20NPC\"&gt;Fade NPC&lt;/a&gt;\" mod adds &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt;'s mother \"Mrs. Linvail\" to the ground floor, and labels this house \"Mrs. Linvail's Home\" on the Bridge District area map.\nThe \"&lt;a href=\"Region%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Region of Terror&lt;/a&gt;\" mega-mod adds the slaver \"Mendor\" to the upper floor, in relation to the side-quest \"Clob's Son Missing\"."}
{"id": "6358", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6358", "title": "Horn of Blasting", "text": "The Horn of Blasting is an item that can be found in and game editions.\nDescription.\nGeneral desctiption&lt;a href=\"Identify\"&gt;Identified&lt;/a&gt; description\nGameplay.\nThe item is placed in a character's \"Quick Item\" slot {like a wand or scroll is used), and the player selects the item with the game interface cursor to select a targeted area of effect.\nThe horn launches a fast-moving projectile that explodes centered at the point selected by the player, in exactly the same radius as a fireball - in fact it looks just like a fireball.\nThe projectile can be aimed so that it doesn't affect the user and has a listed range of 50 feet.\nDespite the description, and mention of \"poor Julius\" being blown apart, this horn's sonic attack only affects hostile creatures in the area of effect of the shockwave. These effects are:\nThe horn makes a unique sound effect as well.\nAll of the horn's effects are non-magical and have 0 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt;, and the sonic attack is \"school less\" with no secondary type.\nThere are no defenses against the effects, other than crushing damage mitigation, or immunity to &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Wing%20buffet\"&gt;Wing buffet&lt;/a&gt; effects.\nAquisition.\nThe horn can be found in &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Maze\"&gt;Firkraag's Maze&lt;/a&gt;, a dungeon level reachable from the &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt; map."}
{"id": "30120", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30120", "title": "Horn of Silence", "text": "Gameplay.\nThe user of this horn activates the Horn's power by first equipping the item in an appropriate slot (like a book or wand would). The power is aimed at a location in range, using the cursor on the map to select the desired center of the area of effect. \nWhen it is activated, a fast-moving sparkle projectile travels to the selected aiming point and an animation plays on the map. A sound effect will also be audible.\nThe various effects now manifest and can affect all creatures in the area of effect (including self and allies). Any creatures exposed must save vs. the &lt;a href=\"Silence\"&gt;Silence&lt;/a&gt; status effect with a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Breath Attack. \nSuccess negates the effect. Failure means the creature is silenced, and an appropriate icon will appear in the creature's portrait icon, and the combat log will display a text string \"Silenced\", and a 3D graphics effect will play over the affected creature. \nThe effect will last for 1 turn.\nNote that &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; can block this effect. \nSpell level protections like &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; won't affect it as the sonic wave has &lt;a href=\"power%20level\"&gt;power level&lt;/a&gt; 0. Creatures with innate spell level immunities (such as a &lt;a href=\"Lich\"&gt;Lich&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Rakshasa\"&gt;Rakshasa&lt;/a&gt;) will have no special protection against this item's sonic power.\nA &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect can remove the silence status effect, but the portrait icon won't be removed (probably an oversight coding faux pas).\nLaunching the horn's sonic blast is coded as a \"Hostile\" spell action, but only if the creature fails its save versus the silence effect.\nA &lt;a href=\"Vocalize\"&gt;Vocalize&lt;/a&gt; spell effect can counter the silence.\nLocation.\nCan be found in a container only in on the main floor of the &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt; Asylum."}
{"id": "4978", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4978", "title": "Horror", "text": "Horror may potentially cause all hostile creatures to flee in terror.\nGameplay.\nThe caster designates a point on the area map to aim this spell toward - use the targeting cursor to set the point location.\nWhen the spell casting is finished a projectile moves to the designated point, then radiates out the spell effect to all hostile creatures in the area of effect. There is a 3D effect that renders on the spot selected for the spell's targeting point (a sort of grimacing face).\nEnemies are allowed a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spells to negate the spell's effect.\nA failed saving throw will cause a &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; effect for the spell's duration. An affected creature will render a 3D effect graphic over the victim's sprite, and a text display reads \"Panic\".\nA player character affected by this spell will show an icon (No. 36) titled \"Panic\" placed on their portrait.\nThis spell is coded with a secondary type \"\"Disabling\" classification and is not flagged as a \"Hostile\"\" spell - it won't affect or elicit a response from non-enemy creatures.\nSince the spell exposes enemies to the Panic status effect, it can be counteracted by spells like &lt;a href=\"Resist%20Fear\"&gt;Resist Fear&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Fear\"&gt;Remove Fear&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe innate ability bhaalspawn power version of this spell works a little differently: it has a faster casting time of 1, instead of 2, but only lasts 3 rounds, as opposed to 10 rounds.\nThere also exists the &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Fear\"&gt;Wand of Fear&lt;/a&gt; in both games, which applies a similar effect - but allows enemies a +2 bonus to save against it, although it also has a 50% longer duration.\nThis spell can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, as well as a &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Necromancy&lt;/a&gt;.\nSaving throws differ by game version - see the InfoBox.\nWhere to obtain its scroll.\n\"Throne of Bhaal\".\n\"&lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; may gain this spell as a special ability in Baldur's Gate: Enhanced Edition during &lt;a href=\"Dreams%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;dreams 3 and 4&lt;/a&gt; with a reputation of 9 or lower. (replaced Ghoul Touch from original BG)\"\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset has no equivalent level 2 Wizard Spell such as Horror, Fear or Panic. \nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its duration. See below for description:\nHorror\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Necromancy\nRange: Long\nDuration: 5 rounds\nCasting Time: 2\nArea of Effect: 30\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: Spell negates\nWhen this spell is cast, all enemies within the area of effect must save vs. spell or flee in terror. Certain creatures are immune to the effects of fear, including all undead."}
