{"id": "31500", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31500", "title": "House Jae'llat", "text": "House Jae'llat is a residence in &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt; and home to &lt;a href=\"Hindra%20Jae%27llat\"&gt;Hindra Jae'llat&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Rilloa%20Jae%27llat\"&gt;Rilloa Jae'llat&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ist%27tar%20Jae%27llat\"&gt;Ist'tar Jae'llat&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0This building requires the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Jae%27llat%20Wardstone\"&gt;Jae'llat Wardstone&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0to enter, obtained from the &lt;a href=\"Intrigue%20with%20Jarlaxle\"&gt;Intrigue with Jarlaxle&lt;/a&gt; questline only.\nGameplay.\nIf the party has possession of the &lt;a href=\"Jae%27llat%20Wardstone\"&gt;Jae'llat Wardstone&lt;/a&gt;, they may enter this area. An interesting battle awaits within - made more difficult by the defenders' innate drow magic resistance. \nThe entire place will go hostile and attempt to repel or kill you, the invaders. The first group will quickly spring into action as the party first transitions inside.\nFurther within if you take an easterly path, are some other family members of House Jae'llat and more guards on the lower platforms. \nIn general, the battle will take place with two groups of defenders. Rilloa commands the first group upon entry to the House, while Hindra and Ist'tar are in the second.\nTreasure.\nAside from personal items that can be obtained from defeated bodies, there are a number of containers that can be examined in the home, you may find some random treasures, as well as:\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes a few changes to all of the creatures. Additionally, if the \"Improved Drow\" component is installed, there will be additional guards added to the original existing ones, by initiating the \"\"DMWWJaellatReinforce\",\"GLOBAL\",1\" script. The script will place (in various locations) additional defenders, including:\nAll these spell casters will perform more intelligently if you have installed the \"Smarter Mages\" and or Cleric components.\nIn the unmodified game, the party will likely have two distinct battle phases between the two groups of defenders. With SCS's \"Better calls for help\" component, Hindra and her bodyguards will move to the entry platform and try and overcome the party with numbers.\nIf the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod is installed, the drow's memorized spells will be the SR versions.\nIf you have installed the &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Construction%20for%20Spellcasters\"&gt;Golem Construction for Spellcasters&lt;/a&gt; Mod, then a unique \"Perfect Clay Golem\" is placed in the Jae'llat House to help defend it. This creature is loyal to the drow, and is a bit tougher than a usual &lt;a href=\"Clay%20Golem\"&gt;Clay Golem&lt;/a&gt;. Works with other Mods as well, including SCS."}
