{"id": "51236", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51236", "title": "House of Desharik's Lover", "text": "House of Desharik's Lover or \"Cayia's Home\" is a freestanding residence on the Southwest Part of &lt;a href=\"Brynnlaw\"&gt;Brynnlaw&lt;/a&gt;, on a main street. This residence is home to Pirate Lord &lt;a href=\"Desharik\"&gt;Desharik&lt;/a&gt;'s lover, &lt;a href=\"Cayia\"&gt;Cayia&lt;/a&gt;, although the party may not become aware of that until much later, or perhaps not at all.\nDescription.\nThis single-level structure with a flat roof. It has one doorway. The internal layout is just one room, furnished with beds, table and chairs and some storage chests, shelving, wardrobe and similar mundane home accouterments. \nGameplay.\nThe home can be entered anytime. No one is home.\nThe exception to this is after accepting an optional questline associated with &lt;a href=\"Saemon%20Havarian\"&gt;Saemon Havarian&lt;/a&gt; and his plan to steal Pirate Lord Desharik's ship to depart Brynnlaw. This is only available after resolving the &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt; confrontation with &lt;a href=\"Irenicus\"&gt;Irenicus&lt;/a&gt;. That plot requires obtaining the &lt;a href=\"Pirate%20Horn\"&gt;Pirate Horn&lt;/a&gt; from Cayia, who is Desharik's current lover.\nSee the &lt;a href=\"Leaving%20the%20island\"&gt;Leaving the island&lt;/a&gt; page for details about this questline.\nContainers.\nThere are several containers that can be examined within the area. These can be rummaged through, and anything found can be removed. "}
{"id": "13396", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13396", "title": "House of the Elemental Lich", "text": "The House of the Elemental Lich is a house in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign. This house does not have an official name, taking its nickname from the &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Lich%20%28Bridge%20District%29\"&gt;Elemental Lich&lt;/a&gt; who holds &lt;a href=\"Kangaxx\"&gt;Kangaxx's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Golden%20Torso\"&gt;Golden Torso&lt;/a&gt;.\nWARNING: The southeastern-facing door is trapped \"(&lt;a href=\"Find%20Traps%20%28skill%29\"&gt;80&lt;/a&gt; | Disintegrate)\" and locked \"(&lt;a href=\"Open%20Locks\"&gt;80&lt;/a&gt;)\" and leads to a different area, assuming you have a &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Stone\"&gt;Rogue Stone&lt;/a&gt; in your inventory. If you make the mistake of entering unprepared, the door is gone and you must fight your way out. For further info, see the &lt;a href=\"Twisted%20Rune%20Hideout\"&gt;Twisted Rune Hideout&lt;/a&gt;.\nLayout.\nEntrance to the first floor is gained through the street-level, southwestern-facing door.\nThe first floor layout is exactly the same as the first floor of the &lt;a href=\"Tanner%20Shop\"&gt;Tanner Shop&lt;/a&gt;, except that there is a third container. Containers include a square table near the door, a work table across the room, and a wicker basket.\nDownstairs is the Crypt, home to an &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Lich%20%28Bridge%20District%29\"&gt;Elemental Lich&lt;/a&gt;. Clicking the sarcophagus gives you a warning status message.\"You feel very uneasy as you approach the sarcophagus. The lid looks heavy but you could remove it if you wish to.\"Clicking again releases its occupant. Clicking once more after beating the lich gets you the &lt;a href=\"Golden%20Torso\"&gt;Golden Torso&lt;/a&gt;."}
