{"id": "11138", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11138", "title": "Huge Spider", "text": "Huge Spiders are enemies found commonly across the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Tethyr\"&gt;Tethyr&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThey have more health than ordinary &lt;a href=\"spiders\"&gt;spiders&lt;/a&gt; but are still one of the weakest varieties. They are distinguishable from their brethren by way of an orange body with dark-green legs. Like most spiders, they can &lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt; their enemies and are immune to &lt;a href=\"Webbed\"&gt;webs&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0 and &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;paralysis&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0. However, they are still relatively susceptible to most other movement restricting magics, such as &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Monster\"&gt;Hold Monster&lt;/a&gt;. Spiders are considered monsters, and are not affected by &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Animal\"&gt;Hold Animal&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Animal\"&gt;Charm Animal&lt;/a&gt;.\nSurprisingly, for such a low level creature, their attacks are treated as having +3 enchantment level."}
