{"id": "37997", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37997", "title": "Hyreth", "text": "Hyreth is a soldier in the grand coalition army who seeks to fight the Shining Crusade of &lt;a href=\"Caelar%20Argent\"&gt;Caelar Argent&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". A devout worshipper of &lt;a href=\"Ilmater\"&gt;Ilmater&lt;/a&gt;, Hyreth's religious zeal can sometimes overwhelm his common sense.\nInvolvement.\nHyreth can be encountered in the triage camp area in the southwest of the &lt;a href=\"Coalition%20Camp\"&gt;Coalition Camp&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Ten%20%E2%80%93%20Allied%20Siege%20Camp\"&gt;Chapter Ten \u2013 Allied Siege Camp&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe has recently been injured quite severely, but is refusing to allow himself to be treated because he feels it brings him closer to his patron god. Talking to him reveals this backstory, and begins the &lt;a href=\"side%20quest\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Wounded%20Zealot\"&gt;The Wounded Zealot&lt;/a&gt;\".\n\"The Wounded Zealot\".\nHealing Hyreth against his will yields &lt;a href=\"experience\"&gt;experience&lt;/a&gt; but costs one point of &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt;. He will leave then."}
