{"id": "51373", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51373", "title": "ICETRL.ITM", "text": "ICETRL.ITM is an weapon used by various &lt;a href=\"Blizzard%20Troll\"&gt;Blizzard Troll&lt;/a&gt; creatures and is typically equipped in the first \"Quick weapon\" slot.\nEffects.\nThe weapon is considered a &lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; weapon of &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20item\"&gt;enchantment&lt;/a&gt; level 2 and deals damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of one.\nAny hit on a target requires a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Breath Attack with a -2 penalty. If the saving throw is made then the targeted creature takes half the . If the saving throw is missed, then the full rolled cold damage is applied, as well as a &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; status effect lasting 3 rounds, and a -1 &lt;a href=\"Dexterity\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; with a duration of 5 rounds.\nThe cold damage bypasses magic resistance and spell level protections such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;. The Stun effect and Dexterity attribute drain are also a &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;level 0&lt;/a&gt; (zero) effect and ignore spell level protections. However, they are blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and can be removed with a Dispel magic function."}
{"id": "50134", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50134", "title": "IESDP", "text": "The Infinity Engine Structures Description Project, or IESDP, is a comprehensive multi-decade resource still actively maintained to this day. All Baldur's Gate games use the &lt;a href=\"Infinity%20Engine\"&gt;Infinity Engine&lt;/a&gt;.\nDefinition.\nAccording to the website's FAQ, the IESDP is an effort to research the workings of the Bioware Infinity Engine\u00ae, and act as a collective resource for those interested in such workings.\nGoals.\nAccording to the website's FAQ, the goal of this project is:\n&lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;Status Effects&lt;/a&gt; information.\nOne of the areas most useful to this Wiki's readers might be the pages on status effects. They are of course quite a bit technical, but very thorough and rarely incorrect or incomplete. The Infinity Engine version used varies from game to game, so pick the right IESDP link based on your needs:"}
{"id": "53161", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53161", "title": "II-Khan Soldier", "text": "II-Khan Soldier is a game file name for several soldier types associated with &lt;a href=\"Saradush\"&gt;Saradush&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Gromnir%20Il-Khan\"&gt;Gromnir Il-Khan&lt;/a&gt; in the part of the saga, &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%208\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 8&lt;/a&gt;.\nTypes of Soldiers.\nThe game has created four varieties of these soldiers, all sharing the same file creature name. Each type has more than one creature resource .cre file assigned. Individual pages are prepared for viewing by selecting the links, below:\nNotes.\nThese soldiers are loyal to &lt;a href=\"Gromnir%20Il-Khan\"&gt;Gromnir Il-Khan&lt;/a&gt;, and not officially part of the city Militia. They are found in various places and in various quantities in the city of Saradush, their barracks, as well as in other areas below the city, and within the Saradush castle areas."}
{"id": "53160", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53160", "title": "II-Khan Soldier (Male Berserker)", "text": "II-Khan Soldier (Male Berserker) is a fighter class NPC found in areas associated with &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%208\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 8&lt;/a&gt; and the city of &lt;a href=\"Saradush\"&gt;Saradush&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nThese male human soldiers are in several locations in Saradush, There are two different creature files with this design.\nThe soldiers are &lt;a href=\"Berserker\"&gt;Berserker&lt;/a&gt; kitted fighters in name only. Their scripts don't use &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt;. They'll fight with their Halberds if made hostile.\nThe creature scripts allow for potion quaffing and use at predetermined thresholds during battle, mostly for healing purposes. Use depends on what potion type is furnished to the creatures quick item use slots. Thy'll shout for help when attacked and can possibly alert other allied creatures to assist.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes minor revisions to these creatures. A new default AI is assigned for better tactical behavior. &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; use is added, and &lt;a href=\"Power%20Attack\"&gt;Power Attack&lt;/a&gt; is scripted for use. Their berserker kit ability will also be initiated at the start of battle with &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt;.\nWeapon proficiencies are revised with 3 pips in Halberd, and 2 pips in two-handed weapon fighting style. All combat performance skills will now improve, such as &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;, weapon damage, weapon speed factor, critical hit chances etc.\nSCS adds a few more potion choices for use during combat, such as &lt;a href=\"Oil%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Oil of Speed&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Superior%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Superior Healing&lt;/a&gt; when wounded."}
{"id": "51119", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51119", "title": "ILLBLUR.ITM", "text": "ILLBLUR.ITM is an undroppable ring used by various &lt;a href=\"Spectral%20Troll\"&gt;Spectral Troll&lt;/a&gt; and other creatures that are to have \"blurry\" semi-transparent cosmetic appearance. Although the item is a ring, it can be placed in other slots by the game engine (such as a helmet or amulet). It does not affect the item's applied effects.\nThe item actually applies &lt;a href=\"IESDP\"&gt;IESDP&lt;/a&gt; effect code number 66 \"Transparency Fade\"."}
