{"id": "51447", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51447", "title": "I Shall Never Forget", "text": "I Shall Never Forget is a melancholic quest mod for &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Shadows of Amn&lt;/a&gt;.\nOverview.\nThe &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; meets a scientist whose lover has died, and who has become obsessed with finding a way to bring her back at any cost \u2013 blind to the further harm his actions are causing to himself and those around him.&lt;br&gt;\nHe pays you good money to help him out with simple tasks in service of his goal, but how far can you justify enabling him?\nHow to start the quest.\nEnter the \"2nd Floor Observatory\" in the &lt;a href=\"Government%20District\"&gt;Government District&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;\nExternal links.\n\"(For the mod's main website/forum/download page, see the infobox above.)\""}
{"id": "32062", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32062", "title": "I met a strange man on the road to the Friendly Arm Inn.", "text": "\"I met a strange man on the road to the Friendly Arm Inn\" is a &lt;a href=\"journal\"&gt;journal&lt;/a&gt; entry in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\".\nThis entry is not directly related to a &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;, but will be obtained when following the suggestions of the &lt;a href=\"Important%20Events\"&gt;Important Events&lt;/a&gt;, specifically &lt;a href=\"Go%20to%20the%20Friendly%20Arm%20Inn\"&gt;going to the Friendly Arm Inn&lt;/a&gt;. Upon leaving the &lt;a href=\"Lion%27s%20Way\"&gt;Lion's Way&lt;/a&gt; to the east and arriving on the &lt;a href=\"Coast%20Way\"&gt;Coast Way&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; will be greeted by an &lt;a href=\"Old%20Man\"&gt;old man&lt;/a&gt; who'd like to know if they count themselves as \"desperate or [\u2026] deranged.\"\nReply might be given as for both options, with a neutral third one in addition. No matter which one is chosen, the following appears as a note in the journal, while the old man leaves.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;\n&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nThis will not remain the only meeting with the old man \u2026"}
{"id": "41233", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41233", "title": "Ice Golem", "text": "Ice Golem may spawn in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Final Seal&lt;/a&gt;, as well as the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe Ice Golem is a rare and unusual type of construct that is a mostly a mindless automaton that will attempt to crush enemy creatures with its bludgeoning fists. It will engage the nearest enemy it can detect and then proceed to forcefully whale away.\nThe golem has a number of typical immunities as most golems do and can only be struck by magical or enchanted weapon attacks. See the InfoBox for a listing.\nThere is the special &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Golem%20%28Guardian%20of%20Ice%29\"&gt;Ice Golem (Guardian of Ice)&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt;, which requires +3 weapons to hit.\nWhen the golem is hit by any sort of fire damage, the golem produces a &lt;a href=\"Scalding%20Steam\"&gt;Scalding Steam&lt;/a&gt; effect, which is implemented as an innate spell.\nThis spell manifests as a \"White Fireball\" animation centered on the golem, that explodes in a 15' diameter in all directions. Any creatures in the area of effect are potentially exposed to the \"steam\", which can inflict 10d3 &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;Cold damage&lt;/a&gt;. A saving throw vs. breath will negate, and a &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; will block it, and so can &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Scalding Steam can occur over and over, anytime the golem is hit by fire damage.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Construction%20for%20Spellcasters\"&gt;Golem Construction for Spellcasters&lt;/a&gt; mod adds a droppable item when the golem is defeated. It is a shard of special ice that can be used as a necessary component when the party mage attempts to build their own Ice Golem.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod and the installation of the \"AI Enhancements\" component improves many aspects of creatures encountered in the game. In regard to golems, the mod implements the following:\nImproved Golems (BG2, BG2EE, BGT/EET)&lt;br&gt;\nThis component doesn't really make golems smarter (they're supposed to be stupid) But it streamlines their scripts a bit, gives their weapons a sensible range, makes them immune to \"Lower Resistance\" and to poison, and tries to prevent situations where golems get stuck behind barricades.\nIce golems are immune to the &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Resistance\"&gt;Lower Resistance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Magic\"&gt;Pierce Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Shield\"&gt;Pierce Shield&lt;/a&gt; spells.&lt;br&gt;\nIf you damage an SCS golem, and then decide to back away and rest somewhere, to continue the fight later, the golem will be restored to full health.&lt;br&gt;\nThe Ice golem gets a revised AI script to change their targeting behavior slightly. In addition to the Scalding Steam ability, the Ice Golem also is able to unleash a &lt;a href=\"Cone%20of%20Cold\"&gt;Cone of Cold&lt;/a&gt;, about every three rounds of combat, as long as an enemy is within 10 feet of the golem. This spell is cast at will and has no limit as long as the golem is functioning."}
{"id": "55659", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55659", "title": "Ice Golem (Guardian of Ice)", "text": "The Ice Golem is the Guardian of Ice found in the Ice Laboratory on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThis golem creature was constructed and devised by the former Ice Elementalist Wizard, as well as the special &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Mist\"&gt;Ice Mist&lt;/a&gt; creatures found alongside it.\nOnce the party is in possession of the &lt;a href=\"Slime%20Scepter\"&gt;Slime Scepter&lt;/a&gt;, the locked gate on the connection to the Slime Library that bars entry into the Ice Laboratory can be opened, and the party can enter that chamber where the creature is. The gate connecting to the Ice Library will still locked until the party possesses the &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Scepter\"&gt;Ice Scepter&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the party enters the Ice Laboratory the guardian and ice mists will attack. The guardian will launch a &lt;a href=\"Cone%20of%20Cold\"&gt;Cone of Cold&lt;/a&gt; after a short delay at any detected enemy. This can be done again on a timed basis, over and over, depending on how long the creature is viable.\nThe guardian and mists will attempt to close to melee range and attack the nearest enemy they can find.\nIf the party has not performed the actions described in the &lt;a href=\"Slime%20Library%20Note\"&gt;Slime Library Note&lt;/a&gt;, they will quickly find out that the creatures in the ice laboratory are immune to all attempts to damage or harm them by the party.\nThe Ice chamber itself gives an advantage to the ice creatures within, as the bone chilling temperatures will apply a transient &lt;a href=\"Slow%20effect\"&gt;Slow effect&lt;/a&gt; upon any party members who venture within. Like any slow effect, this can be countered with &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action\"&gt;Free Action&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrying to draw these creatures out of the Ice Laboratory will prove difficult, as they will only move so far from their protective chamber before moving back inside.\nIn order to actually destroy these creatures, the Ice Laboratory chamber must be flooded with the toxic vapors produced in the Slime Laboratory, as described in the Slime Library Note. This action requires opening connecting gates and activating the magical fan to maximum - basically blowing air from the fan chamber, into the Slime laboratory, through the Slime Library and into the Ice Laboratory. Only then, when a party member enters the Ice lab will a poison cloud appear and render the ice creatures vulnerable to attacks.\nThe Guardian of Ice can only be hit by weapons of at least +3 enchantment (including &lt;a href=\"The%20Kneecapper\"&gt;The Kneecapper&lt;/a&gt;, which has normally +1 but +4 against golems). \nRecover the Ice Scepter from the dead Ice Golem guardian. This scepter allows the opening of the Ice lab's connecting gate to the Ice Library."}
{"id": "7934", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7934", "title": "Ice Island", "text": "The Ice Island is an area where &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; will be teleported to by the mage &lt;a href=\"Shandalar\"&gt;Shandalar&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Ulgoth%27s%20Beard\"&gt;Ulgoth's Beard&lt;/a&gt;. He wants the party to &lt;a href=\"retrieve%20Shandalar%27s%20Cloak\"&gt;retrieve&lt;/a&gt; his &lt;a href=\"Shandalar%27s%20Cloak\"&gt;cloak&lt;/a&gt; \u2014 either by agreeing to help him voluntarily with this &lt;a href=\"Quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; or by forcing them to undertake it.\nThe location and exact nature of the island are unknown, although some people theorize that it is a type of teleportation prison.\nThe log, however states another direction: \"You have been teleported by Shandalar, far up to the north, on an island lost within the ice floes of the northern ocean.\"\nThe island has two levels: the surface and an underground dungeon. On the surface a &lt;a href=\"Polar%20Bear\"&gt;Polar Bear&lt;/a&gt; is strolling around, while a second one is encountered inside the dungeon. Also in the dungeon are several &lt;a href=\"Winter%20Wolf\"&gt;Winter Wolves&lt;/a&gt; along with seven &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;s. One of the mages, all of whom are trapped on the island, will be in possession of the cloak.\nWalkthrough.\nWhen entering the maze in the southeast of the map, two Winter Wolves will attack the party, with the second one waiting around the corner.\nIn the first bigger hall, a group of mages awaits: the \"island greeter\" &lt;a href=\"Andris\"&gt;Andris&lt;/a&gt;, together with &lt;a href=\"Beyn\"&gt;Beyn&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Marcellus\"&gt;Marcellus&lt;/a&gt;. No matter how Gorion's Ward negotiates \u2013 a fight ensues. The &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;from normal missiles protected&lt;/a&gt; Andris will first use a &lt;a href=\"Dimension%20Door\"&gt;Dimension Door&lt;/a&gt;, while the &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;shielded&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 and thus immune against spells from &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;level 1 to 3&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 Beyn &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;steps aside&lt;/a&gt; for a moment. For more information about their specific spell casting abilities, see their individual character pages.\nFrom here, three pathways lead off deeper into the maze. Either follow the long and complete path, or &lt;a href=\"%23short\"&gt;jump&lt;/a&gt; to the one that directly leads to the person and the item you came here looking for.\nWhen following the left of the two northeastern paths, after disabling a &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Strike\"&gt;trap&lt;/a&gt; at its entrance, in the next big hall another Winter Wolf is encountered \u2013 with the mage &lt;a href=\"Cuchol\"&gt;Cuchol&lt;/a&gt; in sight, who will initiate dialogue before eventual combat ensues. He's an opponent very similar to Beyn, including the spell immunity.\nThe path to the southeast, out of this hall, is &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;trapped&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn the long hall directly west to the first one with the three mages, &lt;a href=\"Garan\"&gt;Garan&lt;/a&gt; questions the party. After losing his patience, he will summon his four &lt;a href=\"Ankheg\"&gt;pets&lt;/a&gt;, before leaving the battlefield for a short time through a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt;.\nLeaving that hall to the west leads through a narrow and contorted path, with a Polar Bear at a southwestern expansion \u2013 and a &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;trap&lt;/a&gt; on the floor behind it before ending in a dead end alley. Traveling east, two more Winter Wolves are encountered in the recess near the entrance hall.\nThe right of the two northeastern paths out of the entrance hall is &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missiles\"&gt;trapped&lt;/a&gt; though this one is located a couple of feet away from its beginning. Further down the way, two more traps are set: the first &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;trap&lt;/a&gt; around halfway up of the northernmost section, and the second &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;trap&lt;/a&gt; right around the following corner \u2013 nearly in eyeshot of the next mage.\n&lt;a href=\"Tellan\"&gt;Tellan&lt;/a&gt; is the only one here with whom a fight can be avoided \u2013 by making an offer to take him with you, while asking for his assistance. The latter, however, won't be given \u2013 he just follows your way, or gets in it, and in the end you only can leave him down here. He too is protected from normal missiles.\nAround the corner behind Tellan, the path leads into a more open area, with three more Winter Wolves to the left and \u2013 just out of sight to the right is the last actor in this play; the one who's left; the one who has to be the bearer of the cloak you're looking for \u2013 who, if not he? &lt;a href=\"Dezkiel\"&gt;Dezkiel&lt;/a&gt; is the most talkative of the mages in the dungeon; the one with the most insights and philosophical thoughts. But all that won't keep him from attacking you in the end. Beware his immunity to spells of level 1 to 3.\nAfter taking Shandalar's cloak from Dezkiel's body, together with some &lt;a href=\"Dezkiel%27s%20Scroll\"&gt;sort of journal&lt;/a&gt;, the door behind him leads back to the island's entry point \u2013 more weird and twisted magic in this place. It won't take long, and Shandalar's callback spell becomes effective automatically, now that the &lt;a href=\"Shandalar%27s%20Wardstone\"&gt;wardstone&lt;/a&gt; and cloak are reunited in the open \u2013 the party gets teleported back to Ulgoth's Beard."}
{"id": "27871", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27871", "title": "Ice Library Note", "text": "The Ice Library Note is found in \"\" on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;second floor&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt; in the Ice Library. The note details one of the four tactics to defeating the &lt;a href=\"Chromatic%20Demon\"&gt;Chromatic Demon&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "11843", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11843", "title": "Ice Mephit", "text": "An Ice Mephit is an extra-planar \"outsider\" (i.e., linked to various Elemental, Quasi-Elemental and Outer planes of existence). These creatures are similar to &lt;a href=\"Imp\"&gt;Imps&lt;/a&gt;, and are found in a number of areas during the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;\"Baldur's Gate II\"&lt;/a&gt; games.\nGameplay.\nThe Ice Mephit needs to get fairly close in order to attack in melee with its claws, or near enough to get within range of its innate ability attack, &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Shard\"&gt;Ice Shard&lt;/a&gt;. The Ice shard is launched at a target in range as soon as detected, and then repeats every three rounds afterwards. It has an endless supply of this attack option.\nThe Ice Mephit has elemental resistance to cold, but is particularly vulnerable to fire damage, taking extra if affected by that damage type. It has no magic resistance but retains some immunities to certain status effects as shown in the InfoBox."}
{"id": "55662", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55662", "title": "Ice Mist", "text": "The Ice Mist creatures are located with the &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Golem%20%28Guardian%20of%20Ice%29\"&gt;Guardian of Ice&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt; Ice Laboratory.\nGameplay.\nThis undead creature is nigh invulnerable to death and being harmed, at least until a specific action is taken by the party.\nThe creature will be periodically healed due to the snow drift vents in the frigid ice laboratory chamber.\nThe party can overcome this problem by implementing the plan outlined in the &lt;a href=\"Slime%20Library%20Note\"&gt;Slime Library Note&lt;/a&gt;. The methodology outlined in the note may be the only way to make these creatures vulnerable and allow a chance to destroy them.\nIf the actions described in the note are properly performed, the Ice Mist creatures will lose their near total invulnerability and can be harmed by several standard attack options. This action will remove the &lt;a href=\"INVULNER.ITM\"&gt;special ring&lt;/a&gt; that bestows their invulnerability.\nWhen faced in close quarters combat with these creatures, their melee attacks can inflict physical damage, cold damage and expose the target to a potential &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; effect, although a saving throw is allowed to resist it. For more information see the details on their &lt;a href=\"MISTICE.ITM\"&gt;Weapon&lt;/a&gt; page.\nIce mist creatures can see/sense invisible and hidden creatures in their detection range."}
{"id": "36752", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36752", "title": "Ice Salamander", "text": "Ice Salamanders are a species of extraplanar reptilian humanoids that resemble blue-skinned humans with horns from the waist up and giant, blue-scaled serpents from the waist down. They hail from the Paraelemental Plane of Ice and are the icy counterpart to the common &lt;a href=\"Salamander\"&gt;Salamander&lt;/a&gt;. The assigned class is &lt;a href=\"Water%20Elemental\"&gt;Water Elemental&lt;/a&gt;.\nInvolvement.\nIce Salamanders are a rare encounter but can be found in a select few areas:\nGameplay.\nOne or more Ice Salamanders will be summoned by a unique &lt;a href=\"Glabrezu%20%28TELTAN2%29\"&gt;glabrezu&lt;/a&gt; that is encountered on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt;. This creature (TELICESA.cre) has different &lt;a href=\"HP\"&gt;hit points&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"XP\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;, otherwise all other values are the same.\nThese creatures advance toward detected enemies and engage in melee combat with their spear weapon.\nTrivia.\nIce Salamanders were invented by Black Isle, first debuting in &lt;a href=\"Icewind%20Dale\"&gt;Icewind Dale&lt;/a&gt; before appearing in . The closest equivalent to such a creature in the tabletop of Advanced Dungeons &amp; Dragons is the \"Frost Salamander\", a creature originally from the Mystara setting which resembles a massive, multi-legged lizard - something like a blue-white &lt;a href=\"basilisk\"&gt;basilisk&lt;/a&gt; in appearance.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes only minor revisions to the Ice Salamander (including both varieties). First, it assigns a new default script for smarter tactical targeting, threat recognition, and opponent vulnerability assessments. Second, it changes the Spear weapon proficiency to 3 pips, and assigns 2 pips for two-handed weapon fighting style. This will improve the creature's melee combat abilities over the unmodified version.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Tower%20of%20Deception\"&gt;Tower of Deception&lt;/a&gt; mod populates one dungeon level with various monsters, and you will encounter both Fire and Ice Salamanders within."}
{"id": "27847", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27847", "title": "Ice Scepter", "text": "The Ice Scepter can be found in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt;. This item appears in ' and '.\nGameplay.\nDefeat the &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Golem%20%28Guardian%20of%20Ice%29\"&gt;Guardian of Ice&lt;/a&gt; to obtain this scepter from the creature's corpse.\nThe Ice scepter acts as a key that can unlock three gates on this dungeon level. These are:\nThe item is flagged as \"Critical\" and can't be sold.\nIt is one of four \"keys\" needed to free the captive &lt;a href=\"Chromatic%20Demon\"&gt;Chromatic Demon&lt;/a&gt; from the magical cage."}
{"id": "51290", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51290", "title": "Ice Shard", "text": "Ice Shard is an innate ability effect available to most &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Mephit\"&gt;Ice Mephit&lt;/a&gt; creatures in the game saga. \nEffects.\nThe spell effect is uninterruptable and takes almost no time to deploy. A bullet projectile is launched at a single target in range. It will strike the target and inflict damage. A &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Breath Weapon will half the damage.\nThe innate ability has level 3 spell power, and thus could be blocked by spell protections like &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;. The effect can also be blocked by magic resistance."}
{"id": "6245", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6245", "title": "Ice Star", "text": "Ice Star is an enchanted morning star +4 introduced into the game. \nGameplay.\nThe weapon is encountered in the game and is wielded in the main hand by the bhaalspawn &lt;a href=\"Gromnir%20Il-Khan\"&gt;Gromnir Il-Khan&lt;/a&gt; and can be acquired by defeating this Half-orc; who is alongside his various fighting lackeys. The player will find it on his corpse with other dropped loot.\nThe wielder receives a -4 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus applied to the attack roll with this weapon.\nUpon a successful hit on a target, the weapon inflicts 2d4+4 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt;, which can be modified by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;. In addition to the physical damage, each hit applies 1d4 &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;Cold damage&lt;/a&gt; as well. The cold damage is a non-magical &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20damage\"&gt;Elemental damage&lt;/a&gt; type, that is unaffected by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; or spell &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; protections.\nThe item also applies a passive +20% resistance to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt; (and Magical Fire damage). The wielder's portrait will display icon number 16 \"Protection from fire\"."}
{"id": "20265", "revid": "978785", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20265", "title": "Ice Star +4", "text": ""}
{"id": "5906", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5906", "title": "Ice Storm", "text": "Ice Storm allows the wizard to pummel his enemies with hail stones. It was originally available in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;, but the &lt;a href=\"Enhanced%20Edition\"&gt;Enhanced Edition&lt;/a&gt; ported it back into the first opus.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a single point on the area map to cast the spell at - and the spell manifests and radiates from that selected point.\nIt strikes 4 times in the second opus of the saga, but only 3 times in and .\nThe spell effects occur once per round, for every round that the creature is within the storm's area of effect. \nMoving out of the area stops exposure to the effect.\n&lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; can potentially block this spell, as well as a &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;SI: Evocation&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Mirroring\"&gt;Cloak of Mirroring&lt;/a&gt; will protect the wearer from the damaging effects of this spell.\nThere is no way to dispel this ice storm once it is manifested on the map, and it must run its course before expiring.\nMultiple Ice Storms can be piled on/stacked for extra damage in the same area of effect.\nBugs.\nThe spell is supposed to last four rounds, not three. This issue is already identified and revised by &lt;a href=\"The%20Enhanced%20Edition%20Fixpack%20%28EEFP%29\"&gt;The Enhanced Edition Fixpack (EEFP)&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Ice Storm\" inflicts 3d10 damage per round, and causes a 50% reduction in movement, plus a chance of slipping and falling.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects. See below for description:\nIce Storm\nLevel: 4\nSchool: Evocation\nRange: Long\nDuration: 4 rounds\nCasting Time: 4\nArea of Effect: 30\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen this spell is cast, great magical hailstones pound down for 4 rounds within a 30-foot radius of a point selected by the caster. Creatures within the area of effect have their movement speed reduced by 50% and receive 2d8 points of cold damage for each round they remain inside the storm."}
{"id": "46943", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46943", "title": "Ice Troll", "text": "An Ice Troll is a smaller troll from colder climes. A few of these can be found outside of the &lt;a href=\"De%27Arnise%20Keep\"&gt;de'Arnise Keep&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign.\nWith their affinity to cold, they are 75% resistant to &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;Cold damage&lt;/a&gt; (both magical and mundane).\nWhile unconscious and regenerating, the troll is impervious to cold, electrical, crushing, piercing, slashing and missile damage. Only acid, fire and magic may damage it."}
{"id": "29836", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29836", "title": "Ice mephit", "text": ""}
{"id": "14993", "revid": "25539483", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14993", "title": "Icewind Dale", "text": "Icewind Dale is a sister game series to \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\"\u00a0and \",\"\u00a0which was developed by &lt;a href=\"Black%20Isle\"&gt;Black Isle&lt;/a&gt; Studios.\nUnlike \"Baldur's Gate\", \"Icewind Dale\" doesn't feature NPC companions, but instead the player builds their own party from scratch. Other than that there are only very minor differences in gameplay, such as spells and the like. It was released in June 2000 and also got an Enhanced Edition by &lt;a href=\"Beamdog\"&gt;Beamdog&lt;/a&gt; which was released on October 30, 2014.\n\"Icewind Dale II\" was released on August 27, 2002. Unlike all other games in the family, it doesn't use Advanced Dungeons &amp; Dragons 2nd Edition rules but instead Dungeons &amp; Dragons 3rd Edition. There was a discussion about \"Icewind Dale II: Enhanced Edition\", but due to lost source code of the game, it proved too troublesome.\nGames.\nOver all there exist two main games in the series and one enhanced edition and two expansion packs for the first entry:\nSetting.\nLike \"Baldur's Gate\", \"Icewind Dale\" takes place in the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Realms\"&gt;Forgotten Realms&lt;/a&gt; and centers around the eponymous Icewind Dale region, including Kuldahar, Easthaven, Dorn's Deep and more, which lie at the very northern end of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt;.\nCross-references with Baldur's Gate.\nIn addition to general references regarding the shared setting, the games also share a number of game specific references between each other:"}
