{"id": "7241", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7241", "title": "Icingdeath", "text": "Icingdeath +3, also known as Scimitar +3, Frostbrand in the original games, is an enchanted &lt;a href=\"scimitar\"&gt;scimitar&lt;/a&gt;, wielded by the famous hero &lt;a href=\"Drizzt%20Do%27Urden\"&gt;Drizzt Do'Urden&lt;/a&gt; who appears in (SoA)(SoA).\nDrizzt also carries &lt;a href=\"Twinkle\"&gt;Twinkle&lt;/a&gt; in his other hand slot.\nGameplay.\nEquipping it gives +50% fire resistance \u2013 hence the classic name, &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Aforgottenrealms%3AFrostbrand\"&gt;Frostbrand&lt;/a&gt;. Gaining more than 100% fire resistance, by combination with other items, will cause a character to heal a % of incoming fire damage rather than being hurt by it.\n\"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAcquisition.\nThere are two possibilities to obtain this weapon, either by getting &lt;a href=\"Drizzt%20Do%27Urden\"&gt;Drizzt&lt;/a&gt; killed and taking it from his body or stealing it from him.\nAcquisition.\nThe only way to acquire this weapon is by getting &lt;a href=\"Drizzt%20Do%27Urden\"&gt;Drizzt&lt;/a&gt; killed and taking it from his body, which is an enormously difficult proposition."}
