{"id": "4215", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4215", "title": "Potion of Regeneration", "text": "Potion of Regeneration is available in all Baldur's Gate game versions.\nGameplay.\nUsable by any class character, when the potion is quaffed a text string will display \"\"gulp\" and the player character will have an icon displayed on their portrait, No. 87 \"Regenerating\"\". A sound effect is audible when first using the potion.\nFor a duration of 180 seconds (30 rounds or 3 Turns) the potion's &lt;a href=\"Regeneration\"&gt;Regeneration&lt;/a&gt; effect will restore 1 &lt;a href=\"Hit%20point\"&gt;Hit point&lt;/a&gt; every 3 seconds. When the duration expires, the icon is removed, and a sound effect is audible signifying the end of the regeneration.\nA &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect can remove this potion's effects from an imbiber before it expires.\nDrinking more than one of these potions has an additive effect. Each potion will each apply their regeneration independently for as long as it is functional.\nA character under the &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Haste effect&lt;/a&gt; will have an increased rate of regeneration.\nNote.\nDespite indicating that the potion will give a regeneration similar to a troll, it is not as powerful as that, but only 1/3 as rapid as the troll's innate regeneration."}
{"id": "4216", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4216", "title": "Potion of Stone Form", "text": "Potions of Stone Form set the &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;armor class&lt;/a&gt; of the creature to zero and give the imbiber a bonus of -3 to all &lt;a href=\"saving%20throw\"&gt;saving throw&lt;/a&gt;s, however this will lower &lt;a href=\"dexterity\"&gt;dexterity&lt;/a&gt; by three points. The effects last for 5 turns or until dispelled.\nThis potion has some visual effects, the imbibers look like they're made out of stone after drinking this.\nIt appears in all Bhaalspawn saga games."}
