{"id": "8382", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8382", "title": "Poultry Store", "text": "The Poultry Store is a building located in the district of &lt;a href=\"Central%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Central Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. Several &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28central%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;generic houses&lt;/a&gt; are located behind it and across the street. The &lt;a href=\"High%20House%20of%20Wonders\"&gt;High House of Wonders&lt;/a&gt; (accessible from &lt;a href=\"West%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;West Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;) is also across the street.\nIt appears to have been abandoned by the owner due to an army of rabid chickens that have taken over the store. The chickens will attack the party on sight. Casting a &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt; is a good quick way to eliminate the feathered menace, provided that you have given the character who will perform the action ample protection from any spillover effects.\nThe two lootable containers are empty."}
{"id": "12775", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12775", "title": "Power Attack", "text": "Power Attack\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; available to the &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"ranger\"&gt;ranger&lt;/a&gt;, and monk &lt;a href=\"monk\"&gt;monk&lt;/a&gt; classes.\nPrerequisite for: &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Strike\"&gt;Critical Strike&lt;/a&gt;\nGameplay.\nAll blows, regardless of what melee weapon is equipped will apply the &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; effect. \nIf dual wielding, both weapons will apply the stun. \nThe ability bypasses magic resistance and spell level protections (such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;). \nThe stun effect is non magical and cannot be dispelled.\nThe ability is not applied to missile weapons.\nMod content.\nIn the unmodified game, no opponents use Power Attack in the portion of the saga. \nWith the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod, eligible creatures/opponents are scripted to use selected &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; skills, including Power Attack."}
{"id": "4812", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4812", "title": "Power Word, Blind", "text": "Power Word, Blind will render sightless all hostile creatures within the area of effect for 6 rounds.\nGameplay.\nThe spell may be launched at a single enemy creature within the visual range of the caster. It's casting time of 1 means this spell is rarely disrupted.\nIf the target is under &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Invisibility\"&gt;Improved Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;, then that creature cannot be targeted with the spell.\nThe target and non-party creatures within 4 feet of the target are all exposed to the spell's effects.\nThe spell causes a &lt;a href=\"Blindness\"&gt;Blindness&lt;/a&gt; status effect on the affected creatures in the AoE.\nIf the spell doesn't fail, or for example, isn't blocked by magic resistance, then the combat log will display a text string stating \"Blinded\" applicable to each creature.\nThere is a sound audibled when the spell is cast, as well as 3D effect graphic/color glow played over each affected creature.\nParty members affected by this spell will have an icon in the character's portrait (No. 8) \"Blind\".\nThis is a spell with an 8 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; and can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;. The original target can also defend against this spell with a Spell Protection such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;. In addition, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity Conjuration&lt;/a&gt; will also block it.\nThe spell's effects are subject to being cured from &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Power Word, Blind\" is implemented differently than the BG game's version. The spellcaster selects one creature as the target center, and the effect spreads outward from the center, affecting creatures with the lowest hit point totals first; the spell can also be focused to affect only an individual creature. The spell affects up to 100 hit points of creatures; creatures who currently have 100 or more hit points are not affected and do not count against the number of creatures affected.\nMod Content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its area of effect, duration, effects, school and description:\nPower Word Blind\nLevel: 8\nSchool: Enchantment\nRange: Long\nDuration: Special\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen a Power Word Blind spell is uttered, any creature of the mage\u2019s choice within visual range becomes sightless. This lasts for 1 turn or until dispelled. Creatures with less than 6 Hit Dice are blinded permanently. All of the effects of blindness apply to the victims, including a decreased visibility range and -10 penalty to THAC0."}
{"id": "4811", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4811", "title": "Power Word, Kill", "text": "When a wizard utters Power Word, Kill, the target may instantly die.\nGameplay.\nThe caster designates a single creature in range using the targeting cursor. and then utters the power word.\nThe targeted creature is now exposed to the instant death effect, which will only apply to a target that currently has a 59 or fewer current &lt;a href=\"Hit%20point\"&gt;Hit point&lt;/a&gt; value.\nThe target is not allowed a saving throw.\nIf the target is eligible to be affected by this spell, a 3D effect and brief color glow animation renders upon the target.\nOtherwise, a text will display reading \"Unaffected by effects from Power Word, Kill\".\nShould the creature be killed, the corpse is seen laying on the ground immediately, dead and final.\n&lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; can block this spell.\nThis spell can also be negated by &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Conjuration&lt;/a&gt;.\nA &lt;a href=\"Spell%20protections%20type\"&gt;Spell protections type&lt;/a&gt; defense that has the capacity to deflect/turn a 9 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; spell effect can also block this spell, such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;.\nA creature protected from instant death effects, such as with &lt;a href=\"Death%20Ward\"&gt;Death Ward&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Avoid%20Death\"&gt;Avoid Death&lt;/a&gt; won't be killed, although the spell's animation will still render over the creature.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Power Word, Kill\" is implemented differently than the BG Game's version. For instance, the spell has a 10' radius area of effect. The power word kills either one creature with up to 60 hit points, or multiple creatures with 10 or fewer hit points each, to a maximum of 120 hit points total. The option to attack a single creature or multiple creatures must be stated ahead of casting the spell. \nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its Spell School, saving throw applicability, effects and description. See below:\nPower Word Kill\nLevel: 9\nSchool: Enchantment\nRange: Long\nDuration: Instant\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: Special\nWhen a Power Word Kill spell is uttered, one creature targeted by the caster is slain. Creatures who currently have 60 or more hit points can save vs. spell to avoid the effects, but those with 1 to 59 hit points are powerless to resist. Even if the creature\u2019s maximum hit points are higher than 60, its current hit points are used for this determination."}
{"id": "46185", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46185", "title": "Power Word, Kill (effect)", "text": "Power word, kill is a status effect that kills whichever creature it is applied to if they have strictly less than 60 current &lt;a href=\"Hit%20point\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt;, unless they are explicitly immune to it.\nNote: It is not the only status effect that kills a creature instantly -- other contenders are &lt;a href=\"Disintegrate%20effect\"&gt;Disintegrate&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Kill%20target\"&gt;Kill target&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Slay\"&gt;Slay&lt;/a&gt;. The party should be immune to them in Story mode.\nGameplay.\nAs is true with all status effects, application details vary depending on source -- what is causing the effect. When the effect cannot be resisted explicitly, it is useful to rely on source-specific defences.\nFor example, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; would work against the level 9 spell &lt;a href=\"Power%20Word%2C%20Kill\"&gt;Power Word Kill&lt;/a&gt; but not against &lt;a href=\"Symbol%2C%20Death%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Symbol Death&lt;/a&gt;. On the other hand &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity:Conjuration&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Mirroring\"&gt;Cloak of Mirroring&lt;/a&gt; would work on both. Yet none of these defences actually protect from the Power word kill effect: they prevent the source from getting a shot at applying it on a character."}
{"id": "4813", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4813", "title": "Power Word, Silence", "text": "Power Word, Silence gives a wizard the ability to silence an individual for seven rounds. A neutral target will not turn hostile.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a single creature in range to direct this spell at, using the targeting cursor.\nThe power word is spoken, and the targeted creature is immediately exposed to the spell's effects.\nThis single target \"disabling type \"spell will implement the &lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;Opcode&lt;/a&gt; 38 State: &lt;a href=\"Silence\"&gt;Silence&lt;/a&gt; effect on any creature not protected from that status effect.\nIf the spell lands, a text message display on the combat log will read \"\"Silence\". A sound effect is audibled, 3D Graphics effect (SPPOWWRD) and a Color Glow RGB effect plays over the target.\nA player character will also display an Icon (No. 34) titled \"Silenced\"\" on their portrait.\n&lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; can block this spell, and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Conjuration&lt;/a&gt; will negate it.\nThe spell is a &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 6 spell, thus certain spell protections can also deflect it, such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhile many hostile mages will use &lt;a href=\"Vocalize\"&gt;Vocalize&lt;/a&gt; to counter the effects, it is very effective against &lt;a href=\"Cleric\"&gt;Clerics&lt;/a&gt; who don't have the vocalize spell.\nCasting this spell upon a neutral creature won't make them hostile, even if the spell succeeds.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its duration and school. See below for description:\nPower Word Silence\nLevel: 6\nSchool: Enchantment\nRange: Long\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen a Power Word Silence spell is uttered, the target creature becomes unable make any sound for 1 turn. This silence completely foils any spellcasting because it prevents the target from uttering the required verbal components. The only counters to this spell are a dispel magic or Vocalize."}
{"id": "4815", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4815", "title": "Power Word, Sleep", "text": "When Power Word, Sleep is cast, the target creature is instantly driven into a comatose slumber.\nGameplay.\nThe caster utters the power word and is directed at a single creature in range, use the targeting cursor to designate the creature.\nIf the target currently has 19 or less current hit points it is affected by the spell, no saving throw is allowed.\nThe targeted creature will show a distinctive \"power word\" 3D effect and a brief color glow, but only if their current HP is below the threshold.\nThis special status effect causes makes the target &lt;a href=\"Unconscious\"&gt;Unconscious&lt;/a&gt; and as a result the victim is &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt; for the spell's duration and can end sooner if the creature suffers any damage.\nThe game seems to have omitted coding this spell to allow &lt;a href=\"Elf\"&gt;Elf&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Half-elf\"&gt;Half-elf&lt;/a&gt; creatures their respective 90 and 35% resistance to sleep magic.\nImmunity to the Sleep effect implies immunity to \"Power Word, Sleep\"'s special effect.\nThis spell can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and negated by &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Conjuration&lt;/a&gt;.\nAdditionally, any &lt;a href=\"Spell%20protections%20type\"&gt;Spell protections type&lt;/a&gt; defense can absorb/turn the spell, such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Minor Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;.\nPower Word, Sleep is flagged as a \"hostile\" spell. Casting it on a neutral creature will make the target hostile (even if it doesn't work), and possibly others in the vicinity.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Power Word, Sleep\" differs from the BG game's implementation. The Bioware version of the spell made the power word weaker and only a single target spell, while the Pen and Paper version is potentially more powerful than the 1st-level Wizard \"Sleep\" spell. See the External link for further reading.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects and school. Can affect creatures with 20 plus HP now. See below for description:\nPower Word Sleep\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Enchantment\nRange: Long\nDuration: 5 rounds\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: Spell negates\nWhen a wizard utters this power word, he causes a comatose slumber to come upon one creature. Creatures who currently have 20 or more hit points can save vs. spell to avoid the effects, but those with 1 to 19 hit points are powerless to resist. Elves and half-elves are particularly resistant to sleep effects, while the undead and certain other creatures such as dragons and elementals are completely immune to magically induced sleep.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Power Word, Sleep\" differs from the BG game's implementation. The Bioware version of the spell made the power word weaker and only a single target spell, while the Pen and Paper version is more powerful than the 1st-level Wizard \"Sleep\" spell. See the External link for further reading."}
{"id": "4814", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4814", "title": "Power Word, Stun", "text": "Power Word, Stun allows a wizard to stun any creature with 89 or less Hit Points.\nGameplay.\nThe caster designates a single creature in range using the targeting cursor. and then utters the power word.\nThe targeted creature is now exposed to the instant &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; effect, which will only apply to a target that currently has a 89 or fewer current &lt;a href=\"Hit%20point\"&gt;Hit point&lt;/a&gt; value.\nThe target is not allowed a saving throw.\nIf the target is eligible to be affected by this spell, a 3D effect and brief color glow animation renders upon the target.\nOtherwise, a text will display reading \"Unaffected by effects from Power Word, Stun\".\nIf the creature is immune to the Stun status effect, there will be no text, nor a saving throw, and the spell animation will still render over the target - however, the target will just carry on as normal, completely unaffected.\nA victim affected by the stun effect is &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt; for the spell's duration.\nA party member affected by this spell will show an icon (No. 55) titled \"Stun\" on their portrait.\n&lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; can block this spell.\nThis spell can also be negated by &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Conjuration&lt;/a&gt;.\nA &lt;a href=\"Spell%20protections%20type\"&gt;Spell protections type&lt;/a&gt; defense that has the capacity to deflect/turn a 7 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; spell effect can also block this spell, such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Minor Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;.\nA special &lt;a href=\"status%20effect\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; is inflicted that itself causes a &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; effect on a creature with up to 89 current &lt;a href=\"Hit%20point\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; for the duration in the spell description.\nImmunity to the Stun effect implies immunity to \"Power Word, Stun\"'s special effect.\nA neutral creature exposed to this spell, even if it is stunned with the effect, won't turn hostile, and won't illicit a response from other nearby NOC's.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Power Word, Stun\" is implemented almost identically to the BG Game's version. Maximum movement for a stunned creature is one-third the creature's rate, or 3, whichever is less. Barred are all forms of communication, spell use, item and innate ability use, psionics, fighting, or free movement. \nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its Spell School, effects and description. See below:\nPower Word Stun\nLevel: 7\nSchool: Enchantment\nRange: Long\nDuration: Special\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen a Power Word Stun spell is uttered, any creature of the mage\u2019s choice within visual range is stunned for a length of time dependent upon its current hit points. Creatures with 1 to 29 hit points are stunned for 4d4 rounds, while those with 30 to 59 are stunned for 2d4 rounds, those with 60 to 89 are stunned for 1d4 rounds, and those with 90 or more are stunned for 1 round. Note that if a creature is weakened so that its hit points are below its usual maximum, its current number of hit points is used to determine the spell\u2019s effect."}
