{"id": "11466", "revid": "284203", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11466", "title": "Prebek", "text": "Prebek is an apprentice of the mad &lt;a href=\"Zhentarim\"&gt;Zhentarim&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"necromancer\"&gt;necromancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Xzar\"&gt;Xzar&lt;/a&gt; and is paired with another apprentice named &lt;a href=\"Sanasha\"&gt;Sanasha&lt;/a&gt;. Upon entry into &lt;a href=\"Prebek%27s%20House\"&gt;his house&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Athkatla Docks&lt;/a&gt;, Sanasha will cry out in alarm, and both apprentices will have dialogue with each other, then turn hostile. The fight is unavoidable.\nInteractions.\n&lt;a href=\"Rylock\"&gt;Rylock&lt;/a&gt;, a member of the &lt;a href=\"Harpers\"&gt;Harpers&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;, tasks &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and their &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; with killing Prebek, his accomplice and his 'creations' (which appear to be nothing more than ordinary &lt;a href=\"Goblin%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Goblin&lt;/a&gt;s). This is changed if you install the &lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Unfinished Business (Baldur's Gate II)&lt;/a&gt; mod, which restores the original creatures into the home, as well as the scimitar &lt;a href=\"Shazzellim\"&gt;Shazzellim&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nPeople involved.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises Prebek, especially with the \"Smarter Mages\" component. Prebek is now an Invoker, and has a new array of memorized spells. A default SCS AI script is assigned for smarter tactical behavior. He will deploy a contingency that raises some defensive protections on himself at the outset of hostilities. Prebek has a loaded &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; ready to fire on himself with &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Blur\"&gt;Blur&lt;/a&gt;. SCS will automatically launche several spells that are shown to be cast previously including &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt;. After that, will attempt a &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt;. then perhaps an &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; on self, and then a &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt; or other offensive Invocation spell casts at vulnerable party members in sight. "}
{"id": "13218", "revid": "284186", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13218", "title": "Prebek's House", "text": "Prebek's House is a house in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Docks%20District\"&gt;Docks District&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nInside are Prebek and Sanash, apprentices to &lt;a href=\"Xzar\"&gt;Xzar&lt;/a&gt;, and a few \"goblins.\" The pair have a brief debate about what they should do about your intrusion, and how this might be another \"test\" by their \"master\" but they eventually agree that they should attack.\nThere are three locked and trapped containers to loot, after the battle. The traps deal a fair quantity of damage, beware.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod and the \"Smarter Mages\" component revises Prebek and Sanasha. They both have contingency defensive spells that will trigger at the start of hostilities, including a Spell Protection on each mage. Each has a Minor Sequencer prepared and ready to launch. They'll put up a stiffer fight than the unmodded game.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Unfinished Business (Baldur's Gate II)&lt;/a&gt; Mod restores some of the guardian creatures inside this home. The goblins are replaced by two &lt;a href=\"Ghast\"&gt;Ghast&lt;/a&gt;s The mod also restores the Scimitar &lt;a href=\"Shazzellim\"&gt;Shazzellim&lt;/a&gt; and is inside the Home for you to find, either on a body or in a container.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Construction%20for%20Spellcasters\"&gt;Golem Construction for Spellcasters&lt;/a&gt; mod adds a &lt;a href=\"Flesh%20Golem\"&gt;Flesh Golem&lt;/a&gt; to the guardians within."}
