{"id": "6343", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6343", "title": "Prelate Wessalen", "text": "Prelate Wessalen is the high ecclesiastical dignitary of the &lt;a href=\"Most%20Noble%20Order%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart\"&gt;Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;. He can be found within his office in the &lt;a href=\"Most%20Noble%20Order%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart%20building\"&gt;Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart building&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe party may find the Prelate in his office with the Radiant Heart headquarters.\nInitiate conversation with him for dialogue - the dialogue offered will change depending on previous actions performed and quests assigned to the party.\nDuring &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; may attempt to gain assistance from the Prelate regarding &lt;a href=\"The%20final%20battle%20with%20Bodhi\"&gt;The final battle with Bodhi&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe may or may not agree to provide a small group of knights to fight alongside the party in the &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;catacombs&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Graveyard District&lt;/a&gt; - this is determined by previous actions taken by &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;, and whether or not the party was allied with Bodhi previously. \nCertain dialogue can favorably persuade Wessalen or shutter the requested help, regardless of previous decisions taken.\nIf he grants assistance, the journal registers the following:\nOn the other hand, if the Prelate refuses help, the journal says:\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises the Prelate, providing a new AI script commensurate with his advanced experience level.\nWeapon proficiencies changed to two pips in Two-handed Sword and two pips in two-handed weapon style - three potions are also given for use in combat for healing and ability boosting.\nDepending on the player's game difficulty selection, the Prelate will have use of &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; powers including &lt;a href=\"Whirlwind%20Attack\"&gt;Whirlwind Attack&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Whirlwind%20Attack\"&gt;Greater Whirlwind Attack&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Deva\"&gt;Summon Deva&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Alternatives\"&gt;Alternatives&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some additions to dialogue and triggers for those dialogue paths."}
