{"id": "42209", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42209", "title": "Priest of Cyric (North Forest)", "text": "Priest of Cyric is a cleric class male human encountered during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"North%20Forest%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;North Forest (Shadows of Amn)&lt;/a&gt; area.\nGameplay.\nThis priest is part of an unknown mixed group of adventurers or perhaps mercenaries encountered in about the center of the area map. The whole group is hostile to any intruders that are detected.\nThe priest will let loose a chain of protective buffs when hostilities begin, to include &lt;a href=\"Strength%20of%20One\"&gt;Strength of One&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chant\"&gt;Chant&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;. Next will be an attempted &lt;a href=\"Death%20Ward\"&gt;Death Ward&lt;/a&gt; if the cleric spots a fighter class enemy.\nNow he'll go on the offensive with an &lt;a href=\"Earthquake\"&gt;Earthquake&lt;/a&gt;, then a &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Strike\"&gt;Flame Strike&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Fear\"&gt;Cloak of Fear&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Hold Person (priest)&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen the priest is wounded to a set threshold percentage, he'll try a &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Serious%20Wounds\"&gt;Cure Serious Wounds&lt;/a&gt;. and if near death a &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a new default Smarter Priest AI script for potion use, and spell casting choice and targeting. A revised spell book is provided. Weapon proficiencies are adjusted to 1 pip in mace and two-weapon style.\nThe cleric will have the following \"previously cast\" spells at the outset of battle: &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Resistance%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Magic Resistance (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe cleric carries a priest scroll in inventory, as well as a random potion for quaffing by script.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"https%3A//github.com/RoxanneSHS/LensHunt\"&gt;The Broken Lanthorn&lt;/a&gt; mod installed - this cleric has one of the missing lens pieces needed to repair/complete the &lt;a href=\"Rhynn%20Lanthorn\"&gt;Rhynn Lanthorn&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "48955", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48955", "title": "Priest of Cyric (Slaver Stockade)", "text": "This Priest of Cyric is found in the lower storage room with access to the &lt;a href=\"Sewers%20%28Slums%20District%29\"&gt;Sewers&lt;/a&gt; within the &lt;a href=\"Slaver%20Stockade\"&gt;Slaver Stockade&lt;/a&gt; which is located in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Slums District.&lt;/a&gt; \nGameplay.\nThis priest is accompanied by several other slavers in this room.\nWhen he detects an enemy, he'll near instantly release his prepared spell chain, as shown in the InfoBox.\nIt's likely that nearby cohorts will benefit from these buffs if he's able to release the spells without being disrupted. The &lt;a href=\"Defensive%20Harmony\"&gt;Defensive Harmony&lt;/a&gt; can't be interrupted.\nFrom this point on he'll behave as a divine caster, potentially healing self and allies, and casting disabling spells at enemies, and potentially animating skeleton creatures to help.\nHe wears no armor and carries no weapons. Spells are all he has to thwart his enemy. If he has cast all of his spells and hasn't been killed, he will attack the closest enemy with his &lt;a href=\"Fist\"&gt;Fist&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod alters the Priest's Ai with an SCS \"Smarter Cleric\" script and changes most memorized spells. If the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod is installed, then the spells will be replaced with SR versions. If melee combat is necessary, the priest will use a magically created &lt;a href=\"Spiritual%20Hammer\"&gt;Spiritual Hammer&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "47483", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47483", "title": "Priest of Gond", "text": "This Priest of Gond is found wandering about in the &lt;a href=\"High%20House%20of%20Wonders\"&gt;High House of Wonders&lt;/a&gt; located in &lt;a href=\"West%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;West Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. He offers the basic temple services along with a limited amount of potions and scrolls."}
{"id": "51403", "revid": "39149728", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51403", "title": "Priest of Helm", "text": "Priest of Helm is one of the five class kits available to &lt;a href=\"Cleric\"&gt;Cleric&lt;/a&gt;. Characters choosing this kit option devote themselves to worshipping &lt;a href=\"Helm\"&gt;Helm&lt;/a&gt;, \"the Watcher\" and have &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt; restrictions that differ based on game version.\nAs a general rule, cleric kits gain two bonus special abilities each without any added penalties compared to the base class, so it is generally advisable to always choose a kit that suits your alignment preferences over the \"vanilla\" cleric class.\nThe Priest of Helm is able to heal others and one of the four classes which can cast &lt;a href=\"Priest%20spells%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;priest spells&lt;/a&gt;. They can wear all kinds of armor, just like warriors, except mages robes, but their ethos prohibits them from using weapons and missiles with sharp points &amp; edges and start with two weapon skill points fewer.\nAbility Scores.\nNote: For the information of this table the human race was used, because they have no character bonuses/penalties related to race and therefore act like a 'neutral'. For other races this may be slightly different. See &lt;a href=\"Ability%20Scores\"&gt;Ability Scores&lt;/a&gt; for more information.\nTurn Undead.\nPriest and paladins have the ability turn undead creatures. When this mode is activated and undead creatures are in range of the character, there is a possibility they will stop attacking their targets and run away from the character until the effect is worn off. Whenever the priest or paladins gains a level, this mode will become more powerful. As good-aligned priests, Priests of Helm may use this mode to destroy the undead instantly.\nPriest Spells.\nClerics can use priest spells and only the following spells are available to clerics. Some spells are not available for priests, depending on the alignment the character started with, not the alignment the character currently has.\nClass abilities.\nPriests of Helm have two innate :\nHoly Symbol.\nUpon reaching level 24, Priests of Helm receive &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Symbol%20of%20Helm\"&gt;his holy symbol&lt;/a&gt; which grants bonus lvl 6 and lvl 7 spell slots - one per each level - among other things.\nSpell progression.\nClerics whose wisdom is lower than 18, can use lvl 7 spells in ."}
{"id": "13581", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13581", "title": "Priest of Helm (creature)", "text": "A Priest of Helm can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Helm%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;Temple of Helm&lt;/a&gt; located in the city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and in the &lt;a href=\"Helmite%20Camp\"&gt;Helmite Camp&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis Priest of Helm provides all of the typical services of the temple.\nThis Priest of Helm can be found escorting &lt;a href=\"Hokkney%20of%20Tyr\"&gt;Hokkney of Tyr&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Helmite%20Camp\"&gt;Helmite Camp&lt;/a&gt;. He provides no services and carries no inventory."}
{"id": "47409", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47409", "title": "Priest of Ilmater (Baldur's Gate)", "text": "This Priest of Ilmater is found in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Ilmater\"&gt;Temple of Ilmater&lt;/a&gt; which is located in the western section of &lt;a href=\"Northeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Northeast Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. He only appears during &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Seven\"&gt;Chapter Seven&lt;/a&gt;. He'll offer to show you his secret passage to the &lt;a href=\"Undercellar\"&gt;Undercellar&lt;/a&gt; either through the initial dialogue, if you choose the right dialogue path, or if you speak to him again after the first dialogue attempt has ended.\nThis is a one-way travel action and there is no way to get back to the temple unless you exit back to the outside. The priest doesn't actually accompany you when you exit into the Underceller and he can still be found in the temple if you return to it.\nThe priest doesn't offer any services for the temple."}
{"id": "47411", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47411", "title": "Priest of Ilmater (Shadows of Amn)", "text": "This same Priest of Ilmater can be found in two places at once during the \"\" campaign.\nLocations.\nThe party may first meet him in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Ilmater%20%28Waukeen%27s%20Promenade%29\"&gt;Temple of Ilmater (Waukeen's Promenade)&lt;/a&gt; after emerging from &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irenicus's Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;. He can be found again at the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Ilmater%20%28Slums%20District%29\"&gt;Temple of Ilmater (Slums District)&lt;/a&gt; atop the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt;. Because it is the same person, if you purchase from his shop in one district, the stock in his shop in the other district will also be depleted, as they share the same store.\nTemple Services.\nThe Temple Shop sells potions, scrolls, and identifies objects. The priest also administers temple services which accepts donations and has the usual restorative cures."}
{"id": "14120", "revid": "39149728", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14120", "title": "Priest of Lathander", "text": "Priest of Lathander is one of the five class kits available to &lt;a href=\"Cleric\"&gt;Cleric&lt;/a&gt;. Characters choosing this kit option devote themselves to worshipping &lt;a href=\"Lathander\"&gt;Lathander&lt;/a&gt;, the Morninglord and are restricted to taking a good &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt;, with True Neutral also available in the \"Enhanced Editions\".\nAs a general rule, cleric kits gain two bonus special abilities each without any added penalties compared to the base class, so it is generally advisable to always choose a kit that suits your alignment preferences over the \"vanilla\" cleric class.\nThe Priest of Lathander is able to heal others and one of the four classes which can cast &lt;a href=\"Priest%20spells%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;priest spells&lt;/a&gt;. They can wear all kinds of armor, just like warriors, except mages robes, but their ethos prohibits them from using weapons and missiles with sharp points &amp; edges and start with two weapon skill points fewer.\nAbility Scores.\nNote: For the information of this table the human race was used, because they have no character bonuses/penalties related to race and therefore act like a 'neutral'. For other races this may be slightly different. See &lt;a href=\"Ability%20Scores\"&gt;Ability Scores&lt;/a&gt; for more information.\nTurn Undead.\nPriest and paladins have the ability turn undead creatures. When this mode is activated and undead creatures are in range of the character, there is a possibility they will stop attacking their targets and run away from the character until the effect is worn off. Whenever the priest or paladins gains a level, this mode will become more powerful. As good-aligned priests, Priests of Lathander may use this mode to destroy the undead instantly.\nPriest Spells.\nClerics can use priest spells and only the following spells are available to clerics. Some spells are not available for priests, depending on the alignment the character started with, not the alignment the character currently has.\nClass abilities.\nPriests of Lathander have two innate :\nHoly Symbol.\nUpon reaching level 24, Priests of Lathander receive &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Symbol%20of%20Lathander\"&gt;his holy symbol&lt;/a&gt; which grants bonus lvl 6 and lvl 7 spell slots - one per each level - among other things.\nSpell progression.\nClerics whose wisdom is lower than 18, can use lvl 7 spells in ."}
{"id": "29831", "revid": "36269295", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29831", "title": "Priest of Oghma (Baldur's Gate)", "text": "Priests of Oghma are only found within the walls of &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt; and none are found anywhere else in the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;game&lt;/a&gt;. During the &lt;a href=\"Prologue\"&gt;Prologue&lt;/a&gt; one can be found within the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Oghma%20%28Candlekeep%29\"&gt;Temple of Oghma&lt;/a&gt; and a second priest is inside the &lt;a href=\"clinic\"&gt;clinic&lt;/a&gt;. During &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Six\"&gt;Chapter Six&lt;/a&gt; the same priest is still in the temple while a second priest can be found inside the &lt;a href=\"Priests%27%20Quarters\"&gt;Priests' Quarters&lt;/a&gt;. Six more are found within the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Library\"&gt;library&lt;/a&gt; on floors two through five.\nAs a neutral &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;aligned&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 &lt;a href=\"Lawful%20neutral\"&gt;lawful&lt;/a&gt; in the original Baldur's Gate, &lt;a href=\"true%20neutral\"&gt;true&lt;/a&gt; in the \"\" \u2013 priest of The Lord of Knowledge, he's eager to share his &lt;a href=\"Oghma\"&gt;patron's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"wisdom\"&gt;wisdom&lt;/a&gt; with people &lt;a href=\"Charmed\"&gt;he likes&lt;/a&gt;.\nTemple of Oghma.\n&lt;br&gt;\nThe priest found in the temple offers his services during the prologue and in chapter six. He is able to &lt;a href=\"identify\"&gt;identify&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt;s, accepts donations, offer some healing capabilities, and has the normal temple complement of &lt;a href=\"potions\"&gt;potions&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"scrolls\"&gt;scrolls&lt;/a&gt; available, with no restocking between .\nIn BGEE, this is also the priest who appears at the Candlekeep main gate to &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Light%20Wounds%20%28spell%29\"&gt;heal the wounds&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;, whether injured or not, when &lt;a href=\"Gorion\"&gt;Gorion&lt;/a&gt; and his foster-child are ready to leave at the end of the prologue.\nClinic.\n&lt;br&gt;\nA \"Priest of Oghma\" can be found tending to patients in the clinic in Candlekeep during the prologue.\nAs one \"never can tell\", the caring priest offers a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Healing&lt;/a&gt; once if addressed; this can be accepted or declined. He carries a second one in his inventory; both potions can be &lt;a href=\"pickpocket\"&gt;pickpocket&lt;/a&gt;ed.\nConstantly on the move inside the clinic, he might witness a thief stealing a third potion of healing from the locked desk in the sleeping cubicle and summon a &lt;a href=\"watcher\"&gt;watcher&lt;/a&gt;.\nLibrary.\n&lt;br&gt;\nSeveral priests are found throughout the library between the second and fifth floors when the library becomes accessible in chapter six. One each is found standing between the stairs and a desk on floors two through five and serves as the coordinator for that particular floor. A second priest is found on floors two and four and will provide some insightful information on a few of the current guests found within the library.\nPriest's Quarters.\n&lt;br&gt;\nAlso in chapter six, a \"Priest of Oghma\" is observed studying a dead cat in the &lt;a href=\"Priests%27%20Quarters\"&gt;Priests' Quarters&lt;/a&gt;. Continued pestering results in the priest revealing its true &lt;a href=\"Doppelganger\"&gt;self&lt;/a&gt; \u2013\nand, when it is dealt with, the following &lt;a href=\"Journal\"&gt;Journal&lt;/a&gt; entry:"}
{"id": "47478", "revid": "283601", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47478", "title": "Priest of Oghma (Shadows of Amn)", "text": "This Priest of Oghma is found inside the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Oghma%20%28Athkatla%29\"&gt;Temple of Oghma&lt;/a&gt; that's located in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Docks District&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nTake advantage of the Priest's freely offered knowledge base. Certain topics of concern to the party can be further discussed with this learned man, possibly providing actual factual information - unlike the innuendo and rumors often circulated at this stage of the saga. Ask about the Cowled Wizards and the \"guild war\".\nMuch later in the party's adventures, especially after defeating &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; in chapter 6 - it is likely that &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; may be seeking a means to resurrect and cure vampirism on one the party' companions. If the party spoke with &lt;a href=\"Elhan\"&gt;Elhan&lt;/a&gt; and his &lt;a href=\"Elven%20War%20Sage\"&gt;Elven War Sage&lt;/a&gt; about this subject - they referred to the worshippers of &lt;a href=\"Oghma\"&gt;Oghma&lt;/a&gt; as a source of information. \nAssuming the party travelled to this temple and conferred with the priest on the subject - it does in fact lead to more information. The priest may say:\nWith that information, the next logical place to explore further information gathering is in the Umar Hills. It's possible if the party has visited that location and the village of Imnesvale on prior travels, that some of the merchants near or inside the &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale%20Inn\"&gt;Imnesvale Inn&lt;/a&gt; may be a book dealer or merchant.\nThe priest runs the temple store function from which the party can buy potions, scrolls and identify items. He also administers temple services, including donations and the typical restorative cures offered by most temples.\nTemple services.\nCures.\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"http%3A//shsforums.net/files/file/1109-klatu-tweaks-and-fixes/\"&gt;Klatu Tweaks and Fixes&lt;/a&gt; modification has a component that adds content for the Temple and Priest of Oghma: The Manual of War&lt;br&gt;\nIntroduces an ancient magical tome that, with some effort (HINT: and some WISDOM), can grant the reader extraordinary powers. The book can be found in the ruins of Ulcaster, in Irenicus' Dungeon (if the player has it in their possession on import) or in the depths of Watcher's Keep (if it was not already found earlier). But simply finding it is not enough. Try talking to the local scholars and mages to unlock its powers. "}
{"id": "14119", "revid": "39149728", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14119", "title": "Priest of Talos", "text": "Priest of Talos is one of the five class kits to &lt;a href=\"Cleric\"&gt;Cleric&lt;/a&gt;. Characters choosing this kit option devote themselves to worshipping &lt;a href=\"Talos\"&gt;Talos&lt;/a&gt;, the Storm Lord and has &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt; restrictions which differ based on game version.\nAs a general rule, cleric kits gain two bonus special abilities each without any added penalties compared to the base class, so it is generally advisable to always choose a kit that suits your alignment preferences over the \"vanilla\" cleric class.\nThe Priest of Talos is able to heal others and one of the four classes which can cast &lt;a href=\"Priest%20spells%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;priest spells&lt;/a&gt;. They can wear all kinds of armor, just like warriors, except mages robes, but their ethos prohibites them from using weapons and missiles with sharp points &amp; edges and start with two weapon skill points fewer.\nAbility Scores.\nNote: For the information of this table the human race was used, because they have no character bonunes/penalties related to race and therefore act like a 'neutral'. For other races this may be slightly different. See &lt;a href=\"Ability%20Scores\"&gt;Ability Scores&lt;/a&gt; for more information.\nTurn undead.\nPriest and paladins have the ability turn undead creatures. When this mode is activated and undead creatures are in range of the character, there is a possibility they will stop attacking their targets and run away from the character until the effect is worn off. As many Priests of Talos are evil-aligned, they can use it to control the undead for a limited amount of time as temporary allies. After this runs out, the undead will become hostile to the party.\nPriest Spells.\nClerics can use priest spells and only the following spells are available to clerics. Some spells are not available for priests, depending on the alignment the character started with, not the alignment the character currently has.\nBonus Spells.\nPriests of Talos are also able to cast the following spells as special ability:\nHoly Symbol.\nUpon reaching level 24, Priests of Talos receive &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Symbol%20of%20Talos\"&gt;his holy symbol&lt;/a&gt; which grants bonus lvl 6 and lvl 7 spell slots - one per each level - among other things.\nSpell progression.\nNotes:\nPriest gain additional spell slots for their &lt;a href=\"wisdom\"&gt;wisdom&lt;/a&gt;.\n+Usable by priest whose wisdom is 17 or higher\nUsable by priest whose wisdom is 18 or highe.\nClerics whose wisdom is lower than 18, can use lvl 7 spells in ."}
{"id": "46745", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46745", "title": "Priest of Tempus", "text": "Priest of Tempus is one of five class kits to &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;. Characters choosing this kit option devote themselves to worshipping &lt;a href=\"Tempus\"&gt;Tempus&lt;/a&gt;, the Lord of Battle and are restricted to taking an chaotic or true neutral &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt;. As general rule the cleric kits get two special abilities without penalties, making vanilla cleric of same alignment better only for (potentially) role-playing.\nThe Priest of Tempus is able to heal others and one of the four classes which can cast &lt;a href=\"Priest%20spells%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;priest spells&lt;/a&gt;. They can wear all kinds of armor, just like warriors, except mages robes, but their ethos prohibits them from using weapons and missiles with sharp points &amp; edges and start with two weapon skill points fewer.\nAbility Scores.\nNote: For the information of this table the human race was used, because they have no character bonuses/penalties related to race and therefore act like a 'neutral'. For other races this may be slightly different. See &lt;a href=\"Ability%20Scores\"&gt;Ability Scores&lt;/a&gt; for more information.\nTurn Undead.\nPriest and paladins have the ability turn undead creatures. When this mode is activated and undead creatures are in range of the character, there is a possibility they will stop attacking their targets and run away from the character until the effect is worn off. Priests of Tempus are evil-aligned, they can use it to control the undead for a limited amount of time as temporary allies. After this runs out, the undead will become hostile to the party.\nPriest Spells.\nClerics can use priest spells and only the following spells are available to clerics. Some spells are not available for priests, depending on the alignment the character started with, not the alignment the character currently has.\nBonus spells.\nPriests of Tempus gain ability to cast following spells as special abilities:\nThey start with one usage of both abilities\nHoly Symbol.\nAfter reaching level 24, priest gain the &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Symbol%20of%20Tempus\"&gt;Holy Symbol of Tempus&lt;/a&gt;.\nSpell Progression.\nNotes: Priest gain additional spell slots for their &lt;a href=\"wisdom\"&gt;wisdom&lt;/a&gt;. +Usable by priest whose wisdom is 17 or higher ++Usable by priest whose wisdom is 18 or higher.\nClerics whose wisdom is lower than 18, can use level 7 spells in ."}
{"id": "51750", "revid": "242442", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51750", "title": "Priest of Tyr", "text": "Priest of Tyr is one of five class kits to &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;. Characters choosing this kit option devote themselves to worshipping &lt;a href=\"Tyr\"&gt;Tyr&lt;/a&gt;, the Lord of Justice. The &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignments&lt;/a&gt; they are restricted to taking are either Lawful Good, Neutral Good, or Lawful Neutral. \nAs general rule the cleric kits get two special abilities without penalties, making vanilla cleric of same alignment better only for (potentially) role-playing.\nThe Priest of Tyr is able to heal others and one of the four classes which can cast &lt;a href=\"Priest%20spells%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;priest spells&lt;/a&gt;. They can wear all kinds of armor, just like warriors, except mages robes, but their ethos prohibits them from using weapons and missiles with sharp points &amp; edges and start with two weapon skill points fewer.\nAbility Scores.\nNote: For the information of this table the human race was used, because they have no character bonuses/penalties related to race and therefore act like a 'neutral'. For other races this may be slightly different. See &lt;a href=\"Ability%20Scores\"&gt;Ability Scores&lt;/a&gt; for more information.\nTurn Undead.\nPriest and paladins have the ability turn undead creatures. When this mode is activated and undead creatures are in range of the character, there is a possibility they will stop attacking their targets and run away from the character until the effect is worn off. Priests of Tempus are evil-aligned, they can use it to control the undead for a limited amount of time as temporary allies. After this runs out, the undead will become hostile to the party.\nPriest Spells.\nClerics can use priest spells and only the following spells are available to clerics. Some spells are not available for priests, depending on the alignment the character started with, not the alignment the character currently has.\nBonus spells.\nPriests of Tyr gain ability to cast following spells as special abilities:\nThey start with one usage of both abilities.\nHoly Symbol.\nAfter reaching level 24, priest gain the &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Symbol%20of%20Tyr\"&gt;Holy Symbol of Tyr&lt;/a&gt;.\nSpell Progression.\nNotes: Priest gain additional spell slots for their &lt;a href=\"wisdom\"&gt;wisdom&lt;/a&gt;. +Usable by priest whose wisdom is 17 or higher ++Usable by priest whose wisdom is 18 or higher.\nClerics whose wisdom is lower than 18, can use level 7 spells in ."}
{"id": "49085", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49085", "title": "Priest of Waukeen (Athkatla)", "text": "This unnamed Priest of Waukeen is the sole resident of the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Waukeen%20%28Government%20District%29\"&gt;Temple of Waukeen&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Government\"&gt;Government District&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign.\nHe provides the typical curative Temple Services, accepts Donations, and runs the Waukeen's Temple store. \"Welcome to this altar devoted to our Mistress of Coin, Waukeen, she who smiles on all who trade. Is there something I might do for you?\"If &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; responds, cynically, \"Trade doesn't seem all that holy to me,\" the priest may reply:\"I am sure that there are many who think as you do, dear &lt;GIRL/BOY&gt;. How, then, do you explain all the good that trade has brought to the Realms?\"\"Wondrous cities have been built, communications go between cultures throughout Toril... all because of trade. Without it we would still be living in caves.\"\"To many who ply trade, there is nothing more important in the world. Fortunes are made and lost under Waukeen's auspices.\"\nStock.\nThis Priest sells a few Potions, Scrolls and the &lt;a href=\"Druid%27s%20Ring\"&gt;Druid's Ring&lt;/a&gt;. Neither Stealing nor Fencing is possible. In the Classic game he does not buy anything from the party."}
{"id": "30588", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30588", "title": "Priest spell", "text": ""}
{"id": "32472", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32472", "title": "Priest spell scroll", "text": ""}
{"id": "32471", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32471", "title": "Priest spell scrolls", "text": ""}
{"id": "30483", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30483", "title": "Priest spells", "text": "Priest Spells are accessible through the Priest Scroll of characters capable of casting them. This includes &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt;s,\u00a0and\u00a0&lt;a href=\"shaman\"&gt;shaman&lt;/a&gt;s\u00a0of any level.\u00a0 &lt;a href=\"Ranger\"&gt;Ranger&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt;s may also cast priest spells, but only once they have reached a high enough level.\nFor general information on casting magic, see &lt;a href=\"Spells\"&gt;Spells&lt;/a&gt;.\nLearning Spells.\nUnlike &lt;a href=\"wizard%20spells\"&gt;wizard spells&lt;/a&gt;, priest spells are not scribed from scrolls. Instead, spells of each level are automatically learned when that level becomes accessible. For example, a level 1 cleric automatically knows all 1st level spells that they qualify for; when they reach level 3, they will automatically learn all 2nd level spells that they qualify for, and so on. The shaman class is the only exception, as they must choose which spells they learn (similar to the &lt;a href=\"sorcerer\"&gt;sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;).\nPaladins only reach 4th level spells; rangers only reach 3rd level spells. In addition, their caster level is adjusted based on the level that they gain access to spellcasting. See their class pages for more information.\nCertain priest spells are only available to clerics (and paladins), and some are only available to druids (and shamans and rangers). The &lt;a href=\"Cleric%20/%20Ranger\"&gt;Cleric / Ranger&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"multi-class\"&gt;multi-class&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"dual-class\"&gt;dual-class&lt;/a&gt; has access to both lists for 1st - 3rd levels, and depending on the game version, may have access to 4th - 7th levels as well.\nSpell Slots and Casting Restrictions.\nClerics and druids gain additional spell slots based on their &lt;a href=\"Wisdom\"&gt;Wisdom&lt;/a&gt; score. These are gained as soon as the level is available; for example, a level 1 cleric with 18 WIS will have three 1st level spell slots available.\nShamans, paladins, and rangers do not gain additional spell slots.\nIn the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"Shadows%20of%20Amn\"&gt;Shadows of Amn&lt;/a&gt;\", characters must have 17 WIS to cast 6th level priest spells and 18 WIS to cast 7th level priest spells. This requirement was removed in \"&lt;a href=\"Throne%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;Throne of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt;\", and is not present in the Enhanced Editions.\nEquipment that increases priest spell slots:\nDue\u00a0to the different level caps in the games, certain priests may have access to spell levels that other priests don't. See the table below for the maximum spell level attainable by each class at each level cap.\nSchools.\nPriest spells have schools; these\u00a0interact with &lt;a href=\"Specialist%20Mage\"&gt;Specialist Mage&lt;/a&gt; bonuses for &lt;a href=\"saving%20throw\"&gt;saving throw&lt;/a&gt;s. For example, an Invoker &gt; Cleric dual-class will apply a -2 save penalty when enemies save vs. &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, since it is an evocation spell; Enchanters will receive a +2 save bonus vs. &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Person%20or%20Mammal\"&gt;Charm Person or Mammal&lt;/a&gt; cast by a druid, since it is an enchantment/charm spell.\nThe schools do not interact with specialist restrictions; for example, a &lt;a href=\"gnome\"&gt;gnome&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Cleric%20/%20Mage\"&gt;Cleric / Illusionist&lt;/a&gt; can still cast all necromancy priest spells, even though they cannot cast necromancy wizard spells.\nPriest spells also have spheres, but these have no mechanical interactions.\nScrolls.\nCertain priest spells are available as scrolls. Their only use is as quick items to be cast, however.\u00a0 All priest scrolls can be cast by any of the normal priest spell classes, plus the &lt;a href=\"monk\"&gt;monk&lt;/a&gt;; &lt;a href=\"Restoration\"&gt;Restoration&lt;/a&gt; scrolls are unique and may be cast by any class. As with wizard scrolls, they require 9 &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; to use.\nQuest Spells.\nStarting at 3,000,000 XP in \"&lt;a href=\"Shadows%20of%20Amn\"&gt;Shadows of Amn&lt;/a&gt;\" (only accessible in with \"&lt;a href=\"Throne%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;Throne of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt;\" installed or in \"\"), priests gain access to &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;high-level class abilities&lt;/a&gt; referred to as Quest Spells. These represent exceptional divine powers granted to the priest by their deity. These are only available if the priest has gained 7th level spell slots, and the priest has the ability to select one at each level up. These are added to their priest scroll as 7th level spells, and otherwise function exactly as other spells do.\nSpell List.\nThe following abbreviations are used in the table below:"}
{"id": "4103", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4103", "title": "Priest spells (Baldur's Gate)", "text": "Priest spells are used by &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"ranger\"&gt;ranger&lt;/a&gt;s\u00a0and &lt;a href=\"paladins\"&gt;paladins&lt;/a&gt;. Some spells are universal, while others are limited to either clerics or druids. Rangers gain use of spells available to druids upon reaching level 8. The &lt;a href=\"Cleric%20/%20Ranger\"&gt;Cleric/Ranger&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Multi-class\"&gt;multi-class&lt;/a&gt; is able to use both cleric and druid spells.\nDruids can begin using level 5 spells at level 9. Due to the experience cap of 161,000 experience with , a cleric will never be able to use level 5 spells in an unmodified game. Rangers can use spells available to druids at level 8, but with the experience cap will only be able to use level 1 spells.\nThe Priest Spellbook in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; has 51 spells.\nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod will change and revise \"Divine Spells\" in the game, for all creatures who use them, whether friend or foe. To view the spells and peruse the changes - follow this &lt;a href=\"http%3A//gibberlings3.github.io/SpellRevisions/spells/divine/\"&gt;Link at the Gibberlings 3&lt;/a&gt;. "}
{"id": "4709", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4709", "title": "Priest spells (Baldur's Gate II)", "text": "Priest spells are used by &lt;a href=\"Cleric\"&gt;Cleric&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt;s. &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt;s can use up to 4th level spells and &lt;a href=\"Ranger\"&gt;Ranger&lt;/a&gt;s up to 3rd level.\nBaldur's Gate II has 119 spells \u2013 110 are in and 9 additional in ."}
{"id": "35786", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35786", "title": "Priestess", "text": "The Priestess is a female &lt;a href=\"Sahuagin\"&gt;Sahuagin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Cleric\"&gt;Cleric&lt;/a&gt; aligned with the Rebel faction in the Sahuagin civil strife in the &lt;a href=\"Underwater%20City\"&gt;City of Caverns&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nThe cleric will self-buff with a preparatory group of spells to include &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chant\"&gt;Chant&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Strength%20of%20One\"&gt;Strength of One&lt;/a&gt; - some of these buffs may affect the other rebels in the group, enhancing their abilities. Almost right after this she'll try and get a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Ward\"&gt;Death Ward&lt;/a&gt; on herself.\nAfter that, expect an &lt;a href=\"Earthquake\"&gt;Earthquake&lt;/a&gt; spell cast, and then various offensive and disabling spells done sequentially, if able and not interrupted.\nAs she is wearing the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Mirroring\"&gt;Cloak of Mirroring&lt;/a&gt;, most single-target and some area of effect offensive damage type spells will deflect harmlessly from her.\nTake note of her scripted use spells in the InfoBox. All of those listed can be attempted as the battle transpires.\nShe will attempt to heal herself if damaged to a preset threshold. &lt;a href=\"Mass%20Cure\"&gt;Mass Cure&lt;/a&gt; first, and if severely wounded, then a &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt; will be attempted.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some changes to the creature. A \"smarter Priest\" default cleric script is assigned. A new and revised fully populated level 14 cleric spell book is memorized. When the battle begins, she will instantly self-buff with a group of previously cast spell to include &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spiritual%20Hammer\"&gt;Spiritual Hammer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;.\nWith her weapon now changed to the Spiritual hammer, she could be throwing it or striking at a distance, especially with the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod version and also with the &lt;a href=\"Thrown%20Hammers\"&gt;Thrown Hammers&lt;/a&gt; mod. In terms of further spell casting, these will be selected as determined by the AI's opponent threat and vulnerability assessment scripts. Various offensive and disabling spells will be attempted. She can try various cure spells on self at predetermined thresholds of damage. &lt;a href=\"Unholy%20Blight\"&gt;Unholy Blight&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Unholy%20Word\"&gt;Unholy Word&lt;/a&gt; can be used. She can attempt a &lt;a href=\"Harm\"&gt;Harm&lt;/a&gt; spell as well. "}
{"id": "55094", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55094", "title": "Priestess Demin", "text": "High Priestess Demin is chief cleric of the city of &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt;. She's found in a predicament and in mortal danger inside her &lt;a href=\"Demin%27s%20House\"&gt;House&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nWhen the party enters the priestess's house, a trio of enemies are present within. These include &lt;a href=\"Adsaan\"&gt;Adsaan&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Rajah\"&gt;Rajah&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Rakshasa\"&gt;Rakshasa&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe priestess will cry out for help from the party.\nAssuming the party is able to defeat the rakshasas, and also assuming Demin wasn't slain during the battle - she will thank the party and then initiate a very thorough and informative dialogue chain.\nFrom an information and insight standpoint, priestess Demin has the most information for the party about the \"Exiles\" (Irenicus and Bodhi) and their history with the elves so far in the game.\nDemin is also the first one to admit that the elves' themselves have some culpability in their current dilemma. She realizes the harsh treatment of the exiles may have actually planted the seeds for all the destruction now taking place. She also makes it clear, more than once, that the elves will have to make reparations to those harmed due to their action and inaction.\nIts highly recommended to explore everything and keep an open mind to gather all the dialogue available from her.\nIn the end, she'll explain how to combat Irenicus's forces and possibly turn the tide of battle. By gathering special artifacts, placing them on an altar in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Rillifane\"&gt;Temple of Rillifane&lt;/a&gt;, the divine power of the elves' leaf lord can be brought forth to assist the city in its hour of need. The &lt;a href=\"Avatar%20of%20Rillifane\"&gt;Avatar of Rillifane&lt;/a&gt; will be able to unseal the palace, as well as summon a host of spiritual defenders to sweep through the city and destroy the attackers.\nPriestess Demin is also concerned about queen &lt;a href=\"Ellesime\"&gt;Ellesime&lt;/a&gt;, and she offers information about her whereabouts and needed objectives to save her.\nIf the unfortunate occurs, and the priestess is slain and is unable to provide any of her dialogue - do not despair. Her deceased body drops the &lt;a href=\"Demin%27s%20Note\"&gt;Demin's Note&lt;/a&gt;, which can fill in some of the gaps and a be a guide for what to do next."}
{"id": "47416", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47416", "title": "Priestess of Ilmatar", "text": "This Priestess of Ilmater can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Ilmater%20%28Waukeen%27s%20Promenade%29\"&gt;Temple of Ilmater&lt;/a&gt; located in the &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;. She offers services for the temple and will accept &lt;a href=\"Yoshimo%27s%20Heart\"&gt;Yoshimo's Heart&lt;/a&gt; should you decide to fulfill &lt;a href=\"Yoshimo\"&gt;Yoshimo&lt;/a&gt;s wish and grant the thief peace in death."}
{"id": "35767", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35767", "title": "Priestess of Sekolah", "text": "The Priestess of Sekolah is a female &lt;a href=\"sahuagin\"&gt;sahuagin&lt;/a&gt; cleric that the party can find in the &lt;a href=\"Underwater%20City\"&gt;Underwater City&lt;/a&gt; during Chapter 4 of . She is a low-ranked priestess who serves under &lt;a href=\"Royal%20High%20Priestess%20Senityili\"&gt;Royal High Priestess Senityili&lt;/a&gt;, and will act as a merchant for the party if they begin the quest &lt;a href=\"The%20prophecy%20of%20Sekolah\"&gt;The prophecy of Sekolah&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe priestess is neutral most of the time. She will become hostile if the party refuses to cooperate with Royal High Priestess Senityili at the outset of appearing in the City of Caverns.\nOddly, she does not get hostile if the party kills the King, or the Rebel Prince, or the entire populace of sahuagin. She may be the last shark-spawn left standing and still render temple services.\nIf made hostile she is scripted to try and cast some divine magic, but won't be a serious challenge to the party, being outnumbered and a very basic script to defend herself."}
{"id": "48816", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48816", "title": "Priestess of Umberlee (Brynnlaw)", "text": "This Priestess of Umberlee is found inside the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Umberlee%20%28Brynnlaw%29\"&gt;Temple of Umberlee&lt;/a&gt; that's located on the island of &lt;a href=\"Brynnlaw\"&gt;Brynnlaw&lt;/a&gt;. She offers the typical temple services found in most temples throughout &lt;a href=\"Faer%C3%BBn\"&gt;Faer\u00fbn&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThis priestess is willing to serve all visitors, including providing all offered products for sale, and cures.\nIf the party, for whatever reason decides to be bloodthirsty, and with no provocation, initiates an attack upon her, then she will attempt to fight back.\nHer first action is to apply a group of defensive buffs that are force cast and are not interruptible. These include &lt;a href=\"Death%20Ward\"&gt;Death Ward&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bless\"&gt;Bless&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Strength%20of%20One\"&gt;Strength of One&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Defensive%20Harmony\"&gt;Defensive Harmony&lt;/a&gt;.\nUnless the party is inept or extremely unlucky, then she will probably already be defeated within a round of this action, and unable to complete another spell cast attempt. But if not, then she will methodically attempt further divine spell casting at valid targets. It is improbable that any of those attempts will succeed at this stage of the game.\nClerics of Umberlee are not typically classified as innocents. Killing her may be grisly and unnecessary but leads to no reputation penalty. It will shutter this temple for further use.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises the cleric with a changed opening battery of defensive buffs. These include &lt;a href=\"Regeneration%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Regeneration (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Resistance%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Magic Resistance (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spiritual%20Hammer\"&gt;Spiritual Hammer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Mirror\"&gt;Physical Mirror&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;. A second later an &lt;a href=\"Aerial%20servant%20%28creature%29\"&gt;Aerial servant (creature)&lt;/a&gt; will have been conjured for assistance. As with the unmodified game, the priestess will probably be dead in a round or two and disrupted from further spell casting success from a party at this game stage. If for some strange reason she is not defeated and is able to complete her high-level divine spells casts, then the party could be in some level of risk."}
{"id": "47506", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47506", "title": "Priestess of Umberlee (South Baldur's Gate)", "text": "This Priestess of Umberlee is found inside of the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Umberlee\"&gt;Water Queen's House&lt;/a&gt; located in &lt;a href=\"South%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;South Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. There are a total of four are wandering about inside the temple. The gold-haired priestess will greet the party as soon as you enter and inquire about your purpose for visiting the temple. She is the only priestess who will engage the party in dialogue and she can summon either &lt;a href=\"Jalantha%20Mistmyr\"&gt;Jalantha Mistmyr&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Tenya\"&gt;Tenya&lt;/a&gt;. The other three only have the dialogue to warn you to mind your manners inside the house of the Bitch Goddess."}
