{"id": "50885", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50885", "title": "Prophet", "text": "Prophet refers to several humanoid creatures that spawn within areas of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; upon the initiation of the &lt;a href=\"Investigate%20and%20Destroy%20the%20Cult%20of%20the%20Eyeless\"&gt;Investigate and Destroy the Cult of the Eyeless&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nThese prophets are found in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;. They have their eyes removed, yet still seem to be able to perceive you. They will answer some questions about their new faith, and chastise you with fire and brimstone cult babble if you say the wrong thing, in their opinion.\nTo hear what they have to say, a party member must initiate conversation with them.\nIn general, harming these prophets won't result in any repercussions. However, one of them will cause a reputation loss and cause immediate hostility from a nearby &lt;a href=\"Amnian%20Guard\"&gt;Amnian Guard&lt;/a&gt;. These prophets are basically worthless in terms of loot or experience rewards."}
