{"id": "6180", "revid": "271883", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6180", "title": "Protection From Acid (protection scroll)", "text": "Protection From Acid is a &lt;a href=\"protection%20scroll\"&gt;protection scroll&lt;/a&gt;, usable by everyone, that offers acid resistance of fifty percent for twelve hours."}
{"id": "27427", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27427", "title": "Protection From Acid (scroll)", "text": "Protection From Acid (scroll) might refer to:"}
{"id": "6071", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6071", "title": "Protection From Acid (spell)", "text": "The &lt;a href=\"wizard%20spell\"&gt;wizard spell&lt;/a&gt; Protection From Acid gives the target complete invulnerability to all acid attacks, whether magical or non-magical.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this to a single creature or self - it has a range of basically \"touch\" distance.\nWhen the spell casting is finished the recipient will show a brief color fade, a lighting effect and a 3D graphic rendered on their sprite.\nA text will display, reading \"Protection From Acid\".\nAdditionally, a sound effect will audible when the spell is first cast, and another when it expires.\nA player character will show an icon (No. 24) titled \"Protection From Acid\" on their portrait for the spell's duration. \nThis spell will bestow the recipient with &lt;a href=\"Acid%20damage\"&gt;Acid damage&lt;/a&gt; resistance \"set\" to 100%.\nThis spell can be removed by any applicable &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; source or with a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nMultiple applications of this spell on the same creature will not increase acid resistance over 100%; the most current application will refresh the spell's duration.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Protection from Acid\" protects the creature from all forms of acid, negating acid damage to a limit of 90 points.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has removed the Protection From Acid (spell) from the arcane spell library. It has no equivalent replacement in SR for the player or opponents in the game. However, SR does provide the following 4th level arcane spell (new). See below for description:\nProtection from Elemental Energy\nLevel: 4\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 1 turn/level\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen this spell is cast, the recipient receives complete protection from one damage type: acid, cold, fire, or lightning. 100% of the damage from the selected source of energy will be absorbed, and the target creature will become completely immune to the effects of spells based on that element. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative, but each time a different damage type can be selected.\nThere is also the new 2nd level arcane spell described below:\nResist Elements\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Abjuration\nSphere: Protection\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 1 turn + 1 round/level\nCasting Time: 2\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nUpon the casting of this spell, the recipient\u2019s resistance to all forms of elemental damage is increased by 25%. This effect will last for the duration of the spell or until dispelled. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative."}
