{"id": "6184", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6184", "title": "Protection From Cold (protection scroll)", "text": "Protection From Cold is a &lt;a href=\"protection%20scroll\"&gt;protection scroll&lt;/a&gt;, usable by everyone, that offers &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;cold&lt;/a&gt; resistance of fifty percent for twelve hours.\nGame Mechanic Note.\nThe \"Green\" protection scrolls are implementing their effects differently than a cast spell does. The Scrolls have no assigned \"Spell School\", and no assigned \"Spell Type\". As such they can't be removed by a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; effect as they are not a combat protection nor a specific protection. \nThe spell power level of the scroll is zero, and that means that any dispel magic effect will remove all the protections conferred by the scroll, even if the dispel effect was even a level 1 spell power. \nThese scrolls stack their effectiveness. The maximum protection gained from a Protection from Cold Scroll would be 127% (assuming three scrolls were used, and the creature had no other fire resistance sources). "}
{"id": "27428", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27428", "title": "Protection From Cold (scroll)", "text": "Protection From Cold (scroll) might refer to:"}
{"id": "6131", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6131", "title": "Protection From Cold (spell)", "text": "The &lt;a href=\"wizard%20spell\"&gt;wizard spell&lt;/a&gt; Protection From Cold gives the target complete invulnerability to non-magical &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;cold&lt;/a&gt; attacks and 50% damage resistance against cold from magical cold attacks.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this to a single creature or self - it has a range of basically \"touch\" distance.\nWhen the spell casting is finished the recipient will show a brief color fade, a lighting effect and a 3D graphic rendered on their sprite.\nA text will display, reading \"Protection From Cold\".\nA player character will show an icon (No. 25) titled \"Protection From Cold\" on their portrait for the spell's duration. \nThis spell will bestow the recipient with &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;Cold damage&lt;/a&gt; resistance \"set\" to 100%.\nThis spell can be removed by any applicable &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; source or with a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nMultiple applications of this spell on the same creature will not increase cold resistance over 100%; the most current application will refresh the spell's duration.\nNote that spell also sets resistance to \"magical cold damage\" to 50%, however that damage type is not implemented in the unmodified game.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Protection from Cold\" protects from the effects of normal cold as low as absolute zero. Against magical cold, the spell gives a +4 bonus to the protected creature's saving throw and reduces damage by 50%.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has removed this arcane spell from the game. There is no direct 3rd level equivalent spell. However, there is a 4th level arcane spell, as described below:\nProtection from Elemental Energy\nLevel: 4\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 1 turn/level\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen this spell is cast, the recipient receives complete protection from one damage type: acid, cold, fire, or lightning. 100% of the damage from the selected source of energy will be absorbed, and the target creature will become completely immune to the effects of spells based on that element. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative, but each time a different damage type can be selected.\nThere is also the new 2nd level arcane spell described below:\nResist Elements\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Abjuration\nSphere: Protection\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 1 turn + 1 round/level\nCasting Time: 2\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nUpon the casting of this spell, the recipient\u2019s resistance to all forms of elemental damage is increased by 25%. This effect will last for the duration of the spell or until dispelled. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative."}
{"id": "27442", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27442", "title": "Protection From Cold (spell scroll)", "text": ""}
{"id": "30705", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30705", "title": "Protection From Electricity", "text": "Protection From Electricity may refer to:"}
{"id": "6190", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6190", "title": "Protection From Electricity (protection scroll)", "text": "Protection From Electricity is a &lt;a href=\"protection%20scroll\"&gt;protection scroll&lt;/a&gt;, usable by everyone, that offers electricity resistance of fifty percent for twelve hours.\nGame Mechanic Note.\nThe \"Green\" protection scrolls are implementing their effects differently than a cast spell does. The Scrolls have no assigned \"Spell School\", and no assigned \"Spell Type\". As such they can't be removed by a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; effect as they are not a combat protection nor a specific protection. \nThe spell power level of the scroll is zero, and that means that any dispel magic effect will remove all the protections conferred by the scroll, even if the dispel effect was even a level 1 spell power. \nThese scrolls stack their effectiveness. The maximum protection gained from a Protection from Electricity Scroll would be 127% (assuming three scrolls were used, and the creature had no other fire resistance sources). "}
{"id": "27429", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27429", "title": "Protection From Electricity (scroll)", "text": "Protection From Electricity (scroll) might refer to:"}
{"id": "6132", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6132", "title": "Protection From Electricity (spell)", "text": "The &lt;a href=\"wizard%20spell\"&gt;wizard spell&lt;/a&gt; Protection From Electricity gives the target complete invulnerability to all electrical attacks, whether magical or non-magical.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this to a single creature or self - it has a range of basically \"touch\" distance.\nWhen the spell casting is finished the recipient will show a brief color fade, a lighting effect and a 3D graphic rendered on their sprite.\nA text will display, reading \"Protection From Electricity\".\nAdditionally, a sound effect will audible when the spell expires.\nA player character will show an icon (No. 27) titled \"Protection From Electricity\" on their portrait for the spell's duration. \nThis spell will bestow the recipient with &lt;a href=\"Electricity%20damage\"&gt;Electricity damage&lt;/a&gt; resistance \"set\" to 100%.\nThis spell can be removed by any applicable &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; source or with a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nMultiple applications of this spell on the same creature will not increase electricity resistance over 100%; the most current application will refresh the spell's duration.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Protection from Electricity\" is a 4th-level spell. The protected creature receives a +4 bonus to saving throws against electrical attacks, natural or magical. Any electrical damage received is reduced by 50%. If the saving throw is success\u00adful, then any secondary effects the electrical attack may have (stunning, paralysis, etc.) are negated.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has removed the Protection From Electricity (spell) from the arcane spell library. It has no equivalent replacement in SR for the player or opponents in the game. However SR does provide the following 4th level arcane spell (new). See below for description:\nProtection from Elemental Energy\nLevel: 4\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 1 turn/level\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen this spell is cast, the recipient receives complete protection from one damage type: acid, cold, fire, or lightning. 100% of the damage from the selected source of energy will be absorbed, and the target creature will become completely immune to the effects of spells based on that element. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative, but each time a different damage type can be selected.\nThere is also the new 2nd level arcane spell described below:\nResist Elements\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Abjuration\nSphere: Protection\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 1 turn + 1 round/level\nCasting Time: 2\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nUpon the casting of this spell, the recipient\u2019s resistance to all forms of elemental damage is increased by 25%. This effect will last for the duration of the spell or until dispelled. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative."}
{"id": "27443", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27443", "title": "Protection From Electricity (spell scroll)", "text": ""}
{"id": "6084", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6084", "title": "Protection From Energy", "text": "Protection From Energy raises the spell recipients' energy resistances to all energy types, no matter the source.\nGameplay.\nWhen the spell is completed and cast on a creature, a text is displayed reading \"Protection From Energy\", as well as 3D effect and a color fade is rendered over the sprite, and an icon is placed on the character's portrait.\nWhen the spell expires, an audible sound effect is heard.\nThe recipient of this spell is bestowed a temporary boost to resist &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;Cold damage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Electricity%20damage\"&gt;Electricity damage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Acid%20damage\"&gt;Acid damage&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Magical%20damage\"&gt;Magical damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe elemental resistance modifier value is +75%, which is cumulative with any other similar elemental resistances already present on the creature.\nThe maximum game-allowed damage resistance modifier for these energy resistances is 127%.\nValues over 100% can heal the creature when that particular energy damage type is incurred, for example if the creature has 110% fire resistance and incurs 40 fire damage, the targeted creature can be healed 4 hit points from that damage event.\nA second application of this spell will add cumulative bonuses onto the initial spell - e.g. it can be stacked with the same spell. \nThis spell is affected by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects and can be removed with a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nNote.\nThe spell also boosts resistance to magical cold damage and magical fire damage, which are unused/unimplemented damage types in the unmodified game.\nThis spell can't help with &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt;. For that the character would need a &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Poison\"&gt;Protection From Poison&lt;/a&gt; scroll, or perhaps an item such as the &lt;a href=\"Periapt%20of%20Proof%20Against%20Poison\"&gt;Periapt of Proof Against Poison&lt;/a&gt;, for example. See the &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt; articles.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its duration, effects, and description. See below:\nProtection from Energy\nLevel: 8\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 2 rounds/level\nCasting Time: 8\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen this spell is cast, it confers complete protection from all energy attacks composed of acid, cold, electricity, fire, or magic damage, whether magical or non-magical in origin. 100% of the energy damage from attacks with weapons, wands, breath weapons, etc. will be absorbed, and the target creature will become completely immune to the effects of energy-based spells. This effect lasts for the duration of the spell or until dispelled."}
{"id": "20881", "revid": "26939652", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20881", "title": "Protection From Evil", "text": "Protection From Evil might refer to:"}
{"id": "4858", "revid": "1966519", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4858", "title": "Protection From Evil, 10' Radius", "text": "Protection From Evil, 10' Radius is a 4th-level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; only cast by &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt; classes. the spell bestows the same effects as the 1st-level priest/wizard spells &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Evil\"&gt;Protection From Evil&lt;/a&gt; to multiple party creatures, with a prolonged spell duration.\nSome other classes may cast this spell from scrolls, see the InfoBox.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this spell to themself.\nWhen the spell is applied, the caster and all party affiliated creatures in the 15-feet radius of the caster will show a brief 3D graphic effect and fade from color rendered on their sprite, and a then for the duration of spell the creature will be affected by a continuous color glow pulse effect - a text will display reading \"Protection From Evil\".\nA player character with this spell active will show an icon (No. 142) titled \"Protection From Evil\" on their portrait.\nThe spell can be applied to party summoned/gated demons as well - which might be desired if the party has summoned multiple fiends (so they won't target and attack each other).\nThis spell does not apply to all demons; only those specifically summoned by spells like &lt;a href=\"Cacofiend\"&gt;Cacofiend&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Fiend\"&gt;Summon Fiend&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Gate\"&gt;Gate&lt;/a&gt;. For example, as &lt;a href=\"Aec%27Letec\"&gt;Aec'Letec&lt;/a&gt; simply spawns like an ordinary creature, the spell doesn't prevent him from targeting you. It will apply its &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; and saving throw effects normally, however.\nIn the original games, this spell is cumulative with itself. In the \"Enhanced Editions\", it will not stack with itself.\nDespite the wording in the spell description, the spell doesn't cause evil creatures to have 2-point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; penalty, it instead boosts the &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; of the spell recipient by 2 points if the attacker's alignment is evil, at least in the Enhanced Edition.\nSimilarly, the spell recipient is conferred with a 2-point bonus to all saving throws versus attacks/effects originating from creatures with an evil alignment.\nProtection from evil 10' Radius can be removed by any &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect. A &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell will remove it as well.\nThe actual effects of this spell were changed throughout the course of the which was not always reflected in its description.\n\"Baldur's Gate\".\nBesides using a fixed duration, the very first is the only one that applies the described &lt;a href=\"saving%20throw\"&gt;saving throw&lt;/a&gt; bonus, as the spell should according to pen-and-paper rules. However, together with the &lt;a href=\"armor%20class\"&gt;armor class&lt;/a&gt; bonus, these effects are applied in general and do not check the alignment of enemy creatures, granting them versus any and all attacks and spells. As summoned demons do not exist in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\", the later added effect isn't needed \u2013 instead it is also the only game that simulates the actual \"second\" pen-and-paper effect (attack and save bonuses are pooled as first there): immunity to becoming possessed by &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;evil&lt;/a&gt; creatures, read \"&lt;a href=\"charmed\"&gt;charmed&lt;/a&gt;\". This, however, isn't written into the description.\n\"Shadows of Amn\".\nThe original \"\" doesn't alter the description, but removes the saving throw bonus and the charm immunity \u2013 for both it is technically not possible to limit them to evil sources without much extra effort in coding. The replacement effect, protection from &lt;a href=\"summoned%20demons\"&gt;summoned demons&lt;/a&gt;, is not mentioned.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Priest spell \"Protection from Evil, 10' Radius\" has several differences from the game's version. First, is a reversible spell and could as well be cast as \"Protection From Good, 10' Radius\". If the anyone in the radius melee attacks across the spell barrier the protection is cancelled. Extra planar creatures cannot make bodily contact across the spell's barrier.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced \"Protection From Evil 10' Radius\" with \"Magic Circle against Evil\". See below for description:\nMagic Circle against Evil\nLevel: 4\nSchool: Abjuration\nSphere: Protection\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 5 turns\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 30\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: None\nUpon casting this spell, the priest causes all friendly creatures within the area of effect to be affected by the spell Protection from Evil. Creatures leaving the area are still subject to the spell\u2019s effect; those entering the area after the casting is completed are not."}
{"id": "30565", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30565", "title": "Protection From Evil (arcane)", "text": ""}
{"id": "30564", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30564", "title": "Protection From Evil (divine)", "text": ""}
{"id": "42952", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42952", "title": "Protection From Evil (effect)", "text": "Protection From Evil provides a magical barrier around the recipient at a distance of one foot. The barrier moves with the recipient and has two major effects: First, all attacks made by evil or evilly enchanted creatures against the protected creature receive a penalty of -2 to each attack roll. Second, the protected creature makes all &lt;a href=\"saving%20throw\"&gt;saving throw&lt;/a&gt;s against attacks from such opponents with a -2 bonus.\nA third benefit is not part of the status effect itself, but of the various Protection From Evil spells instead: cannot target the protected creature.\nIf the caster is &lt;a href=\"evil\"&gt;evil&lt;/a&gt;-aligned and protected from evil, they do get save bonuses against their own attacks."}
{"id": "4628", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4628", "title": "Protection From Evil (priest)", "text": "Protection From Evil is a 1st level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; only usable by &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt; classes. It grants the target defense against &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;evil-aligned&lt;/a&gt; creatures.\nThis spell provides bonuses identical to its &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Evil%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;wizard counterpart&lt;/a&gt; but has a longer duration.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this spell to a single creature including self if desired, and the range of the spell is only 1 foot (touch).\nWhen the spell is applied, the recipient will show a brief 3D graphic effect and fade from color rendered on their sprite, and a then for the duration of spell the creature will be affected by a continuous color glow pulse effect - a text will display reading \"Protection From Evil\".\nA player character with this spell active will show an icon (No. 142) titled \"Protection From Evil\" on their portrait.\nThis spell does not apply to all demons; only those specifically summoned by spells like &lt;a href=\"Cacofiend\"&gt;Cacofiend&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Fiend\"&gt;Summon Fiend&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Gate\"&gt;Gate&lt;/a&gt;. For example, as &lt;a href=\"Aec%27Letec\"&gt;Aec'Letec&lt;/a&gt; simply spawns like an ordinary creature, the spell doesn't prevent him from targeting you. It will apply its &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; and saving throw effects normally, however.\nIn the original games, this spell is cumulative with itself. In the \"Enhanced Editions\", it will not stack with itself.\nDespite the wording in the spell description, the spell doesn't cause evil creatures to have 2-point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; penalty, it instead boosts the &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; of the spell recipient by 2 points if the attacker's alignment is evil, at least in the Enhanced Edition.\nSimilarly, the spell recipient is conferred with a 2-point bonus to all saving throws versus attacks/effects originating from creatures with an evil alignment.\nProtection from evil can be removed by any &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect. A &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell will remove it as well.\nThe actual effects of this spell were changed throughout the course of the which was not always reflected in its description.\n\"Baldur's Gate\".\nBesides using a fixed duration, the very first is the only one that applies the described &lt;a href=\"saving%20throw\"&gt;saving throw&lt;/a&gt; bonus, as the spell should according to pen-and-paper rules. However, together with the &lt;a href=\"armor%20class\"&gt;armor class&lt;/a&gt; bonus, these effects are applied in general and do not check the alignment of enemy creatures, granting them versus any and all attacks and spells. As summoned demons do not exist in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\", the later added effect isn't needed \u2013 instead it is also the only game that simulates the actual \"second\" pen-and-paper effect (attack and save bonuses are pooled as first there): immunity to becoming possessed by &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;evil&lt;/a&gt; creatures, read \"&lt;a href=\"charmed\"&gt;charmed&lt;/a&gt;\". This, however, isn't written into the description.\n\"Shadows of Amn\".\nThe original \"\" doesn't alter the description (besides updating the duration of the spell to a per-level basis), but removes the saving throw bonus and the charm immunity \u2013 for both it is technically not possible to limit them to evil sources without much extra effort in coding. The replacement effect, protection from &lt;a href=\"summoned%20demons\"&gt;summoned demons&lt;/a&gt;, is not mentioned.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Priest spell \"Protection from Evil\" has several differences from the game's version. First, is a reversible spell and could as well be cast as \"Protection From Good\". If the caster melee attacks across the spell barrier the protection is cancelled. Extra planar creatures cannot make bodily contact across the spell's barrier.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this divine spell, revising its effects, duration and description. See below:\nProtection from Evil\nLevel: 1\nSchool: Abjuration\nSphere: Protection\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 5 turns\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen this spell is cast, it creates a magical barrier around the recipient at a distance of one foot. The barrier moves with the recipient and has two major effects: first, all attacks made by evil creatures against the protected creature receive a -2 penalty to their attack roll, and second, any saving throws caused by such attacks are made by the protected creature with a +2 bonus."}
{"id": "16199", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16199", "title": "Protection From Evil (wizard)", "text": "Protection From Evil creates a magical barrier around the target to help safeguard it against evil sources of harm.\nThis spell provides bonuses identical to its &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Evil%20%28priest%29\"&gt;priest counterpart&lt;/a&gt; but has a shorter duration.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this spell to a single creature including self if desired, and the range of the spell is only 1 foot (touch).\nWhen the spell is applied, the recipient will show a brief 3D graphic effect and fade from color rendered on their sprite, and a then for the duration of spell the creature will be affected by a continuous color glow pulse effect - a text will display reading \"Protection From Evil\".\nA player character with this spell active will show an icon (No. 142) titled \"Protection From Evil\" on their portrait.\nThis spell does not apply to all demons; only those specifically summoned by spells like &lt;a href=\"Cacofiend\"&gt;Cacofiend&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Fiend\"&gt;Summon Fiend&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Gate\"&gt;Gate&lt;/a&gt;. For example, as &lt;a href=\"Aec%27Letec\"&gt;Aec'Letec&lt;/a&gt; simply spawns like an ordinary creature, the spell doesn't prevent him from targeting you. It will apply its &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; and saving throw effects normally, however.\nIn the original games, this spell is cumulative with itself. In the \"Enhanced Editions\", it will not stack with itself.\nDespite the wording in the spell description, the spell doesn't cause evil creatures to have 2-point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; penalty, it instead boosts the &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; of the spell recipient by 2 points if the attacker's alignment is evil, at least in the Enhanced Edition.\nSimilarly, the spell recipient is conferred with a 2-point bonus to all saving throws versus attacks/effects originating from creatures with an evil alignment.\nProtection from evil can be removed by any &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect. A &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell will remove it as well.\nThe actual effects of this spell were changed throughout the course of the which was not always reflected in its description.\n\"Baldur's Gate\".\nBesides using a fixed duration, the very first is the only one that applies the described &lt;a href=\"saving%20throw\"&gt;saving throw&lt;/a&gt; bonus, as the spell should according to pen-and-paper rules. However, together with the &lt;a href=\"armor%20class\"&gt;armor class&lt;/a&gt; bonus, these effects are applied in general and do not check the alignment of enemy creatures, granting them versus any and all attacks and spells. As summoned demons do not exist in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\", the later added effect isn't needed \u2013 instead it is also the only game that simulates the actual \"second\" pen-and-paper effect (attack and save bonuses are pooled as first there): immunity to becoming possessed by &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;evil&lt;/a&gt; creatures, read \"&lt;a href=\"charmed\"&gt;charmed&lt;/a&gt;\". This, however, isn't written into the description.\n\"Shadows of Amn\".\nThe original \"\" doesn't alter the description (besides updating the duration of the spell to a per-level basis) but removes the saving throw bonus and the charm immunity \u2013 for both it is technically not possible to limit them to evil sources without much extra effort in coding. The replacement effect, protection from &lt;a href=\"summoned%20demons\"&gt;summoned demons&lt;/a&gt;, is not mentioned.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Protection from Evil\" has several differences from the game's version. First, is a reversible spell and could as well be cast as \"Protection From Good\". If the caster melee attacks across the spell barrier the protection is cancelled. Extra planar creatures cannot make bodily contact across the spell's barrier.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, changing its effects and duration. It no longer has any extra power over gated Demons. See below for description:\nProtection from Evil\nLevel: 1\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 5 turns\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen this spell is cast, it creates a magical barrier around the recipient at a distance of one foot. The barrier moves with the recipient and has two major effects: first, all attacks made by evil or evilly enchanted creatures against the protected creature receive a -2 penalty to their attack roll, and second, any saving throws caused by such attacks are made by the protected creature with a +2 bonus."}
