{"id": "30656", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30656", "title": "Protection From Fire (arcane)", "text": ""}
{"id": "30657", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30657", "title": "Protection From Fire (divine)", "text": ""}
{"id": "5086", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5086", "title": "Protection From Fire (priest)", "text": "Protection From Fire is a 3rd level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt;. It gives the target creature protection from &lt;a href=\"fire%20damage\"&gt;fire damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is identical to its 3rd level &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Fire\"&gt;wizard counterpart&lt;/a&gt;, but has a longer casting time and shorter duration. It also has a higher magic fire resistance bonus, but this has no gameplay effect; see the \"Gameplay\" section below.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this Divine spell, revising it to a 5th level spell, and changing the casting time, duration, effects and description. See below:\nProtection from Fire:\nLevel: 5\nSchool: Abjuration'\nSphere: Elemental, Protection\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 1 turn/level\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen a Protection from Fire spell is cast, the recipient receives complete protection from fire-based attacks, whether magical or non-magical in origin. 100% of the damage from attacks like fiery dragon breath will be absorbed, and the target creature will become completely immune to the effects of spells such as Burning Hands, Fireball, Flame Strike, and Fire Storm. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative."}
{"id": "6195", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6195", "title": "Protection From Fire (protection scroll)", "text": "Protection From Fire is a &lt;a href=\"protection%20scroll\"&gt;protection scroll&lt;/a&gt;, usable by everyone, that offers resistance of fifty percent against elemental &lt;a href=\"fire%20damage\"&gt;fire damage&lt;/a&gt; for twelve hours.\nGame Mechanic Note.\nThe \"Green\" protection scrolls are implementing their effects differently than a cast spell does. The Scrolls have no assigned \"Spell School\", and no assigned \"Spell Type\". As such they can't be removed by a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; effect as they are not a combat protection nor a specific protection. \nThe spell power level of the scroll is zero, and that means that any dispel magic effect will remove all the protections conferred by the scroll, even if the dispel effect was even a level 1 spell power. \nThese scrolls stack their effectiveness. The maximum protection gained from a Protection from Fire Scroll would be 127% (assuming three scrolls were used, and the creature had no other fire resistance sources). "}
{"id": "27430", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27430", "title": "Protection From Fire (scroll)", "text": "Protection From Fire (scroll) might refer to:"}
{"id": "27444", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27444", "title": "Protection From Fire (spell scroll)", "text": ""}
{"id": "16201", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16201", "title": "Protection From Fire (wizard)", "text": "The &lt;a href=\"wizard%20spell\"&gt;wizard spell&lt;/a&gt; Protection From Fire bestow upon the target creature protection from magical and non-magical &lt;a href=\"fire%20damage\"&gt;fire damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this to a single creature or self - it has a range of basically \"touch\" distance.\nWhen the spell casting is finished the recipient will show a brief color fade, a lighting effect and a 3D graphic rendered on their sprite.\nA text will display, reading \"Protection from Fire\".\nA player character will show an icon (No. 16) titled \"Protection From Fire\" on their portrait for the spell's duration. \nThis spell will bestow the recipient with &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt; resistance \"set\" to 100%.\nThis spell can be removed by any applicable &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; source or with a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nMultiple applications of this spell on the same creature will not increase fire resistance over 100%; the most current application will refresh the spell's duration.\nNote that this spell also sets 'magical fire damage\" resistance to 50%, however, that damage type is not implemented in the unmodified game.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Protection from Fire\" protects the creature touched by the caster and is immune to normal fire. Against magical flame, protected creatures receive a +2 bonus to saving throws against fire-based attacks, and such attacks in\u00adflict only 50% of their normal damage.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has removed this arcane spell from the game. There is no direct 3rd level equivalent spell. However, there is a 4th level arcane spell, as described below:\nProtection from Elemental Energy\nLevel: 4\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 1 turn/level\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen this spell is cast, the recipient receives complete protection from one damage type: acid, cold, fire, or lightning. 100% of the damage from the selected source of energy will be absorbed, and the target creature will become completely immune to the effects of spells based on that element. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative, but each time a different damage type can be selected.\nThere is also the new 2nd level arcane spell described below:\nResist Elements\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Abjuration\nSphere: Protection\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 1 turn + 1 round/level\nCasting Time: 2\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nUpon the casting of this spell, the recipient\u2019s resistance to all forms of elemental damage is increased by 25%. This effect will last for the duration of the spell or until dispelled. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative."}
{"id": "56833", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56833", "title": "Protection From Good", "text": "Protection From Good creates a magical barrier around the target to help safeguard it against good sources of harm.\nThis innate spell was introduced by Beamdog for the and encountered during the companion quest &lt;a href=\"Hexxat%27s%20request\"&gt;Hexxat's request&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=\"Raffiyah\"&gt;Raffiyah&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere is also a Protection from Good 10'radius version as well (OHBPROH1.spl)\nGameplay.\nThe spell isn't for use by the player.\nProtection from good provides the recipient with a 2-point bonus to &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; against creatures with a good alignment.\nAny &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect or a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell will remove it as well."}
{"id": "4756", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4756", "title": "Protection From Lightning", "text": "Protection from Lightning is a 4th level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt;. It grants immunity to electrical damage.\nIt has identical effects to the 5th level &lt;a href=\"wizard%20spell\"&gt;wizard spell&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Electricity%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Protection From Electricity&lt;/a&gt;, but has a longer casting time and a shorter duration.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced \"Protection From Lightning\" with \"Protection from Electricity\", a 5th level spell. See below for description:\nProtection from Electricity\nLevel: 5\nSchool: Abjuration\nSphere: Elemental, Protection\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 1 turn/level\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen a Protection from Electricity spell is cast, the recipient receives complete protection from all electrical-based attacks, whether magical or non-magical in origin. 100% of the damage from attacks like electric dragon breath will be absorbed, and the target creature will become completely immune to the effects of spells such as Lightning Bolt, Glyph of Warding, Call Lightning, and Chain Lightning. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative."}
{"id": "6221", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6221", "title": "Protection From Magic", "text": "Gameplay.\nThe caster places this scroll in one of their \"Quick Items\" slots then selects the item - this in turn brings up a targeting cursor.\nPlace the targeting cursor over a target creature on the map in range, or self, or a party member's portrait, and click to activate the scroll.\nThe scroll has zero casting time, and no projectile, so it should immediately render a \"bluish globe\" upon the designated creature for the duration of the protection effects.\nThat creature will now be under the effects of the \"Protection from Magic\".\nIf a player character is under the scroll's protection, an icon is shown (No. 28) titled \"Protection from Magic\" on their portrait.\nNotes - what occurs from this scroll's protection effects.\nHere are some facts and notes about what occurs when a \"Protection From Magic\" spell is cast from the scroll.\nBugs.\nAs of BG2EE 2.6, The Protection from Magic Scroll is not removing all buffs before going into effect. This is identified and corrected in &lt;a href=\"The%20Enhanced%20Edition%20Fixpack%20%28EEFP%29\"&gt;The Enhanced Edition Fixpack (EEFP)&lt;/a&gt;. Ref: (scrl07.itm)\nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes a few changes to the Scroll and spell (if you install that component, after being asked). These changes are made only if you are not playing with &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod, as Spell Revisions already implements this. From the SCS Readme:\nAllow Spellstrike to take down a Protection from Magic scroll (BG2,BGEE,BGT,EET)\nIn the original game, the protective sphere produced by a Protection from Magic scroll is completely impenetrable by any spell at all - if you use one, all a hostile wizard can do is run away or fight in melee. This component allows the most powerful mage anti-magic spell, the 9th level spell Spellstrike, to destroy the anti-magic sphere of one of these scrolls. It also allows the anti-magic ray of the &lt;a href=\"Hive%20Mother\"&gt;Hive Mother&lt;/a&gt; beholder to destroy the sphere.\nIf you are using the Icewind Dale spell system, Spellstrike and the Hive Mother ray can also destroy the &lt;a href=\"https%3A//icewinddale.fandom.com/wiki/Antimagic_Shell\"&gt;\"Antimagic Shell\"&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "5840", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5840", "title": "Protection From Magic Energy", "text": "Protection From Magic Energy bestows one target creature with 100% resistance to all &lt;a href=\"Magical%20damage\"&gt;Magical damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this to a single creature or self - it has a range of basically \"touch\" distance.\nWhen the spell casting is finished the recipient will show a brief color fade, and a 3D graphic rendered on their sprite.\nA text will display, reading \"Protection from Magic Energy\".\nAdditionally, a sound effect will audible when the spell expires.\nA player character will show an icon (No. 123) titled \"Protected from Magical Energy\" on their portrait for the spell's duration. \nThis spell will bestow the recipient with &lt;a href=\"Magical%20damage\"&gt;Magical damage&lt;/a&gt; resistance \"set\" to 100%.\nThis spell can be removed by any applicable &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; source or with a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nMultiple applications of this spell on the same creature will not increase magical energy resistance over 100%; the most current application will refresh the spell's duration.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset has no comparable spell to \"Protection from Magical Energy\" - the BG video game spell version is a creation of the developers.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its description. See below:\nProtection from Magic Energy\nLevel: 6\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 1 turn/level\nCasting Time: 6\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen a Protection from Magic Energy spell is cast, the recipient receives complete protection from all magic damage-based attacks. 100% of the damage from attacks like Cause Wound will be absorbed, and the target creature will become completely immune to the effects of spells such as Magic Missile, Skull Trap, Disintegrate, and Horrid Wilting. This effect lasts for the duration of the spell or until dispelled. Certain creatures are immune to the effects of this spell, including all undead."}
{"id": "20442", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20442", "title": "Protection From Magic Weapons", "text": ""}
{"id": "5841", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5841", "title": "Protection From Magical Weapons", "text": "Protection From Magical Weapons gives the wizard complete invulnerability to all magical weapons but does not block normal (non-enchanted) weapons.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this spell to self only.\nUpon completion of the spell a text is displayed reading \"Protected from Magical Weapons\".\nThe caster has a brief 3D effect and color glow animation rendered over their sprite.\nA player character shows an icon (No. 71) titled \"Protection From Magical Weapons\" on their portrait for the spell's duration.\nAdditionally, a sound effect will audible when the spell expires.\nThe spell implements protection from all weapon attacks (melee or missile) that are classified as \"magical\".\nThis spell can be removed by an appropriate &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect, or a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nThis spell is incompatible with &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Normal Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mantle\"&gt;Mantle&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Mantle\"&gt;Improved Mantle&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Absolute%20Immunity\"&gt;Absolute Immunity&lt;/a&gt; spells; they will not be allowed to cast if attempted.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset has a 6th level Wizard spell titled \"Invulnerability to Magical Weapons\". This spell creates an immobile, faintly shimmering magical sphere around the caster that cannot be penetrated by magical blunt, edged, or missile weapons; all such weapons are harmlessly deflected (missile weapons strike the sphere, then immediately fall to the ground). However, the sphere offers no protection against magically-created creatures (such as golems) or from creatures whose attacks are magically based (such as the gaze of a medusa).\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its description. See below:\nProtection from Magical Weapons\nLevel: 6\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 4 rounds\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: Caster\nSaving Throw: None\nThis spell creates an immobile, faintly shimmering magical sphere around the caster that cannot be penetrated by magical weapons; all such weapons are harmlessly deflected (missile weapons strike the sphere, then immediately fall to the ground). This includes weapons that are blessed or enchanted as well as attacks of especially powerful monsters. Due to this spell\u2019s short casting time and duration, it is mainly used to buy the wizard a few rounds in the thick of combat. The spell\u2019s effect lasts for the duration of the spell or until dispelled."}
{"id": "5026", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5026", "title": "Protection From Normal Missiles", "text": "Protection From Normal Missiles is a third-level &lt;a href=\"wizard%20spell\"&gt;wizard spell&lt;/a&gt; in the .\nGameplay.\nThe wizard casts this spell and my apply it to one creature, including self - the range is only 1 foot.\nThe spell launches a sparkling green projectile at the targeted creature, which then affects the target with a color change - if the target is a party member, their portrait will display an icon (No. 11) labeled as \"Protection From Missiles\", and the combat log will display a text reading \"Protected from Normal Missiles\".\nWhen the spell is first applied to a target a sound effect is audibled, and another when the spell expires.\nWhen the spell manifests, the targeted creature is surrounded by a semitransparent, purple-colored cylinder graphic that remains over the protected creature for the spell's duration, or until the spell is removed.\nThis spell can be taken down by a &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect or a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe spell protects against certain projectiles, nine different types altogether.\nIf any missiles use that particular projectile, then the wizard will not be struck, and the combat screen will display a \"Weapon ineffective\" message.\nWhen a weapon has both a melee and ranged mode, Protection From Normal Missiles only affects the ranged mode (because this mode uses a \"projectile\").\nMissiles blocked by the spell.\nThe table lists , &lt;a href=\"bolts\"&gt;bolts&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"bullets\"&gt;bullets&lt;/a&gt; first, followed by &lt;a href=\"throwing%20hammers\"&gt;throwing hammers&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20axes\"&gt;axes&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20spears\"&gt;spears&lt;/a&gt;, then &lt;a href=\"darts\"&gt;darts&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"throwing%20daggers\"&gt;throwing daggers&lt;/a&gt;. It can be sorted alphabetically or by . \nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its title, effects and duration. See below for description:\nProtection from Missiles\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 3\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nBy means of this spell, the wizard bestows upon a creature total invulnerability to hurled and projected missiles such as arrows, axes, bolts, javelins, and sling stones. This spell does not convey any protection from magical attacks such as Fireballs, Lightning Bolts, or Magic Missiles, but magically created missiles such as Melf\u2019s Acid Arrows, Melf\u2019s Minute Meteors, and Flame Arrows will be harmlessly deflected."}
{"id": "5855", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5855", "title": "Protection From Normal Weapons", "text": "Protection From Normal Weapons gives the wizard total invulnerability to non-magical weapons.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this spell to self only.\nUpon completion of the spell a text is displayed reading \"Protected from Normal Weapons\".\nThe caster has a brief 3D effect and color glow animation rendered over their sprite.\nA player character shows an icon (No. 70) titled \"Protection From Normal Weapons\" on their portrait for the spell's duration.\nAdditionally, a sound effect will audible when the spell expires.\nThe spell implements protection from all weapon attacks (melee or missile) that are classified as \"non magical\".\nThis spell can be removed by an appropriate &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect, or a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nThis spell is incompatible with &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, and if that spell is attempted, it will fail, a text will display, reading \"Cannot cast Protection From Magical Weapons when already protected from normal weapons\".\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset has no spell titled \"Protection from Normal Weapons\". However, there is a 5th-level Wizard spell known as \"Invulnerability to Normal Weapons\". This spell creates an immobile, faintly shim\u00admering magical sphere around the caster that cannot be penetrated by non-magical blunt weapons, edged weapons, or missile weapons. The caster can use these weapons from inside the sphere to attack opponents normally. Spells can also be cast through the sphere. Any effort to combine this spell with magics that grant immunity to magical weapons cause this spell to fail immediately.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its description. See below:\nProtection from Normal Weapons\nLevel: 5\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 1 round/level\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: Caster\nSaving Throw: None\nThis spell creates an immobile, faintly shimmering magical sphere around the caster that cannot be penetrated by non-magical weapons; all such weapons are harmlessly deflected (missile weapons strike the sphere, then immediately fall to the ground). This does not include weapons that are blessed or enchanted. The effect lasts for the duration of the spell or until dispelled."}
