{"id": "6225", "revid": "5653418", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6225", "title": "Protection From Petrification (protection scroll)", "text": "Protection From Petrification is a &lt;a href=\"protection%20scroll\"&gt;protection scroll&lt;/a&gt;, usable by everyone, that offers immunity to petrification \u2013 e.g. by attacks from &lt;a href=\"basilisks\"&gt;basilisks&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 for six hours."}
{"id": "27431", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27431", "title": "Protection From Petrification (scroll)", "text": "Protection From Petrification (scroll) might refer to:"}
{"id": "4989", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4989", "title": "Protection From Petrification (spell)", "text": "Protection From Petrification gives the target immunity to all forms of petrification.\nScrolls for this spell can be added to the spellbook through learning (chance to Write Magic) and can be used as a one-time only spell by a spell caster.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this spell to one creature or self at a range of basically \"touch\" distance.\nWhen the spell casting is finished, a short series of graphic effects renders on the recipient, including a color fade, lighting effect and a 3D graphic.\nA text will display, reading \"Gaze Reflection\".\nA player character will show an icon (No. 10) titled \"Protection From Petrification\" on their portrait for the spell's duration.\nAdditionally, a sound effect will audible when the spell expires.\nThis spell prevents the recipient from the &lt;a href=\"Petrified\"&gt;Petrified&lt;/a&gt; status effect - they are immune to being turned to stone as long as the spell is active.\nThe spell won't be able to cure or revert petrification upon a creature that is already turned to stone.\nThis spell can be removed with any &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect or the &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition has no 1st-level wizard spell titled \"Protection from Petrification\". However, at the 5th-level there is a spell titled \"Protection from Petrification, 10' Radius\". See the External link for further reading.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod hasn't changed this arcane spell, except for some minor internal coding and changing the capitalization of \"From\". See below for description:\nProtection from Petrification\nLevel: 1\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 1 hour\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nThis spell grants the recipient immunity to all petrification attacks. This includes basilisk and medusa gaze, cursed scrolls of petrification, etc."}
