{"id": "6204", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6204", "title": "Protection From Poison", "text": "Game Mechanic Note.\nThe \"Green\" protection scrolls are implementing their effects differently than a cast spell does. The Scrolls have no assigned \"Spell School\", and no assigned \"Spell Type\". As such they can't be removed by a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; effect as they are not a combat protection nor a specific protection. \nThe spell power level of the scroll is zero, and that means that any dispel magic effect will remove all the protections conferred by the scroll, even if the dispel effect was even a level 1 spell power.\nThe Protection from Poison Scroll protects against all poison damage and all poisoning effects. It also prevents Drunkedness or being &lt;a href=\"Intoxicated\"&gt;Intoxicated&lt;/a&gt;. Once applied to a creature the scroll cures poison effects. The scroll will not cure or remove intoxication (but &lt;a href=\"Slow%20Poison\"&gt;Slow Poison&lt;/a&gt; will). This scroll will not stack with other poison protection items, and the poison damage resistance will never exceed 100%."}
{"id": "5848", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5848", "title": "Protection From The Elements", "text": "Protection From The Elements raises the wizard\u2019s resistances to every elemental type, no matter the source.\nGameplay.\nWhen the spell is completed and cast on a creature, a text is displayed reading \"Protection From The Elements\", as well as 3D effect and a color fade is rendered over the sprite, and an icon is placed on the character's portrait.\nWhen the spell expires, an audible sound effect is heard.\nThe recipient of this spell is bestowed a temporary boost to resist &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;Cold damage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Electricity%20damage\"&gt;Electricity damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe elemental resistance modifier value is +75%, which is cumulative with any other similar elemental resistances already present on the creature.\nThe maximum game-allowed damage resistance modifier for these elemental resistances is 127%.\nValues over 100% can heal the creature when that particular elemental damage is incurred, for example if the creature has 110% fire resistance and incurs 40 fire damage, the targeted creature can be healed 4 hit points from that damage event.\nThis spell is affected by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects and can be removed with a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nNote.\nThe spell also boosts resistance to magical cold damage and magical fire damage, which are unused/unimplemented damage types in the unmodified game.\nThe spell is not stackable with a second spell application.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Ruleset has no 7th-level Wizard spell titled or equivalent to \"Protection From The Elements\" - there is however a 4th-level Wizard spell titled &lt;a href=\"https%3A//adnd2e.fandom.com/wiki/Protection_from_the_Elements_%28Wizard_Spell%29\"&gt;Protection from the Elements&lt;/a&gt;. That spell is very rare, and not included in most non \"Arabian\" campaigns. The Pen and Paper spell version is very different as well. Looks like the video game version is just a developer invention.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its duration, effects, and description. See below:\nProtection from the Elements\nLevel: 7\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 1 turn/2 levels\nCasting Time: 7\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen this spell is cast, it confers complete protection from all elemental attacks composed of acid, cold, electricity, or fire, whether magical or non-magical in origin. 100% of the elemental damage from attacks with weapons, wands, breath weapons, etc. will be absorbed, and the target creature will become completely immune to the effects of elemental spells. This effect lasts for the duration of the spell or until dispelled."}
{"id": "6217", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6217", "title": "Protection From Undead", "text": "Gameplay.\nThese scrolls are very powerful and work even against the strongest undead (&lt;a href=\"Lich\"&gt;Liches&lt;/a&gt; etc.), who basically can't attack the protected character. However, the protection can be removed if the enemy casts &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; / &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt;."}
