{"id": "51183", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51183", "title": "Psionic Ability", "text": "A Psionic Ability in the Baldur's Gate Infinity Engine games is basically an Innate Power or ability possessed by certain creatures in the game saga. Most notably these are the &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayer\"&gt;Mind Flayer&lt;/a&gt; race, the &lt;a href=\"Githyanki%20%28Race%29\"&gt;Githyanki Race&lt;/a&gt; and the Athasian Halflings in &lt;a href=\"The%20Planar%20Sphere\"&gt;The Planar Sphere&lt;/a&gt;, specifically &lt;a href=\"Entu\"&gt;Entu&lt;/a&gt;. All these creatures may be able to use one or more psionic abilities.\nOver the game series, the developers were fairly consistent in which creatures use psionic abilities, however, the philosophy behind how the abilities are designed is not as consistent. It is pretty clear from examining the files, that some abilities were based on a Wizard spell, and are almost identical to those.\nSome others were made from scratch and are closer to the idea behind how psionics are explained in the Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset.\nPsionic abilities are classified as either \"innate\", \"wizard,\" or \"psionic\", with the latter occurring in the Throne of Bhaal era of the game development.\nDescription.\nIn general terms, a Psionic Ability is an innate power initiated by a creature's own mind that can almost instantly apply some kind of potential effect upon oneself or a target.\nThe game assigns these abilities a specific SPIN.XXX file, similar to an arcane or divine magic spell would have. They behave in some similar ways to a spell cast, but they are different as well. They can be scripted to a creature to use, they can be \"memorized\" but more often than not will just be included in a creature's script. They typically can be used multiple times per battle, on a timed basis, or if specific conditions have occurred during the encounter. Most Psionics launch and produce a projectile that travels toward the target at varying speeds, the same as spell would. There are exceptions as well.\nCharacteristics of psionics.\nA Psionic Ability is usually launched instantly or near instantly.\nA Psionic Ability is usually not interruptible like a regular spell cast, as they are \"ForceSpell\" cast (a scripting execution command) - there are a few exceptions, such as when a player character assumes a Mind Flayer form with the &lt;a href=\"Shapechange\"&gt;Shapechange&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nA Psionic Ability that is \"ForceSpell\" cast is usually not affected by &lt;a href=\"Miscast%20Magic\"&gt;Miscast Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects, &lt;a href=\"Deafness%20effect\"&gt;Deafness effect&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Silence\"&gt;Silence&lt;/a&gt; effects. No verbal or somatic component is necessary.\nA Psionic Ability is a typically a non-magical effect (when coded in that manner). Thus, they are not influenced by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, and typically cannot be touched or affected by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects. As always, there are a few exceptions where the ability is not coded like this and is more spell-like than an innate non-magical design.\nA Psionic ability is usually not assigned to a \"School of Magic\" such as Necromancy, or Evocation, but some are. This means for some psionic abilities that specialist mages will get no saving throw modifiers against these powers, and the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt; arcane spell will not have any effect.\nA Psionic Ability typically has no assigned spell power level and is &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;level 0&lt;/a&gt;. The practical outcome of this is that protective spells that block spell levels have no effect, like &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt; for example. There are a several exceptions to this.\nA Psionic Ability may however have an assigned \"secondary type\" as many spells have, such as \"Offensive Damage\" or \"Disabling\", or \"Illusionary protection\". Some psionic powers do not. "}
{"id": "50641", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50641", "title": "Psionic Blast", "text": "Psionic Blast is an innate &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Ability\"&gt;Psionic Ability&lt;/a&gt; available to the &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayer\"&gt;Mind Flayer&lt;/a&gt; race. The ability is initiated via script by the AI. The effect is directed at a target in visible range of the source creature. The blast will require those creatures in the area of effect radius of the target to make a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. spell or suffer a &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; effect that lasts one turn. The effect is non-magical and can't be dispelled. \nPlayers who have transformed into a Mind Flayer via the 9th-Level Arcane Spell &lt;a href=\"Shapechange\"&gt;Shapechange&lt;/a&gt; have access to this ability via the innate abilities' menu. Transforming into another form, then back to Mind Flayer will reset this ability, allowing it to be cast again. \nThe Psionic Blast will bypass &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and cannot be blocked by spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;. It is party-friendly if cast by a &lt;a href=\"Shapechange\"&gt;Shapechanged&lt;/a&gt; party member.\nA more potent variety of this innate ability is often used by the more powerful illithids, such as the &lt;a href=\"Ulitharid\"&gt;Ulitharid&lt;/a&gt; - assigned as SPIN959.spl. This Psionic Blast variety has a -4 saving throw penalty.\nNote.\nMany &lt;a href=\"Githyanki%20%28Race%29\"&gt;Githyanki (Race)&lt;/a&gt; opponents have scripted use of a variant of Psionic Blast (which is a different spell), and during combat text displayed on the player's combat log will indicate when it is used. \nInternally, in the creature's script the spell is referred to as either &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Mind%20Blast%20%28githyanki%29\"&gt;Psionic Mind Blast&lt;/a&gt; or just Psionic Blast. See the link to read about the differences between the illithid and githyanki versions."}
{"id": "56191", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56191", "title": "Psionic Disintegrate", "text": "Psionic Disintegrate, or also sometimes just written as \"Disintegrate\", is a &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Ability\"&gt;Psionic Ability&lt;/a&gt; reserved for the &lt;a href=\"Githyanki\"&gt;Githyanki&lt;/a&gt; race creatures, some of which the game bestows this ability to, mostly from the and games.\nGameplay.\nThe githyanki creature aims this spell at a detected enemy, and it is a \"ForceSpell\" cast.\nThe spell exposes the target to a &lt;a href=\"Disintegrate%20effect\"&gt;Disintegrate effect&lt;/a&gt; that requires a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Death/poison to negate.\nA failed save will kill the target creature, kick the sprite from the party, force all inventory to drop, and if \"gore\" is enabled, destroy items not flagged as \"critical\". \nThis so-called Psionic ability is basically a clone of the Wizard spell &lt;a href=\"Disintegrate\"&gt;Disintegrate&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe spell effect can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, as well as Spell Protection defenses capable of deflecting/turning &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 6 effects, such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Alteration&lt;/a&gt; can also stymie this spell, as well as the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Mirroring\"&gt;Cloak of Mirroring&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "50642", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50642", "title": "Psionic Domination", "text": "Psionic Domination is an innate ability available to &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayer\"&gt;Mind Flayer&lt;/a&gt; creatures. The ability is initiated via script by the AI. The effect is directed at a single creature target in visible range of the source creature. The Domination will require the target to make a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. spell with a -2 penalty or suffer a &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Creature\"&gt;Dire Charm&lt;/a&gt; effect that lasts 45 seconds. The effect is non magical and can't be dispelled. Once the effect duration has expired or otherwise been lifted, the target creature will revert to its natural allegiance, which will most likely be hostile to the Mind Flayer.\nThe Psionic Domination will bypass &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and cannot be blocked by spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "56188", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56188", "title": "Psionic Inertial Barrier", "text": "Psionic Inertial Barrier, or also sometimes just written as \"Inertial Barrier\", is a &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Ability\"&gt;Psionic Ability&lt;/a&gt; reserved for the &lt;a href=\"Githyanki\"&gt;Githyanki&lt;/a&gt; race creatures, some of which the game bestows this ability to, mostly from the and games.\nGameplay.\nThe githyanki creature aims this spell at itself and the spell is \"ForceSpell\" cast.\nThe spell is applied (usually to oneself) as a combat protection.\nThe psionic ability functions almost identically to the Wizard spell &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt;. It has a duration of 5 Turns (300 seconds).\nThis spell is actually classified as a \"Psionic\" spell, but it really behaves like the Wizard spell, and it can be dispelled and taken down with a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt;.\nHowever, unlike the BG2EE Wizard spell version, this psionic version protects against all normal arrow, thrown axe, bolt, bullet, dart, thrown dagger and spear projectiles."}
{"id": "56190", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56190", "title": "Psionic Inflict Pain", "text": "Psionic Inflict Pain, or also sometimes just written as \"Inflict Pain\", is a &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Ability\"&gt;Psionic Ability&lt;/a&gt; reserved for the &lt;a href=\"Githyanki\"&gt;Githyanki&lt;/a&gt; race creatures, some of which the game bestows this ability to, mostly from the and games.\nGameplay.\nThe githyanki creature aims this spell at a detected enemy, and it is a \"ForceSpell\" cast.\nThe spell exposes the target to a &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; effect that requires a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Death/poison to negate.\nA failed save will afflict the target with a stunned state for 5 rounds (30 seconds) and be &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt;. \nIF the spell takes hold, a brief 3D graphic effect and color glow plays over the target, and text displays \"Stunned\", and the character portrait displays a \"Stun\" icon. \nThe spell effect can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, as well as Spell Protection defenses capable of deflecting/turning &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 7 effects, such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Conjuration&lt;/a&gt; can also stymie this spell.\nA &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect can remove the Stun effect."}
{"id": "56189", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56189", "title": "Psionic Life Drain", "text": "Psionic Life Drain, or also sometimes just written as \"Life Drain\", is a &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Ability\"&gt;Psionic Ability&lt;/a&gt; reserved for the &lt;a href=\"Githyanki\"&gt;Githyanki&lt;/a&gt; race creatures, some of which the game bestows this ability to, mostly from the and games.\nGameplay.\nThe githyanki creature aims this spell at a detected enemy, typically when the caster's Hit Points have been reduced (example, by 50%), and it is a \"ForceSpell\" cast.\nThe spell exposes the target to 1d6+4 &lt;a href=\"Magical%20damage\"&gt;Magical damage&lt;/a&gt;, and whatever the damage rolled is applied as a temporary addition to the caster's current hit points - these HP's can heal damage and potentially boost HP over the creatures maximum HP value. \nAny extra hit points fade away after one turn if there are any that exceed the creatures maximum HP value.\nThe spell plays a brief lighting effect and color fade over the target, and a sound effect when the spell hits, and when the hit point duration expires.\nThe spell effect is unaffected by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, but the internal &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; is 4, so most spell protections can block it, save &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Necromancy&lt;/a&gt; can also stymie this spell, as well as the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Mirroring\"&gt;Cloak of Mirroring&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis spell is basically a modified version of the &lt;a href=\"Larloch%27s%20Minor%20Drain\"&gt;Larloch's Minor Drain&lt;/a&gt; spell, but with a few changes."}
{"id": "50643", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50643", "title": "Psionic Maze", "text": "Psionic Maze is an innate ability available to a few &lt;a href=\"Githyanki%20%28Race%29\"&gt;Githyanki&lt;/a&gt;s such as &lt;a href=\"Simyaz\"&gt;Simyaz&lt;/a&gt;, various githyanki with &lt;a href=\"Kruin\"&gt;Kruin&lt;/a&gt;, a number of creatures in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Githyanki%20Encampment\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Githyanki Encampment&lt;/a&gt;, and in only, the &lt;a href=\"Gish%20%28githyanki%29\"&gt;Gish (githyanki)&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nThe effect is directed at a single creature target in visible range of the source creature. The Psionic Maze will require the target to make a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. spell with a -4 penalty or suffer a &lt;a href=\"Maze\"&gt;Maze&lt;/a&gt; effect that lasts a variable duration based on the victim's &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; score. The effect is non magical and can't be dispelled. \nThe Psionic ability will bypass &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and can be blocked by spell protections that prevent level 8 Spell Power to penetrate, such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Barbarian%20Rage\"&gt;Barbarian Rage&lt;/a&gt; will also protect against it. A &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Magic%20Shielding\"&gt;Potion of Magic Shielding&lt;/a&gt; will also block it since it ensures the saving throw always succeeds.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns this Psionic Ability to &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayer\"&gt;Mind Flayer&lt;/a&gt; creatures of all types as well as the &lt;a href=\"Githyanki%20%28Race%29\"&gt;Githyanki&lt;/a&gt;. It is one of the core &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Ability\"&gt;Psionic Ability&lt;/a&gt; that SCS modified Mind Flayers possess."}
{"id": "56186", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56186", "title": "Psionic Mind Blast (githyanki)", "text": "Psionic Mind Blast, or also sometimes just written as Psionic Blast, is a &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Ability\"&gt;Psionic Ability&lt;/a&gt; reserved for the &lt;a href=\"Githyanki\"&gt;Githyanki&lt;/a&gt; race creatures, some of which the game bestows this ability to, mostly from the and games.\nThis particular spell is different from the &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayer\"&gt;Mind Flayer&lt;/a&gt; version of their &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Blast\"&gt;Psionic Blast&lt;/a&gt;, which is generally more potent and has an area of effect.\nGameplay.\nThe githyanki creature aims this spell at a detectable target and the spell is \"ForceSpell\" cast at a party member or single target creature.\nThe mind blast uses the &lt;a href=\"Chromatic%20Orb\"&gt;Chromatic Orb&lt;/a&gt; projectile, and once it is launched it will unerringly home-in and strike the target.\nIt can be blocked by a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Conjuration&lt;/a&gt;.\nOn the other hand, the spell will bypass &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; - mainly because the internal spell components are coded as &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 0.\nAssuming the projectile strikes the target, it is exposed to a &lt;a href=\"Unconscious\"&gt;Unconscious&lt;/a&gt; effect, that is negated by a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spell.\nIf the saving throw fails, the target is made unconscious and &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt; for 25 seconds, and a 3D graphic effect plays over the sprite as well as a sound effect audibles. \nAdditional damage to the target won't awaken it, and as the spell effect isn't magical in nature, it can't be dispelled."}
{"id": "56192", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56192", "title": "Psionic Project Force", "text": "Psionic Project Force, or also sometimes just written as \"Project Force\", is a &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Ability\"&gt;Psionic Ability&lt;/a&gt; reserved for the &lt;a href=\"Githyanki\"&gt;Githyanki&lt;/a&gt; race creatures, some of which the game bestows this ability to, mostly from the and games.\nGameplay.\nThe githyanki creature aims this spell at a detected enemy, and it is a \"ForceSpell\" cast.\nThe spell exposes the target to a &lt;a href=\"Wing%20buffet\"&gt;Wing buffet&lt;/a&gt; effect that has no &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; and knocks backwards the target creature up to 20 feet away from the source for a duration of 2 seconds.\nAdditionally, 2d10 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt; is dealt, but a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Breath will reduce it by half.\nA second saving throw vs. Spell with a -10 penalty is necessary to prevent a 3 second &lt;a href=\"Unconscious\"&gt;Unconscious&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nThis knockback event is unaffected by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and Spell protections.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Abjuration&lt;/a&gt; can block it, and so can a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Shield\"&gt;Spell Shield&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "8810", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8810", "title": "Pugney", "text": "Pugney is the owner of the &lt;a href=\"Mithrest%20Inn\"&gt;Mithrest Inn&lt;/a&gt;. You can rent a room or buy a drink from him. Quaffing a couple of high priced drinks may gain you some current rumors about local events. Other than that, he has no information to give."}
{"id": "36206", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36206", "title": "Purification Stone", "text": "The Purification Stone is an which provides immunity to the &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Disease\"&gt;Disease&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;Status Effects&lt;/a&gt; and can be used to cast &lt;a href=\"Neutralize%20Poison\"&gt;Neutralize Poison&lt;/a&gt; once per day. This stone is given by the &lt;a href=\"Nereid\"&gt;Nereid&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River\"&gt;Underground River&lt;/a&gt; as a reward for completing the &lt;a href=\"Strunk%27s%20Elementals\"&gt;Strunk's Elementals&lt;/a&gt; quest in ."}
{"id": "7121", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7121", "title": "Purifier", "text": "Purifier +4 is an enchanted bastard sword which can only be used by non-evil aligned &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; class warriors. This item appears in and .\nGameplay.\nThe bastard sword inflicts 2d4+4 points of &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; with +4 additional points against chaotic evil aligned creatures.\nThe blade provides a -4 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus, weighs 6 pounds and it has a speed factor of 4. \nAlso, the weapon bestows the wielder with +20% &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; while equipped. \nAquisition.\nThe weapon can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt; level, within a &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20-%20Balor%20%28AR3008%29\"&gt;a specific chamber&lt;/a&gt;. \nThis chamber has a great rock column in the center of the area, which can be interacted with. \nThe rock has the following inscription chiseled onto it face:\nIf the character is not lawful good, or of any evil alignment, then nothing happens except for a text displayed, reading:\nIf an evil aligned character interacts with it, the stone will display a text reading: \nAt this point the room is bombarded by a &lt;a href=\"Meteor%20Swarm\"&gt;Meteor Swarm&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nIf a lawful good-aligned character interacts with the rock, they trigger a different text display:\nThe character has the Purifier +4 placed in their backpack. If full, it will appear on the ground.\nUpgraded Purifier.\nIt can be upgraded by &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt;, which requires the &lt;a href=\"Eye%20of%20Tyr\"&gt;Eye of Tyr&lt;/a&gt; and some gold.\nPurifier +5 now deals 2d4 +5 points of damage with +5 additional points of damage against chaotic evil aligned creatures, has a -5 THAC0 bonus, weighs 5 lbs and it has a speed factor of 3. Also, the weapon gives the wielder 30% magical resistance and it can be used twice per day to cast &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; and once per day to cast &lt;a href=\"Mass%20Cure\"&gt;Mass Cure&lt;/a&gt;. This weapon is now a very powerful weapon, perhaps the most powerful of its type along with &lt;a href=\"Foebane\"&gt;Foebane&lt;/a&gt;.\nBugs.\nAs of BG2EE 2.6, Several items that cast area-of-effect spells required creature targets but should not have: Cone of Cold via the White Dragon Scale, Dispel Magic via Purifier, Prismatic Spray via the Helm of Brilliance. This is identified and corrected in &lt;a href=\"The%20Enhanced%20Edition%20Fixpack%20%28EEFP%29\"&gt;The Enhanced Edition Fixpack (EEFP)&lt;/a&gt;. Ref: (chan20.itm, comps65.itm, helm16.itm, sw1h65.itm).\nAlthough the upgraded weapon's description claims that its Dispel Magic ability is cast at level 20, it actually scales with the character's divine caster level. On a test with a level 30 Thief (with Use Any Item) and a level 30 Paladin, the Thief was unable to dispel a level 8 Bard's Mirror Image using this weapon's Dispel Magic, whereas the Paladin was able to do it consistently. This bug does not apply to the Mass Cure ability, that one works properly (it's cast at level 20, no matter who wields the weapon)."}
